<h1>PRP Skin &amp; Hair, PRF Gel</h1><h2>Regenerative Aesthetics for Hair Restoration &amp; Skin Rejuvenation</h2><p>Watching your hair thin or your skin lose its firmness isn’t just cosmetic—it changes how you feel in your own skin. Most products are designed to mask these changes, not correct them.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, we take a different approach.</p><p>Using advanced regenerative therapies like PRP (platelet-rich plasma) and PRF (platelet-rich fibrin), we stimulate your body’s own repair systems—helping restore hair growth, rebuild collagen, and improve overall skin quality from within. Nothing synthetic. Nothing foreign. Just your biology, working the way it was designed to.</p><h2>What Are PRP &amp; PRF?</h2><p>PRP and PRF are both derived from a small sample of your own blood. Through a specialized centrifuge process, we isolate and concentrate powerful growth factors your body naturally uses to heal, repair, and regenerate tissue.</p><ul><li><p><strong>PRP (Platelet-Rich Plasma):</strong> A concentrated solution of growth factors that stimulates collagen production, improves skin tone and texture, and supports hair regrowth.</p></li><li><p><strong>PRF (Platelet-Rich Fibrin):</strong> A more advanced form of PRP that includes a fibrin matrix, allowing for a slower, sustained release of growth factors over time.</p></li></ul><p>Both treatments are grounded in well-established science across dermatology and regenerative medicine—and both are designed to improve function, not just appearance.</p><h2>PRP/PRF for Hair and Skin</h2><p>PRP (platelet-rich plasma) and PRF (platelet-rich fibrin) work by delivering concentrated growth factors directly into targeted areas—stimulating your body’s natural ability to repair, regenerate, and restore.</p><p>For the skin, these regenerative treatments boost collagen and elastin production, helping improve:</p><ul><li><p>Fine lines and wrinkles</p></li><li><p>Skin texture and tone</p></li><li><p>Acne scarring</p></li><li><p>Overall radiance and firmness</p></li></ul><p>For the scalp, PRP and PRF address hair thinning at the follicle level by:</p><ul><li><p>Reactivating dormant hair follicles</p></li><li><p>Increasing blood supply to the hair root</p></li><li><p>Supporting thicker, stronger hair growth over time</p></li></ul><p>These treatments are most effective in early-to-moderate hair thinning, when follicles are still present but underperforming—making them one of the most effective natural options for both men and women experiencing hair loss.</p><p>At REFRESH, we take a comprehensive approach. In addition to treating the scalp or skin directly, we evaluate underlying factors like hormone balance, nutrition, and overall health—because lasting results come from addressing the root cause, not just the symptom.</p><h2>Microneedling with PRP</h2><p>When paired with microneedling, PRP becomes even more effective.</p><p>Microneedling creates controlled micro-channels in the skin, triggering your natural healing response. When PRP is applied during this process, growth factors penetrate deeper—enhancing collagen production and accelerating skin repair.</p><p>This combination is ideal for:</p><ul><li><p>Acne scars</p></li><li><p>Fine lines</p></li><li><p>Enlarged pores</p></li><li><p>Uneven texture</p></li><li><p>Dull or aging skin</p></li></ul><p>Results develop gradually, revealing healthier, stronger, more radiant skin over time.</p><h2>PRF Gel — Advanced Regeneration &amp; Natural Volume</h2><p>PRF takes regenerative treatment a step further.</p><p>Using a slower processing method without additives, PRF forms a fibrin matrix—a natural scaffold that holds growth factors in place and releases them gradually over 10–14 days. This creates longer-lasting stimulation and more sustained tissue repair.</p><p>When transformed into <strong>PRF Gel</strong>, it becomes a powerful treatment that:</p><ul><li><p>Restores subtle, natural-looking volume</p></li><li><p>Improves skin quality and elasticity</p></li><li><p>Stimulates long-term collagen production</p></li><li><p>Improves under-eye hollows, facial contours, and overall skin health</p></li></ul><p>Unlike traditional fillers, PRF Gel doesn’t just add volume—it rebuilds your tissue over time.</p><h3>PRF Gel Under Eye Treatment</h3><p>This is one of the most requested treatments we see at REFRESH LKN - and for good reason. Hollowing under the eyes, dark circles, and that thin, crepey texture make people look tired even when they feel great. Traditional fillers in this delicate area can cause puffiness or that telltale bluish hue. PRF Gel is lighter, integrates naturally into the tissue, and gradually improves volume, skin quality, and discoloration without the risks associated with synthetic products. PRF under eye treatment is a real game-changer for clients who've been told "you look tired" one too many times.</p><h2>PRF Gel vs. Traditional Fillers</h2><p>Hyaluronic acid fillers provide immediate volume—but they are temporary and rely on a synthetic substance.</p><p>PRF Gel works differently.</p><ul><li><p>Uses <strong>100% your own biology</strong></p></li><li><p>Gradually improves volume and skin quality</p></li><li><p>No risk of allergic reaction</p></li><li><p>No migration or overfilled appearance</p></li><li><p>Enhances skin—not just shape</p></li></ul><p>For clients who want natural, regenerative results—especially in delicate areas like under the eyes—PRF Gel offers a more refined alternative.</p><h2>What to Expect During Treatment</h2><p>Your appointment begins with a small blood draw—quick and similar to routine lab work. Your sample is processed on-site in a centrifuge while we apply a topical numbing cream for comfort.</p><p>Once your PRP or PRF is prepared, our board-certified nurse practitioner performs every injection with precision, guided by your anatomy and treatment goals.</p><ul><li><p>Treatment time: ~45–60 minutes</p></li><li><p>Minimal downtime</p></li><li><p>Mild swelling or bruising possible for a few days</p></li></ul><p>For best results, most clients complete a series of:</p><ul><li><p><strong>2–3 sessions for PRF Gel</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>3–4 sessions for PRP hair restoration<br />
</strong>spaced about 4–6 weeks apart, with maintenance treatments as needed.</p></li></ul><h2>Results &amp; Timeline</h2><p>PRP and PRF work by stimulating your body—not masking symptoms—so results develop gradually.</p><ul><li><p><strong>Hair:</strong> Reduced shedding within weeks, visible growth at 3–6 months</p></li><li><p><strong>Skin:</strong> Improved tone and texture within weeks, full collagen results at 3–6 months</p></li></ul><p>The outcome is subtle, natural, and long-lasting—because it’s built by your own body.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How much does PRP or PRF cost?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the treatment area and whether therapies are combined. We provide full, transparent pricing during your consultation, including package options for treatment series.</p><h3>Does PRP for hair loss work for women?</h3><p>Yes. PRP is highly effective for female hair thinning and is one of our most requested treatments for women experiencing hormonal or stress-related hair loss.</p><h3>How should I prepare for treatment?</h3><p>Stay well-hydrated and avoid anti-inflammatory medications (like ibuprofen) for a few days prior, as they can affect platelet function. We’ll provide full prep instructions before your appointment.</p><h3>Can PRP or PRF be combined with other treatments?</h3><p>Absolutely. These therapies pair well with microneedling, laser treatments, and other aesthetic services. We’ll guide the timing to ensure optimal results.</p><h3>What's the difference between PRP and PRF?</h3><p>Both are derived from your own blood, but PRF is processed differently and contains a fibrin matrix that releases growth factors more gradually. PRP tends to work faster while PRF offers a more sustained response over time. We'll recommend the best option based on what you're treating and the results you're hoping for.</p><p><strong>Is PRF better than PRP?</strong></p><p>They serve different purposes. PRP is excellent for stimulating repair and hair growth, while PRF provides longer-lasting, more sustained regeneration and is ideal for areas needing both volume and skin improvement.</p><h3>Are results permanent?</h3><p>Results are long-lasting but not permanent. Maintenance treatments every 6–12 months help sustain improvements as natural aging continues.</p><h3>Do you offer financing for PRP treatment series?</h3><p>We understand that a multi-session series is an investment. We can walk you through available payment options during your consultation so you can choose what works best for your budget. Just ask - we want this to feel accessible, not stressful.</p><h2>Schedule Your Consultation</h2><p>If you’re starting to notice changes in your hair or skin, the best next step is a conversation.We’ll evaluate where you are, what’s contributing to those changes, and whether PRP or PRF is the right approach for your goals. No pressure—just honest, personalized guidance.</p>
<hr>
<h1>Injectables</h1><p>You want to look like yourself - just a little more rested, a little more refreshed. Not frozen. Not overdone. Not like someone else. That's exactly where we come in. At REFRESH LKN, every injectable treatment we perform is guided by one simple principle: you should still look like you. Our board-certified nurse practitioner personally performs every cosmetic injectable treatment - your care is never handed off to rotating staff or someone you've never met. Whether you're curious about BOTOX®, considering dermal fillers for the first time, or interested in regenerative treatments like PRP and PRF, we offer the full range of cosmetic injectables at our clinic in Cornelius. We'll walk you through everything, answer every question, and create a plan based on your face, your goals, and your comfort level. No pressure. No cookie-cutter approach. Just honest guidance from someone who does this every single day.</p><h2>Wrinkle Relaxers (BOTOX®, Dysport®, JEUVEAU®, and DAXXIFY®)</h2><p>Neuromodulators like BOTOX®, Dysport®, JEUVEAU®, and DAXXIFY® work by gently relaxing the muscles responsible for dynamic wrinkles - the ones that form when you squint, smile, or furrow your brow. Over time, those repeated muscle movements etch lines into the skin that don't go away even when your face is at rest. A few precise injections can soften forehead lines, crow's feet, frown lines between the brows (the dreaded "11s"), platysma neck bands, and more. We also use wrinkle relaxers for subtle brow lifts and lip flips, which can make a surprisingly noticeable difference.</p><p>Here's the thing most people worry about: looking frozen. We get it. And honestly, that's almost always the result of too much product or possibly placement - not the product itself. Our approach to natural-looking BOTOX® results is about preserving your expressions, not erasing them. You should still be able to raise your eyebrows and laugh without your face looking like it forgot how. Treatments take about 10 to 15 minutes, require no downtime, and fit easily into a lunch break. Clients throughout Cornelius, Davidson, and Huntersville count on us for wrinkle relaxers that look effortless, because that's exactly how results should feel.</p><h2>Dermal Fillers &amp; Facial Volume</h2><h3>What Dermal Fillers Are</h3><h2>What Are Dermal Fillers?</h2><p>Dermal fillers are injectable treatments designed to restore volume, enhance facial contours, and soften lines that develop with age. Most commonly made from hyaluronic acid—a substance naturally found in the body—fillers work by adding structure beneath the skin to create a smoother, more youthful appearance.</p><p>They are often used to treat areas such as:</p><ul><li><p>Lips for added volume and definition</p></li><li><p>Cheeks for lift and contour</p></li><li><p>Nasolabial folds (smile lines)</p></li><li><p>Under-eye hollows</p></li><li><p>Jawline and chin for structure</p></li></ul><p>Results are typically visible immediately and can last anywhere from several months to over a year, depending on the product used and treatment area.</p><p>While dermal fillers are highly effective for restoring volume, they do not stimulate your body’s own regenerative processes in the same way treatments like PRP or PRF do. That’s why many clients choose a combination approach—or opt for regenerative therapies when they’re looking for more natural, gradual improvement driven by their own biology.</p><h3>What Fillers Treat</h3><p>Wrinkles get a lot of attention, but volume loss is often what ages a face the most. When you lose fullness in your cheeks, temples, or under-eye area, it changes the entire balance of your face - creating shadows, deepening folds, and making you look tired even when you're not. Dermal fillers like JUVÉDERM®, Restylane®, RHA® Collection, and REVANESSE LIPS® restore that lost volume and can also smooth nasolabial folds, soften marionette lines, and bring definition back to the jawline and chin. Different fillers have different densities and consistencies, and we choose specific products based on where they're being placed and what kind of result we're after. A filler that works beautifully in the cheeks isn't the right choice for lips, and vice versa. That's why having an experienced, board-certified injector in North Carolina who understands facial anatomy makes all the difference in your outcome.</p><h3>Lip Filler at REFRESH</h3><p>We know - lip filler can feel intimidating. You've seen the overfilled results on social media and thought, "absolutely not." Fair. But well-done lip filler doesn't look like that. At REFRESH, our goal with lip filler is to enhance your natural lip shape, not redesign it. Maybe you want a little more definition in your border, some added fullness to your upper lip, or just a bit of hydration and symmetry. That's enough. We use numbing to keep you comfortable, and while some swelling is normal for the first couple of days, the final result settles into something soft, balanced, and unmistakably you. Clients search for lip filler near me hoping to find someone they can trust with this particular treatment - and that trust is something we take seriously every single time.</p><p>If you're ready to talk about what's possible for your face, we'd love to hear from you. Call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online to get started.</p><p><strong>Facial Contouring and Balancing</strong></p><p>Facial contouring isn't just about filling lines - it's about shaping. Strategic filler placement along the jawline, chin, and midface can create structure and definition—enhancing the way your face photographs, improving shadowing, and optimizing how your skin catches and reflects light—while elevating how you feel when you catch your reflection. Think of it as sculpting, not just smoothing. Our nurse practitioners evaluate your full face as a composition - bone structure, proportions, symmetry - and use that assessment to place product where it will make the most meaningful impact. In many cases, combining BOTOX® or another neuromodulator with filler gives us the best results, because relaxing certain muscles while restoring volume in others creates a more balanced, refreshed appearance. Non-surgical facial contouring has become one of the most popular requests we see from clients across the Charlotte area, Mooresville, and beyond, and the results can be striking without a single incision.</p><h2>What to Expect at Your Visit</h2><h3>Consultation &amp; Planning</h3><p>Every new client at REFRESH starts with a real conversation - not a sales pitch. Our nurse practitioner will sit down with you, assess your facial anatomy, listen to what's been bothering you, and talk through your options honestly. You don't need to come in knowing treatment names or specific products. Just tell us what you're noticing. We'll explain why we're recommending something, not just what it is, so you feel confident in every decision. Sometimes we'll suggest pairing injectables with a laser treatment or medical-grade skincare when it would make a real difference - but only when it's genuinely in your best interest.</p><h3>During &amp; After Treatment</h3><p>On treatment day, we'll cleanse the area, apply numbing or ice if needed, and get to work. Most injectable sessions take between 15 and 45 minutes depending on what we're doing. BOTOX® and other neuromodulators typically show full results in about 14 days. Filler results are visible right away, though you'll see the final outcome once swelling settles - usually within about two weeks. Some bruising, mild swelling, and tenderness are completely normal afterward, and we'll send you home with clear aftercare instructions. You'll know exactly what to do and what to watch for. Nothing about this process should feel like a mystery.</p><h2>Schedule Your Consultation</h2><p>Whether you're considering your very first injectable treatment or you're looking for a new provider who'll take the time to really listen, we're here for you. REFRESH Medical Spa &amp; Wellness is located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, in Cornelius - right in the heart of Lake Norman and easy to reach from Huntersville, Davidson, Mooresville, and the greater Charlotte area. We believe you deserve personalized, natural-looking results from an experienced, board-certified provider who knows your face and your goals. That's what we deliver, every time.</p><p><a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call <strong>980-216-8484</strong> to schedule your injectable consultation at REFRESH LKN. We can't wait to meet you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How often do I need TOX treatments?</h3><p>Most clients come in every three to four months to maintain results, though some find they can stretch treatments longer with consistent appointments over time. We'll help you build a maintenance schedule that fits your budget and your goals, so you're never guessing about timing.</p><h3>Can I combine TOX and dermal fillers in one visit?</h3><p>Absolutely - and it's actually one of the most common requests we see. Treating wrinkles and volume loss in the same session often gives a more balanced result than addressing just one. Your provider will map out what makes sense based on your specific needs.</p><h3>What should I avoid before or after treatment?</h3><p>Before your appointment, avoid blood thinners, alcohol, and supplements like fish oil and vitamin E for at least 48 hours - these increase bruising risk. Afterward, skip strenuous exercise, hot showers, and direct pressure on treated areas for 24 to 48 hours.</p><h3>How do I know which filler is right for me?</h3><p>That's exactly what the consultation is for. Different fillers vary in thickness, flexibility, and longevity, and each one performs best in specific areas of the face. Your provider will match the product to the treatment area and the look you want - you won't need to research brands beforehand.</p><h2>SCULPTRA® </h2><h3>What Is Sculptra® (PLLA)?</h3><h3>For many clients at REFRESH LKN, Sculptra becomes a foundational part of their treatment plan, often combined with other aesthetic services to create balanced, natural-looking results that evolve beautifully over time.</h3><h3>Before Treatment</h3><p>Everything starts with a consultation at REFRESH LKN. Our nurse practitioners will assess your facial structure, ask about your goals, review your medical history, and set expectations that are honest and grounded. This isn't a rushed appointment where someone tries to upsell you. It's a thoughtful evaluation of what will actually give you the results you're after.</p><p>In the days leading up to treatment, we'll ask you to avoid blood thinners, alcohol, and certain supplements like fish oil and vitamin E - all of which can increase bruising. We'll give you a clear pre-treatment checklist so there are no surprises.</p><h3>During and After</h3><p>Each session typically takes thirty to forty-five minutes. The product is mixed with lidocaine for comfort, and we apply topical numbing beforehand. Injection technique matters enormously with SCULPTRA® - precise placement and proper depth are what separate a beautiful, even result from a mediocre one. This is exactly why our practitioner handles every treatment personally.</p><p>Afterward, you'll follow what's known as the 5-5-5 rule: massage the treated areas for five minutes, five times a day, for five days. This helps distribute the product evenly and encourages smooth collagen formation. Temporary swelling, tenderness, and some redness at the injection sites are completely normal and typically resolve within a few days. Most people head right back to their regular routine - picking up kids from school, running to meetings in Cornelius or Huntersville, all of it. Downtime is minimal.</p><h2>SCULPTRA® vs. Other Options</h2><p>Hyaluronic acid fillers like JUVÉDERM® and Restylane® give you instant volume that lasts several months to a year or more, and they're reversible - which makes them ideal for targeted areas like lips or under-eye hollows. SCULPTRA® works differently. It's a gradual process that addresses broader volume loss and actually improves skin quality over time. Think of it as facial rejuvenation without surgery, focused on rebuilding rather than replacing.</p><p>Treatments like RF microneedling with VirtueRF® or laser resurfacing with CoolPeel® - both available at REFRESH - complement SCULPTRA® beautifully by addressing texture, tone, and fine lines at the skin's surface while SCULPTRA® rebuilds structure underneath. Many of our clients combine approaches for a result that covers all the bases. Skin, tone, texture, definition - all thoughtfully enhanced.</p><p>The right plan depends entirely on you. During your consultation, we'll map out what makes the most sense for your face, your goals, and your timeline.</p><h2>Schedule Your Consultation</h2><p>We built REFRESH LKN to be the kind of place where you can walk in, say "something doesn't look right and I don't know what to do about it," and get an honest, expert answer. No jargon. No pressure. Just a board-certified nurse practitioner who will look at your face, listen to your concerns, and help you understand your options - whether that's SCULPTRA®, something else entirely, or a combination that gets you where you want to be.</p><p>We're located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, in Cornelius - right in the heart of Lake Norman and easy to reach from Denver, Mooresville, Davidson, and throughout the Charlotte metro. If you've been thinking about this, trust that instinct. <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We'd love to meet you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How much does SCULPTRA® cost?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the number of vials needed and how many sessions your treatment plan includes, so it varies from person to person. We'll give you a clear cost breakdown during your consultation so you know exactly what to expect before committing to anything.</p><h3>Am I a good candidate if I've had dermal fillers before?</h3><p>Absolutely - many of our clients have existing hyaluronic acid filler and transition to SCULPTRA® for longer-lasting, broader results. Our nurse practitioner will evaluate what's currently in place and design a plan that works with it, not against it.</p><h3>How many vials of SCULPTRA® will I need?</h3><p>Most patients get two vials per session, and 2-3 sessions depending on age, degree of volume loss, and which areas are being treated. This is something we determine together during your consultation after assessing your facial structure in person.</p><h3>Does SCULPTRA® work on areas other than the face?</h3><p>SCULPTRA® can be used on the décolletage, buttocks, and hands to stimulate collagen in those areas as well. During your appointment at REFRESH, we'll discuss which treatment areas make sense for your specific goals and what to realistically expect.</p><h3>What if I don't complete all recommended sessions?</h3><p>You'll still see some benefit - collagen stimulation begins with the first treatment. However, partial treatment typically yields partial results, and you may not achieve the full structural improvement that a complete series delivers.</p><h3>Does REFRESH offer financing for SCULPTRA® treatments?</h3><p>We want treatments to be accessible, so we're happy to discuss payment options when you come in for your consultation. Our team can walk you through what's available so cost doesn't have to be the thing that holds you back.</p>
<hr>
<h1>PDO Thread Lifts (PDO Max™ Threads)</h1><p>If you’re starting to notice skin laxity—along the jawline, cheeks, brows, or neck—but you’re not quite ready for surgery, PDO thread lifts offer a powerful, in-between solution. Using PDO Max™ threads, this treatment provides an immediate lift while also stimulating your body’s natural collagen production for longer-term improvement.</p><p>PDO (polydioxanone) threads are dissolvable sutures placed just beneath the skin to reposition and support tissue. Once placed, they create a subtle but noticeable lift in areas that have begun to descend. But the real benefit continues after you leave—over the next several months, your body responds by producing new collagen around the threads, improving firmness, texture, and overall skin quality. As the threads gradually dissolve, what’s left behind is stronger, more supported skin.</p><p>This treatment is ideal for softening jowls, lifting the midface, improving jawline definition, and tightening lax skin in the neck. Results are natural—not overdone—and designed to restore, not change, your appearance.</p><h2>Before Your PDO Thread Lift (PDO Max™ Threads)</h2><p>A little preparation goes a long way in ensuring a smooth treatment and optimal results. Before your PDO thread lift, we’ll start with a personalized consultation to assess your skin, facial structure, and goals. This allows us to determine if PDO Max™ threads are the right fit for you and design a treatment plan that delivers natural, balanced results.</p><p>In the days leading up to your appointment, we typically recommend avoiding blood-thinning medications and supplements—such as aspirin, ibuprofen, fish oil, and vitamin E—unless medically necessary, as these can increase the risk of bruising. It’s also best to avoid alcohol for 24–48 hours prior to treatment.</p><p>Come to your appointment with clean skin, free of makeup, and plan for a relatively low-key day afterward. While downtime is minimal, giving your body time to settle and heal will help you get the best outcome.</p><p>If you have a history of cold sores, are prone to bruising, or have any upcoming events, let us know during your consultation so we can plan accordingly. Our goal is to make the entire process—from preparation to results—feel seamless, comfortable, and fully tailored to you.</p><h2>During &amp; After Your PDO Thread Lift</h2><p>Your PDO thread lift with PDO Max™ threads is performed comfortably in-office and typically takes about 45–60 minutes, depending on the areas treated. We begin by thoroughly numbing the treatment areas using lidocaine to ensure you’re relaxed and comfortable throughout the procedure. While you may feel some light pressure or movement as the threads are placed, most clients are pleasantly surprised by how easy the experience is.</p><p>Immediately after treatment, you may notice a visible lift, along with some mild swelling, tenderness, or bruising—this is completely normal and typically resolves within a few days. We’ll guide you through simple aftercare, including avoiding strenuous activity, excessive facial movement, and sleeping on your side for about a week to allow the threads to settle properly.</p><p>Most clients return to their normal routine within 24–48 hours, with results continuing to improve over time. As collagen production increases over the next 8–12 weeks, your skin becomes firmer, smoother, and more supported. Results typically last 12–18 months, depending on your skin, lifestyle, and overall treatment plan.</p><h2>FAQs</h2><p><strong>How is this different from filler?<br />
</strong>Filler adds volume to specific areas, while PDO threads physically lift and reposition tissue. They also stimulate collagen, making them a great complement to filler rather than a replacement.</p><p><strong>Will I look overdone or “pulled”?<br />
</strong>No. When performed correctly, thread lifts create a subtle, natural lift. The goal is to look refreshed—not different.</p><p><strong>Are the threads permanent?<br />
</strong>No. PDO threads dissolve naturally over time, but the collagen they stimulate helps maintain results even after they’re gone.</p><p><strong>Is there downtime?<br />
</strong>Downtime is minimal. Most clients experience mild swelling or bruising for a few days, but it’s typically easy to manage and short-lived.</p><p><strong>Who is a good candidate?<br />
</strong>Ideal candidates have mild to moderate skin laxity, no history of keloid scarring, and want a noticeable lift without surgery. It’s also a great option for those looking to maintain results or delay more invasive procedures.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, PDO thread lifts with PDO Max™ threads are part of a thoughtful, customized approach to facial rejuvenation—designed to lift, support, and restore your natural structure with results that build over time.</p>
<hr>
<h1>Sclerotherapy</h1><p>You know exactly which veins you're trying to hide. The purple web creeping across the back of your calf. The bluish cluster behind your knee that showed up a few years ago and never left. You've stopped reaching for the shorts you used to love. Skirts feel like a risk. And living near Lake Norman - where the weather practically begs you to be poolside or out on the water - makes it that much harder to just ignore them.</p><p>Here's what most people don't realize: spider veins on legs aren't always purely cosmetic. They can ache. They can throb after a long day. Your legs might feel heavy or restless, and you're left wondering if it's "bad enough" to do something about. It is. Sclerotherapy is the gold-standard, minimally invasive vein procedure for eliminating spider veins and small varicose veins - no surgery, no significant downtime, just visible results. At REFRESH LKN, every vein treatment is personally overseen by our board-certified nurse practitioner. You're not handed off. You're cared for - start to finish - by a vein specialist near Lake Norman who truly knows what she's doing.</p><h2>What Is Sclerotherapy?</h2><p>Sclerotherapy is a form of vein injection therapy that's been used safely and effectively for decades. The concept is straightforward: we inject a saline or chemical sclerosant solution directly into the damaged vein using a very fine needle. That solution irritates the lining of the vein, causing it to collapse and seal shut. Over time, your body naturally reabsorbs the closed vein, and it fades from view.</p><p>It's the most effective non-surgical approach for spider veins, broken capillaries, and smaller varicose veins - and it works remarkably well. The procedure falls under our injectables category here at REFRESH, which means it's delivered with the same precision, attention to detail, and personalized care we bring to every treatment we offer. There's no guesswork involved. We assess your veins, understand your goals, and treat what's actually there - not what a textbook says to do.</p><h2>Spider Vein Treatment at REFRESH LKN</h2><h3>Who Is a Good Candidate?</h3><p>If you can see spider veins or small varicose veins on your legs - and they bother you cosmetically, physically, or both - you're likely a great candidate. Many of our clients come in because they're tired of covering up, but some also experience discomfort like aching, swelling, or that nagging heavy-leg feeling. Both are valid reasons to seek treatment.</p><p>There are a few situations where we'd pause or explore alternatives. If you're currently pregnant or have certain blood clotting disorders, sclerotherapy may need to wait. That's exactly why we start with a thorough consultation. We evaluate your vein health, review your medical history, and create a plan that makes sense for you specifically - never a one-size-fits-all approach.</p><h3>Common Treatment Areas</h3><p>The most frequently treated areas are the calves, thighs, shin area - where spider veins tend to show up and settle in. Vascular lesion treatment can also address smaller broken capillaries and reticular veins, which are those slightly deeper "feeder" veins that often contribute to visible clusters on the surface. Some of our clients choose to combine sclerotherapy with other cosmetic vein treatments at REFRESH LKN for more complete results, and we're always happy to map that out together.</p><h2>What to Expect During Leg Vein Injections</h2><h3>Before Your Appointment</h3><p>A little preparation goes a long way. In the days leading up to your session, avoid anti-inflammatory medications like ibuprofen, as they can increase bruising. On the day of your appointment, skip any lotion or moisturizer on your legs and wear loose, comfortable clothing. If compression stockings have been recommended, bring those along. We'll walk you through everything during your consultation so there are no surprises - just clear, personalized guidance from our team.</p><h3>During the Procedure</h3><p>Here's what actually happens. You'll be positioned comfortably, and your provider uses a very fine needle to inject the sclerosant solution into each targeted vein. Most sessions address multiple veins in one sitting. The sensation? Honest answer - you'll feel a slight pinch at the injection site and sometimes a mild cramping that fades within seconds. No anesthesia is needed. The whole process typically takes 15 to 30 minutes, and the careful, precise technique we use at REFRESH means every injection is intentional and deliberate.</p><p>If you've been thinking about scheduling, there's no reason to wait. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online - we'll get you in for a consultation and take it from there.</p><h3>After Treatment and Recovery</h3><p>Right after your session, you'll put on compression stockings and wear them for the period we recommend. Walking the same day is actually encouraged - it helps circulation and supports healing. What you'll want to avoid for one to two weeks is strenuous exercise and direct sun exposure on the treated areas. The veins may look slightly worse before they look better. Bruising, some darkening, a little tenderness - all normal and temporary. Most people return to their regular routine immediately. This is a truly minimally invasive vein procedure, and the recovery reflects that.</p><h2>Sclerotherapy Results and Timeline</h2><p>Let's set honest expectations, because that matters more than hype. Spider veins typically begin fading within three to six weeks after treatment. Larger veins can take three to four months to fully resolve. Some veins clear beautifully after a single session, while others need two or three treatments spaced several weeks apart for complete clearance. It depends on the size, number, and depth of the veins we're treating.</p><p>The good news? Once a treated vein is gone, it's gone for good. It won't come back. However, your body can develop new spider veins over time - genetics, hormones, aging, and lifestyle all play a role. That's why periodic maintenance sessions can be a smart move to keep your legs looking clear year after year. At REFRESH, we track your progress closely and adjust your treatment plan based on how your body responds. Your results guide the process, not a rigid plan.</p><h2>Why Choose REFRESH for Spider Vein in Cornelius NC</h2><p>There's no shortage of places offering vein treatments in the Charlotte area. So why REFRESH LKN? Because we do things differently - and the difference matters when a needle is going into your veins.</p><p>Our board-certified nurse practitioner personally performs every sclerotherapy treatment. Your care is never delegated to a technician. That level of direct clinical expertise means more precise injections, better results, and a provider who can answer your questions in real time - because she's the one doing the work.</p><p>We're also Lake Norman's only wellness &amp; aesthetic clinic combining advanced medical aesthetics with wellness services under one roof. That means your vein care isn't treated as an isolated concern. It's part of a whole-person approach to how you look and feel. If you want to pair sclerotherapy with a skin rejuvenation treatment or explore other services while you're here, we can build a plan that covers all of it.</p><p>Our Cornelius location makes us easy to reach whether you're coming from Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, or anywhere across the greater Charlotte area. And our environment is nothing like a sterile vein clinic. This is a comfortable, welcoming space where medical spa vein care meets genuine warmth. You'll feel the difference the moment you walk through the door.</p><h2>Schedule Your Cosmetic Vein Treatment</h2><p>Visible veins are one of those things people put up with for years before realizing how quick and straightforward the fix actually is. Sclerotherapy doesn't require surgery. It doesn't require weeks of recovery. It requires a short appointment, a skilled hand, and a plan built around your specific veins and your specific goals.</p><p>If you're ready to stop hiding your legs - or even if you're just curious about whether sclerotherapy is right for you - we'd love to see you for a consultation at REFRESH LKN in Cornelius. We'll evaluate your veins, talk through what to expect, and put together a treatment plan that feels right. You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. Your legs have been waiting long enough.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How much does sclerotherapy cost at REFRESH LKN?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the number of veins being treated and how many sessions your treatment plan requires. We'll discuss all costs upfront during your consultation so you know exactly what to expect - no surprises.</p><h3>How long does a sclerotherapy appointment take?</h3><p>Most treatment sessions run 15 to 30 minutes. Your initial consultation may take a bit longer since we'll evaluate your veins and walk through your personalized plan in detail.</p><h3>How far in advance should I book if I want clear legs by summer?</h3><p>Since results develop over several weeks and you may need more than one session, we recommend starting at least two to three months before any big event or the start of summer. The earlier you begin, the more time your body has to fully respond.</p><h3>Do I need to wear compression stockings, and for how long?</h3><p>Yes - compression stockings are an important part of your results. We typically recommend wearing them for one to two weeks after each session, though we'll give you specific guidance based on your treatment. They help the treated veins close properly and minimize bruising.</p><h3>Is there anything I absolutely should not do after treatment?</h3><p>Avoid hot baths, saunas, and direct sun exposure on the treated areas for at least two weeks. We also ask that you skip high-impact exercise for a few days, though normal walking is encouraged right away.</p><h3>Does REFRESH offer financing or payment plans?</h3><p>We're happy to discuss payment options during your consultation. Since cosmetic spider vein treatment is typically not covered by insurance, we want to make sure you have clear information about pricing and any available options before you commit to a plan.</p>
