<h1>Chrome Laser Treatments</h1><p>You look in the mirror and notice it's not just one thing. There's some sun damage here, a little redness there, texture that didn't used to bother you, and a dullness that no skincare product seems to fix. You start Googling and realize you might need three different treatments to address everything - separate appointments, separate recovery windows, separate costs. That's exhausting before you even start. Chrome Laser was designed for exactly this situation. It's a medical-grade laser platform that addresses multiple skin concerns in a single session, and it's one of the treatments we're most excited to offer here at REFRESH LKN. Whether you're coming to us from Cornelius, Davidson, Huntersville, or anywhere across the Lake Norman area, this is advanced laser skin care delivered by a board-certified nurse practitioner who personally oversees every treatment. No shortcuts, no guesswork - just real results backed by real expertise.</p><h2>What Is Chrome Laser Treatment?</h2><p>Chrome Laser is an advanced professional laser treatment platform that combines multiple wavelengths and modalities into one session. Think of it this way: most laser treatments are designed to do one thing well. One targets pigment. Another addresses redness. A third works on texture and fine lines. Chrome brings those capabilities together under one roof - your skin gets a full spectrum of rejuvenation without you having to book three separate appointments and manage three separate recovery periods.</p><p>What makes this different from a basic facial or a consumer-grade device you'd find at a retail store is the precision. We're working with medical-grade laser technology that can be adjusted and customized based on what your skin actually needs. Someone dealing primarily with sun spots and uneven tone will have a different treatment configuration than someone focused on fine lines and texture. That's the beauty of it - and it fits perfectly with how we approach care at REFRESH. We don't believe in one-size-fits-all anything. Your skin is yours, and your treatment plan should reflect that.</p><p>During your initial consultation, we assess your skin, talk about what's been bothering you, and build a plan around your specific goals. It's laser skin rejuvenation that's as individual as you are.</p><h2>Skin Concerns Chrome Laser Addresses</h2><p>Chrome Laser is remarkably versatile, which is why we recommend it so often. It's effective for sun damage and age spots - those stubborn patches of hyperpigmentation that seem to multiply every summer. It also targets redness, rosacea, and visible veins by addressing the vascular component beneath your skin's surface. If uneven skin tone and rough texture are what brought you here, Chrome works on that too, smoothing and refining in ways that creams and serums simply can't match.</p><p>Fine lines and early signs of aging respond well to the collagen stimulation that Chrome delivers, and if your complexion just looks tired and dull despite a solid skincare routine, this treatment can restore that brightness you've been missing. Whether you're dealing with one of these concerns or a combination - which is honestly the more common scenario - we can adjust the treatment to match. Skin tone and texture improvement happens gradually and naturally, which means the results look like you, just refreshed.</p><p>If you're ready to learn what Chrome Laser could do for your skin, give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> - we'd love to walk you through your options.</p><h2>How Fractional Laser Therapy Works</h2><h3>The Science Behind the Results</h3><p>Here's what's actually happening when laser energy meets your skin. Different structures in your skin - melanin (pigment), hemoglobin (the red in blood vessels), and water in your tissue - each absorb specific wavelengths of light. Chrome Laser uses this principle to selectively target the things you want to change without damaging everything around them. Pigmented spots absorb one wavelength. Redness and visible veins respond to another. It's precise in a way that makes non-invasive skin renewal therapy genuinely effective.</p><p>The “fractional” part is important too. Instead of treating every square millimeter of skin in the target area, fractional laser therapy treats a fraction of the surface at a time—creating tiny columns of treatment surrounded by untouched skin. That untouched skin helps speed healing dramatically, so you get powerful results with significantly less downtime than older, fully ablative laser methods. Meanwhile, beneath the surface, your body kicks into repair mode—building fresh collagen and remodeling the deeper layers of your skin over the weeks that follow.</p><p>This approach can also be customized based on how aggressive or gentle we want the treatment to be. With <strong>deep fractional (DF)</strong>, we focus energy deeper in the skin to target concerns like wrinkles, acne scarring, and more advanced texture changes—stimulating stronger collagen remodeling below the surface. With <strong>high coverage fractional (HC)</strong>, we treat a greater percentage of the skin’s surface more superficially, making it ideal for improving overall tone, sun damage, and fine texture with a bit less downtime.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, we choose the right approach—or a combination of both—based on your skin, your goals, and how much downtime you’re comfortable with, so your results feel aligned with your vision.</p><h3>What a Session Feels Like</h3><p>We start every Chrome Laser session with a conversation. Your skin gets assessed, we confirm your treatment plan, and we prep the area being treated. During the actual treatment, most clients describe the sensation as warm with occasional prickling - noticeable but very manageable. Sessions typically run between 30 and 60 minutes depending on the areas we're treating and the specific concerns we're addressing.</p><p>Right afterward, your skin may look a little pink and feel warm, similar to a mild sunburn. That's completely normal and fades quickly. Our team keeps you informed and comfortable throughout - we're not the kind of practice where you're left wondering what's happening next. You'll know exactly what to expect at every step.</p><h2>Results and Recovery Timeline</h2><p>One of the things clients love most about Chrome Laser is the minimal downtime. Most people return to their normal routine within a day or two. You might notice some mild redness or slight swelling initially, but it resolves quickly. Within the first few days, your skin starts to look brighter and smoother as the initial healing response kicks in.</p><p>The real magic, though, happens over weeks. As your body produces new collagen and the deeper remodeling process continues, your skin continues to improve - better texture, more even tone, a healthy glow that builds over time. Many clients see meaningful improvement after even a single session, but for optimal skin resurfacing results, we often recommend a series of treatments spaced several weeks apart. During your consultation, we'll map out a personalized plan that includes the recommended number of sessions and a maintenance schedule to keep your results going strong.</p><h2>Why Choose REFRESH for Laser Skin Rejuvenation</h2><h3>Expert-Led Care at Every Visit</h3><p>At REFRESH LKN, your treatment is overseen by a board-certified nurse practitioner - not delegated to someone with minimal training. That matters when we're talking about medical-grade laser skin treatment. The settings, the approach, the adjustments made in real time during your session - all of that requires clinical expertise and an experienced eye. We're Lake Norman's only medspa combining advanced lasers with hormone wellness, personalized weight loss, and injectables, which means we understand your skin in context. Your hormones, your nutrition, your overall health - it all connects, and we see the full picture.</p><h3>A Full Menu of Skin Health Options</h3><p>Chrome Laser is a powerful standalone treatment, but it's also one piece of a much larger toolkit. Depending on your goals, we might recommend pairing it with CoolPeel® CO2 laser for deeper resurfacing, Forever Young BBL™ for ongoing photorejuvenation, or even PRP skin treatments to accelerate healing and collagen production. Chemical peels, SkinPen® microneedling, BOTOX® - we have the range to build a plan that actually addresses everything you're working toward, not just one concern at a time.</p><p>That's the advantage of choosing a practice with this depth of options. Clients come to us from across the Charlotte area - Mooresville, Denver, Huntersville, Davidson - because they know they're getting a plan built around them, not a menu item pulled off a wall. Our Cornelius location on Catawba Avenue makes it easy to get to from anywhere around Lake Norman, and we think you'll feel the difference the moment you walk in.</p><h2>Schedule Your Chrome Laser Consultation</h2><p>If what you've been reading resonates - if you're tired of managing multiple skin concerns with products that only do so much - we'd love to sit down with you. A Chrome Laser consultation at REFRESH is a relaxed conversation where we look at your skin, listen to what you're noticing, and figure out whether this treatment is the right fit for your goals. No pressure, just honest guidance from someone who does this every day.</p><p>You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online anytime, or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031 - right in the heart of the Lake Norman community. Your skin goals deserve expert attention, and we're here for every step of it.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How many Chrome Laser sessions will I need for full results?</h3><p>Most clients see noticeable improvement after one session, but a series of three to five treatments spaced four to six weeks apart typically delivers the best long-term outcome. We'll give you a specific recommendation based on your skin during your consultation.</p><h3>Is Chrome Laser treatment safe for darker skin tones?</h3><p>Laser treatments require careful calibration for different skin tones, and certain settings work better for deeper complexions than others. During your consultation, we'll evaluate your skin type and let you know exactly what's safe and effective for you.</p><h3>Can I combine Chrome Laser with other treatments like BOTOX® or chemical peels?</h3><p>Absolutely - many of our clients pair Chrome Laser with other services for more complete results. Timing matters, though, so we'll help you sequence treatments in a way that's both safe and effective for your skin.</p><h3>How should I prepare my skin before a Chrome Laser appointment?</h3><p>We'll give you specific pre-treatment instructions during your consultation. Generally, you'll want to avoid excessive sun exposure, self-tanners, and certain active ingredients like retinoids for about a week beforehand.</p><h3>Are there activities or products I should avoid after treatment?</h3><p>For the first few days after your session, you'll want to skip heavy exercise, hot showers, direct sun exposure, and active skincare ingredients. We'll send you home with a clear aftercare guide so there's no guessing involved.</p><h3>How does Chrome Laser compare to CoolPeel® CO2 Laser?</h3><p>Chrome Laser works across multiple wavelengths to address a broad range of concerns like pigment, redness, and texture simultaneously. CoolPeel® is a CO2-specific treatment that focuses more on surface-level resurfacing with very minimal downtime. We often recommend one or both depending on your particular goals.</p><p>If you're ready to learn whether a Chrome treatment is the right choice for your skin, give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online.</p><h2></h2><h2>Deka CO2 Laser &amp; CoolPeel®</h2><p>When your skin needs more than surface-level treatments—when texture, deeper lines, sun damage, or laxity are starting to show—CO2 resurfacing is one of the most effective ways to truly reset it. At REFRESH LKN, we use the Deka CO2 laser to deliver customizable treatments ranging from deeper resurfacing to lighter, no-downtime options like CoolPeel®.</p><p>Both treatments use CO2 laser energy to create controlled micro-injuries in the skin, stimulating collagen production and resurfacing damaged layers. The difference is in how aggressively that energy is delivered—and how much downtime you want.</p><p>Deka CO2 is a fully customizable fractional resurfacing treatment. It can target deeper wrinkles, acne scarring, and more advanced sun damage by reaching further into the skin and creating more intensive collagen remodeling.</p><p>CoolPeel®, on the other hand, is a lighter, more superficial CO2 treatment designed to improve skin tone, texture, and fine lines with minimal downtime. It delivers the benefits of CO2 resurfacing—without the extended recovery traditionally associated with it.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, we tailor the depth and intensity based on your skin, your goals, and your lifestyle.</p><h2>Benefits</h2><ul><li><p>Improves fine lines and wrinkles</p></li><li><p>Smooths skin texture and reduces acne scarring</p></li><li><p>Brightens sun damage and discoloration</p></li><li><p>Tightens and firms skin through collagen stimulation</p></li><li><p>Customizable from light refresh to deeper resurfacing</p></li></ul><p>CoolPeel® is ideal if you want noticeable improvement with minimal interruption to your routine.<br />
Deka CO2 is best when you’re ready for more dramatic correction and longer-lasting structural change.</p><h2>Before Your Treatment</h2><p>We’ll start with a thorough consultation to determine the right level of treatment for your skin. In the weeks leading up, you’ll want to avoid sun exposure, tanning, and self-tanners. We may recommend pausing retinoids or active skincare ingredients several days prior.</p><p>If you have a history of cold sores or pigmentation concerns, we’ll guide you on pre-treatment medications or skincare to minimize risk and optimize your results.</p><h2>During Treatment</h2><p>Your experience will depend on the intensity of your treatment. For deeper Deka CO2 resurfacing, we apply a topical numbing cream—and in some cases additional comfort measures—to keep you comfortable throughout the procedure. For CoolPeel®, numbing is often not required or minimal.</p><p>During treatment, you’ll feel warmth and a mild prickling or snapping sensation as the laser moves across the skin. Treatments typically take 20–45 minutes depending on the area and depth.</p><h2>After Treatment</h2><p>With CoolPeel®, you can expect mild redness—similar to a sunburn—for 1–2 days, with a sandpaper-like texture as your skin renews. Most clients return to normal activities quickly.</p><p>With deeper Deka CO2, downtime is longer. You may experience redness, swelling, and peeling for several days to a week, depending on the depth of treatment. As your skin heals, you’ll notice a gradual improvement in tone, texture, and firmness.</p><p>In both cases, proper aftercare and strict sun protection are essential. Your skin will continue to improve over the following weeks as collagen production increases.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose REFRESH LKN for Laser Resurfacing</h2><p>There are a few things that set us apart, and they're the kind of things that matter when you're trusting someone with a laser on your face. First, our nurse practitioner doesn't just oversee treatments - she performs them. Every CoolPeel® session. Every time. That level of direct clinical involvement isn't standard at most clinics, and it should be.</p><p>Second, we use the <strong>DEKA SmartXide Tetra® CO₂</strong> platform to deliver customizable resurfacing. The technology matters because it gives your provider more precise control over energy delivery, which translates directly to better outcomes and safer treatments.</p><p>And then there's this: REFRESH LKN is the only wellness and aesthetic clinic in the Lake Norman area that brings together advanced cosmetic laser treatment with hormone wellness, medical weight loss, and injectables under one roof. So if your CoolPeel® /CO2 consultation reveals that your skin concerns are connected to something deeper - hormonal shifts, nutritional gaps, stress - we can address the whole picture, not just the surface. Clients come to us from Davidson, Mooresville, Huntersville, and throughout the greater Charlotte area because that kind of connected care is hard to find.</p><h2>Schedule Your CoolPeel® /CO2 Consultation</h2><p>Choosing any laser treatment is a real decision, and we respect that. We'd never push you toward something without first understanding your skin, your concerns, and what matters most to you. That's exactly what your consultation is for - a one-on-one conversation with our nurse practitioner where we look at your skin together, talk honestly about what CoolPeel® or Deka CO2 can and can't do, and figure out whether it's the right path forward. Sometimes we'll recommend combining it with other treatments. Sometimes we'll suggest starting somewhere else entirely. Either way, you'll leave with a clear plan.</p><p>We'd love to see you at REFRESH LKN, located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031. You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online anytime, or call us directly at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're here when you're ready.</p><h2>FAQs</h2><p>What’s the main difference between Deka CO2 and CoolPeel®?<br />
Depth and downtime. Deka CO2 can treat deeper concerns with more recovery time, while CoolPeel® offers lighter resurfacing with less downtime.</p><p>How many treatments will I need?<br />
CoolPeel® is often done in a series of treatments for best results. Deeper CO2 resurfacing may require fewer sessions, sometimes even one, depending on your goals.</p><p>Does it hurt?<br />
We prioritize comfort. Numbing is used for deeper treatments, and CoolPeel® is very tolerable for most clients.</p><p>When will I see results?<br />
You’ll notice early improvement as your skin heals within days to weeks, with continued collagen building over the next 2–3 months.</p><p>Is there downtime?<br />
CoolPeel® has minimal downtime (typically 1–2 days of redness). Deeper CO2 treatments require more recovery (several days to a week).</p><p>Who is a good candidate?<br />
Anyone looking to improve skin texture, tone, fine lines, or sun damage. The specific treatment is customized based on your skin type, concerns, and tolerance for downtime.</p><h3>Is CoolPeel® safe for darker skin tones?</h3><p>CO2 lasers do carry a higher risk of pigmentation changes in darker skin tones (typically Fitzpatrick types IV through VI), so candidacy depends on a careful in-person evaluation. During your consultation, our nurse practitioner assesses your specific skin type and history to determine whether CoolPeel® is appropriate or whether a different treatment would serve you better.</p><h3>How does CoolPeel® compare to chemical peels?</h3><p>Chemical peels use acids to exfoliate the skin's surface, while CoolPeel® uses fractional CO2 laser energy for more precise, controlled resurfacing. They actually complement each other well - many of our clients alternate between the two depending on the season and their skin's needs.</p><h3>Can I combine CoolPeel® or CO2 with BOTOX® or fillers?</h3><p>Absolutely. We typically recommend scheduling injectables about two weeks before or after your CoolPeel® session to let each treatment settle properly. During your consultation, we map out a treatment timeline that makes sense for everything you want to address.</p><h3>What time of year is best for CoolPeel®?</h3><p>Fall and winter are popular because sun exposure is naturally lower, but CoolPeel® can be performed year-round as long as you commit to diligent sunscreen use afterward. We'll give you specific aftercare guidance based on the time of year you're treated.</p><h3>How much does CoolPeel® cost at REFRESH?</h3><p>Pricing varies depending on the treatment area and whether we're combining CoolPeel® with other services. The best way to get an accurate quote is during your consultation, where we can discuss your goals and recommend the right plan. We're always happy to walk you through pricing before you commit to anything.</p>
