<h1>Laser Hair Removal</h1><p>You've spent years - maybe decades - dealing with razors, waxing strips, ingrown hairs, and that stubble that shows up roughly twelve hours after you just shaved. It's exhausting, it's never-ending, and honestly? You deserve better. Laser hair removal is the most effective path to permanent hair reduction in Cornelius, NC, and it's one of the most popular services we offer at REFRESH LKN for good reason. Long-lasting hair-free results without the constant upkeep. We're a true medical spa, which means your treatments are overseen by a board-certified nurse practitioner using medical-grade laser technology - not a watered-down version you'd find at a chain salon. Every treatment plan we create is built around you: your skin, your hair, your goals. If you're anywhere in the Lake Norman area and you're ready to stop fighting unwanted hair, this is where we begin.</p><h2>How Laser Hair Removal Works</h2><p>Here's the short version: laser energy targets the melanin (pigment) inside your hair follicle. When that energy is absorbed, it converts to heat, which damages the follicle enough to disrupt its ability to produce new hair. Over time and with repeated sessions, those follicles become less and less active - some stop producing hair entirely. That's hair follicle destruction in action, and it's the reason lasers are so much more effective than anything you can do at home.</p><p>You'll hear us say "permanent hair reduction" rather than "permanent hair removal." That's not us being cautious - it's the FDA's terminology, and it's accurate. Most clients see a dramatic decrease in hair growth, often 80–90% reduction in treated areas. Some fine or stubborn hairs may return over time, but they're typically lighter and thinner than what you started with. The key thing to understand is that lasers can only affect hair follicles that are actively growing. Your hair grows in cycles, and at any given time only a portion of follicles are in the active growth phase (called anagen). That's why you'll need multiple treatment sessions spaced out over time - but more on that shortly.</p><h3>IPL vs Laser Hair Removal</h3><p>If you've been researching, you've probably come across IPL devices - including those at-home gadgets that promise salon results from your bathroom. IPL stands for Intense Pulsed Light, and while it can reduce hair growth to some degree, it works differently than a true laser. IPL uses a broad spectrum of light wavelengths, which scatters energy across the skin. A medical-grade laser delivers a single, concentrated wavelength that penetrates more precisely to the follicle. The difference matters, especially for certain skin and hair combinations where precision is everything. At REFRESH LKN, we use professional laser technology because the results are more predictable, the treatments are safer across a wider range of skin tones, and we can dial in settings specific to your needs. IPL has its place, but when it comes to effective, lasting hair reduction, true laser wins.</p><h2>Treatment Areas for Unwanted Hair</h2><p>One of the best things about laser hair removal is how versatile it is. We treat clients from Cornelius, Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, and throughout the greater Charlotte area, and the most common request we hear is: "Can you do everything?" The answer is usually yes. But most people start with the areas that bother them most.</p><h3>Bikini &amp; Brazilian Laser Hair Removal</h3><p>Bikini line laser treatment and full Brazilian laser hair removal are easily among our most requested services - especially as Lake Norman pool season rolls around. If you've been enduring regular waxing appointments (and the dread that comes with them), switching to laser is a relief in every sense. Our clinical environment is private, professional, and comfortable. We do this all day, and we make it easy. A few sessions in, you'll wonder why you didn't do this years ago.</p><h3>Underarms, Legs &amp; Other Areas</h3><p>Underarm hair removal laser sessions are quick - sometimes under fifteen minutes - and the convenience of never reaching for a razor again is hard to beat. Full legs, arms, back, chest, upper lip, chin - we treat all of these regularly. You can target a single area or combine multiple zones into one visit. We build your treatment plan around whatever matters most to you, and we adjust as your goals evolve.</p><p>If you're ready to talk specifics about which areas you'd like to treat, give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online. We'll walk you through everything during your consultation.</p><h2>Skin &amp; Hair Types That Respond Best</h2><p>Let's talk candidacy, because this is one of the most common questions we get. Laser treatment for dark hair on lighter skin tones has traditionally produced the strongest results. High contrast between hair pigment and skin tone gives the laser a clear target. That said, technology has come a long way. Modern laser systems have expanded options significantly, and we're able to safely and effectively treat a much wider range of skin tones than older equipment allowed.</p><p>Not every person or every area responds the same way, and we think honesty about that is more valuable than promises we can't keep. Very light blonde, red, or gray hair has less melanin for the laser to target, which can limit results. That's exactly why we do a personalized consultation before any treatment - so we can assess your unique skin and hair combination, set realistic expectations, and recommend the best approach. If laser isn't the right fit for a particular area, we'll tell you that directly. Transparency builds trust, and trust is everything in this work.</p><h2>What to Expect During Treatment</h2><p>If you've been putting this off because you're worried about pain, let's put that to rest. Pain-free hair removal sessions might be a stretch - everyone's sensitivity is different - but modern cooling technology built into today's lasers makes the experience far more comfortable than you'd expect. Most clients describe the sensation as a warm snap against the skin, similar to a rubber band flick. Compared to waxing? It's considerably more tolerable, and it gets easier with each session as hair becomes finer.</p><p>Here's how a typical visit goes. You'll arrive at our Cornelius location having shaved the treatment area a day or so before - this is important because the laser needs to target the follicle below the surface, not the hair above it. Avoid sun exposure leading up to your appointment, and skip waxing, plucking, or threading for at least four weeks prior (those methods remove the follicle the laser needs to find). Your session could be as quick as ten minutes for a small area like the upper lip or underarms, or up to an hour for larger zones like full legs. Afterward, you might notice some mild redness - that's normal and fades quickly. We'll send you home with simple aftercare instructions: stay out of direct sun, use SPF, skip hot baths for a day or two. Easy.</p><h2>Multiple Sessions &amp; Lasting Results</h2><p>Because hair grows in cycles and the laser only works on follicles in their active growth phase, one session won't get you there. Most treatment plans involve six to eight sessions spaced four to eight weeks apart, depending on the body area being treated. Faster-growing areas like the bikini line may need sessions closer together, while legs or arms can be spaced a bit further apart.</p><p>The results are progressive, and that's actually one of the satisfying parts. After two or three sessions, you'll notice real reduction - thinner regrowth, patchier coverage, longer stretches between any visible hair. By the time you finish your full series, the difference is dramatic. Most clients find that an occasional maintenance session once or twice a year keeps everything smooth long-term. When you add up what you'd spend on razors, shaving cream, waxing appointments, and ingrown-hair treatments over five, ten, twenty years - the math starts to look pretty compelling.</p><h2>Cornelius Medical Spa Hair Treatments</h2><p>There are plenty of places offering laser hair removal in the Charlotte area. So why choose REFRESH LKN? Because we're not a chain clinic running you through on a conveyor belt, and we're not a salon that added a laser to the back room. We're a medical spa led by a board-certified nurse practitioner who personally oversees clinical treatments and builds individualized plans for every client who walks through our door on W. Catawba Avenue.</p><p>That matters more than you might think. Hormonal factors - something we understand deeply through our wellness services including bioidentical hormone replacement - can directly affect hair growth patterns. If you're dealing with unwanted hair that seems to keep coming back despite treatment elsewhere, there may be an underlying reason. At REFRESH, we look at the full picture, not just the surface. Clients throughout Lake Norman, from Denver to Huntersville and everywhere in between, trust us because we combine real medical knowledge with genuine care for how you feel when you leave our space. Confident. Comfortable. Like yourself.</p><h2>Your Next Step Toward Smooth Skin</h2><p>You've done the research. You know what you want. The next step is simple: come see us. A consultation at REFRESH LKN gives you a chance to ask every question on your mind, see our space, meet our team, and walk out with a clear treatment plan designed just for you. No pressure, no commitment until you're ready.</p><p><a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're here in Cornelius and we'd love to help you finally say goodbye to the razor for good.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How long do laser hair removal results last?</h3><p>Most clients experience significant, lasting reduction that holds for years. Some hair may slowly return over time - usually finer and lighter - which is why we recommend one or two maintenance sessions per year. Individual results vary based on hormones, genetics, and the area treated.</p><h3>Is laser hair removal safe during pregnancy?</h3><p>We recommend waiting until after pregnancy and nursing to begin or continue laser hair removal treatments. While there's no evidence of harm, the treatment hasn't been studied enough in pregnant women to confirm safety, and hormonal changes during pregnancy can affect hair growth patterns and skin sensitivity.</p><h3>Can I shave between sessions?</h3><p>Yes - shaving is perfectly fine and actually encouraged before each appointment. What you should avoid is waxing, plucking, or threading between sessions, because those methods remove the hair follicle that the laser needs to target.</p><h3>What if I miss a session or fall off schedule?</h3><p>Life happens, and missing a session won't ruin your progress. You may just need an extra session to get back on track. Consistency gives you the best results because it aligns treatments with your hair's natural growth cycles, but we can always adjust your plan.</p><h3>Are there medications that affect treatment?</h3><p>Certain medications can make your skin more sensitive to light, including some antibiotics, retinoids, and photosensitizing drugs. During your consultation, we'll review any medications or supplements you're taking so we can plan your treatments safely.</p><h3>Do you offer package pricing?</h3><p>We do offer packages for multiple treatment sessions, and pricing varies based on the area or combination of areas you'd like treated. The best way to get current pricing details is to call us at 980-216-8484 or book a consultation - we'll put together a plan and pricing that makes sense for your goals.</p>
<hr>
<h1>Forever Young BBL™</h1><p>You've been consistent with your skincare. You wear sunscreen, you moisturize, you stay on top of things. And yet, every time you catch your reflection in a certain light, there they are - brown spots that weren't there a few years ago, a redness across your cheeks that never quite fades, a dullness that no serum seems to fix. Living near the lake means more time outside, and that sun exposure adds up faster than most people realize.</p><p>Forever Young BBL™ is a light-based anti-aging treatment that works differently than anything you've probably tried before. Instead of treating only the surface, BroadBand Light therapy targets skin at the cellular level - actually changing the way your skin ages over time. At REFRESH LKN, we offer this Sciton-powered photorejuvenation treatment as part of our advanced laser menu, and every session is personally performed by our board-certified nurse practitioner. No handoffs. No guesswork. Here's everything you need to know about how it works, what it treats, and what your experience will look like.</p><h2>What Is BroadBand Light Therapy?</h2><p>BBL stands for BroadBand Light, and it's made by Sciton - one of the most respected names in medical laser technology. If you've heard of IPL skin rejuvenation, think of BBL as its more advanced, more precise successor. Older IPL devices delivered broad pulses of light with limited control. BBL uses customizable wavelength filters, advanced cooling, and precise energy delivery so we can target exactly what your skin needs without affecting the tissue around it.</p><p>Forever Young BBL™ is a specific treatment approach within the BBL platform, designed for anti-aging and long-term skin health. What makes it remarkable? A landmark study out of Stanford University showed that regular BBL treatments actually changed gene expression in treated skin - making it behave more like younger skin at a molecular level. That's not marketing language. That's published research. And it's why this treatment has become one of the most trusted non-invasive skin renewal options available today. No surgery, no needles, minimal downtime.</p><h2>Skin Concerns Forever Young BBL™ Treats</h2><h3>Sun Damage and Age Spots</h3><p>If you spend time on Lake Norman - boating, paddleboarding, sitting on a dock with a good book - your skin has been absorbing UV rays for years, even on cloudy days. That cumulative exposure shows up as brown spots, age spots, sun spots, and scattered freckling. Forever Young BBL™ is one of the most effective options for sun damage correction, breaking down excess pigment so your skin can clear it naturally.</p><h3>Uneven Skin Tone and Texture</h3><p>Redness, rosacea, broken capillaries, blotchy patches - these can make your complexion look tired even when you feel great. BBL addresses skin tone and texture improvement across the face, neck, chest, and hands. The light energy targets both vascular redness and pigment irregularities, giving you a more even, calm, healthy-looking appearance.</p><h3>Early Signs of Aging</h3><p>Fine lines, crepe-like texture, loss of that natural glow you used to take for granted - BBL treats these too. The light energy triggers your skin's own collagen stimulation response, encouraging it to repair and rebuild from within. This makes Forever Young BBL™ both preventive and corrective. Whether you're in your mid-30s noticing the first subtle shifts or in your 60s wanting brighter, smoother skin, this treatment meets you where you are.</p><h2>How the Treatment Works</h2><h3>Before Your Session</h3><p>Everything starts with a consultation at REFRESH. We'll look at your skin closely, talk about what's bothering you, review your history, and determine whether BBL is the right fit. We'll also go over pre-treatment guidelines - mainly avoiding direct sun exposure and tanning in the weeks leading up to your appointment. What matters most here is the customization. Our nurse practitioner selects specific wavelengths and filter settings based on your skin type, your concerns, and your goals. No two sessions are identical because no two clients are.</p><h3>During the Treatment</h3><p>The device glides across your skin, delivering pulses of light energy. Most people describe the sensation as warm with a light snapping feeling - like a tiny rubber band. It's very tolerable. The BBL handpiece has built-in cooling that keeps the surface of your skin comfortable throughout. We can treat the full face, neck, décolleté, and hands depending on where your concerns are. Sessions typically take about 20 to 30 minutes, making it easy to fit into a lunch break or a busy afternoon.</p><h3>After Your Session</h3><p>You might notice some mild warmth or pinkness right after - similar to a light sunburn. This fades quickly for most people. Here's the part that surprises some clients: brown spots and freckles may actually darken temporarily before they flake away over the next week or so. That's completely normal and expected. It means the treatment is working exactly as it should. Most clients head right back to their regular activities the same day.</p><p>If you're ready to see what Forever Young BBL™ can do for your skin, we'd love to talk. Call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online.</p><h2>Results and Collagen Benefits</h2><p>Many clients notice a visible difference after their very first session - clearer, brighter skin with less pigmentation and redness. But the real results come with consistency. Forever Young BBL™ is designed as a collagen stimulation treatment that builds on itself over time. Each session triggers new collagen production beneath the surface, which means firmer, smoother, more youthful glowing skin that continues to improve in the weeks following treatment.</p><p>A typical plan starts with two to four initial sessions spaced a few weeks apart, followed by one to two maintenance sessions per year. There's a reason this treatment approach is called "Forever Young" - it's a long-term strategy for aging well, not a one-and-done quick fix. The results compound over time, especially when you pair treatments with solid daily skincare and consistent sun protection. Clients who stick with their annual sessions often tell us their skin looks better at 50 than it did at 40. That's not an exaggeration.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose REFRESH LKN</h2><p>Not every clinic in the Charlotte metro area invests in Sciton technology. It's a premium platform, and it requires experienced hands to get the best results. At REFRESH Medical Spa &amp; Wellness, our board-certified nurse practitioner personally performs every BBL treatment. She's not supervising from another room - she's the one holding the handpiece, reading your skin in real time, and adjusting settings as needed. That matters.</p><p>We're a boutique wellness and aesthetic clinic in Cornelius, not a high-volume assembly line. Clients from Huntersville, Davidson, Mooresville, and across the Lake Norman area come to us because they want someone who sees the whole picture - not just one brown spot or one concern, but their overall skin health. Forever Young BBL™ also pairs beautifully with other treatments we offer, including CoolPeel® CO2 laser sessions, chemical peels, and RF microneedling for skin resurfacing in Cornelius, NC that addresses texture, tone, and firmness together. We'll help you build a plan that makes sense for your skin and your life.</p><h2>Schedule Your Consultation</h2><p>If you've been noticing changes in your skin that creams and serums can't seem to touch, a Forever Young BBL™ consultation is a great next step. We'll sit down together, look at your skin, talk through your goals, and figure out whether BBL - on its own or as part of a larger plan - is right for you. No pressure. Just honest, expert guidance from someone who does this every single day.</p><p>You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC - right in the heart of the Lake Norman community. We look forward to meeting you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How many Forever Young BBL™ sessions will I need?</h3><p>That depends on your skin's condition and what you're hoping to achieve. Most clients start with a series of two to four treatments, then transition to one or two maintenance sessions annually. We'll map out a recommendation during your consultation based on what we see.</p><h3>Is Forever Young BBL™ safe for all skin types?</h3><p>BBL works best on lighter to medium skin tones. Darker skin types carry a higher risk of pigment changes with light-based treatments, so candidacy is something we assess carefully during your consultation. We'll always be straightforward about whether this is the right option for you.</p><h3>Can I combine BBL with other treatments at REFRESH?</h3><p>Absolutely, and many of our clients do. Forever Young BBL™ pairs well with CoolPeel® for deeper resurfacing, chemical peels for exfoliation, or SkinPen® microneedling for texture refinement. We'll space treatments appropriately so your skin has time to respond and heal between sessions.</p><h3>How much does Forever Young BBL™ cost?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the treatment area and whether you're booking a single session or a package series. We're happy to go over all pricing details during your consultation so there are no surprises. We also offer package options that make maintenance sessions more affordable.</p><h3>How far in advance should I schedule my appointment?</h3><p>We recommend booking at least one to two weeks ahead, especially during spring and summer when demand picks up. If you're planning BBL before a special event, give yourself about three to four weeks so your skin has time to fully clear and settle.</p><h3>When should I avoid scheduling a Forever Young BBL™ treatment?</h3><p>You'll want to avoid BBL if you have a recent tan, active sunburn, or have been using self-tanner within the past two weeks. Certain medications like antibiotics or retinoids may also require a pause. Pregnancy is another time we'd hold off. We'll review all of this before your first session.</p><p><strong>IPL (Intense Pulsed Light)</strong></p><p><strong>What is IPL?</strong></p><p>If your skin is starting to show the effects of sun exposure—brown spots, redness, uneven tone, or that overall “dull” look—IPL is one of the most effective ways to reset it. Especially after years of Lake Norman summers, it’s common for pigment and vascular changes to surface in ways that skincare alone just can’t correct.</p><p>IPL uses targeted pulses of light to break up unwanted pigment and reduce redness beneath the skin’s surface. Over time, this helps clear sun damage, even out skin tone, and restore a brighter, more uniform complexion. It’s not about peeling or resurfacing—it’s about correcting what’s underneath so your skin looks clearer and healthier on top.</p><p>This treatment is ideal for sun spots, age spots, redness, broken capillaries, and overall discoloration on the face, chest, and neck. The result is skin that looks more even, more radiant, and more like itself again.</p><p><strong>Before Your IPL Treatment</strong></p><p>Before treatment, we’ll evaluate your skin to ensure IPL is the right fit for your concerns and skin type. It’s important to avoid sun exposure, tanning beds, and self-tanners for at least 1–2 weeks prior, as IPL targets pigment and works best when your natural skin tone is not recently tanned.</p><p>You’ll also want to avoid active skincare ingredients like retinoids or exfoliating acids for several days beforehand. Come to your appointment with clean, makeup-free skin. If you have a history of melasma or are prone to pigmentation, we’ll guide you on how to prep your skin appropriately for the best outcome.</p><p><strong>During &amp; After Treatment</strong></p><p>IPL treatments are performed in-office and typically take about 20–30 minutes, depending on the area. We apply a cooling gel to the skin, and while no numbing is usually required, the treatment is very tolerable—most clients describe it as a quick snapping sensation, like a rubber band against the skin.</p><p>After treatment, you may notice mild redness or warmth, similar to a light sunburn, which usually resolves within a few hours. Pigmented spots will temporarily darken over the next few days before gradually flaking off or fading. This is a normal and expected part of the process.</p><p>There’s little to no downtime, but sun protection is essential. You’ll want to wear SPF daily and avoid direct sun exposure as your skin heals. Over the next 1–2 weeks, your skin will appear clearer, brighter, and more even in tone. A series of treatments is typically recommended for optimal results.</p><p><strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong></p><p><strong>How is IPL different from a laser?<br />
</strong> IPL uses broad-spectrum light to target multiple concerns like pigment and redness at once, while lasers are typically more targeted to a specific issue. IPL is great for overall skin tone correction.</p><p><strong>Does it hurt?<br />
</strong> Most clients tolerate IPL very well. It feels like a quick snap of heat against the skin, but it’s fast and manageable without numbing.</p><p><strong>How many treatments will I need?<br />
</strong> Most clients benefit from a series of 3–4 treatments spaced a few weeks apart, followed by maintenance sessions as needed.</p><p><strong>When will I see results?<br />
</strong> You’ll start to notice improvement within a week, with continued clearing and brightening over the next couple of weeks.</p><p><strong>Is there downtime?<br />
</strong> Minimal. You may have some redness and temporary darkening of pigment, but most people return to normal activities the same day.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, IPL is often a cornerstone treatment for restoring clarity and brightness to the skin—especially when sun damage and uneven tone are standing between you and that refreshed, healthy glow.</p>
<hr>
<h1>Rejuvenation &amp; Repair Therapies</h1><p>You take care of your skin. You've tried the serums, the masks, the fancy moisturizers - and sure, they help a little. But when you look in the mirror, something still feels off. Maybe it's the fine lines that seem deeper than they were a year ago. Maybe it's the sun damage that's settled into your cheeks and chest after years of Lake Norman summers. Or maybe your skin just looks tired, no matter how much sleep you get. That disconnect between how you feel and what you see? It's real, and you're not imagining it.</p><p>Here's the truth: there's a ceiling to what over-the-counter products and basic facials can do. When you're ready to move past that ceiling, clinical skin rejuvenation treatments are the answer. At REFRESH LKN, we offer advanced aesthetic treatments designed to restore your skin from the inside out - not with a one-size-fits-all approach, but with a plan built around you. Our board-certified nurse practitioner personally evaluates every client and selects the right combination of therapies based on your unique skin, your concerns, and your goals. This page walks you through exactly what we offer, how each treatment works, and what kind of results you can expect.</p><h2>Why These Treatments Deliver Lasting Results</h2><p>Most skincare products work on the surface. They hydrate, they exfoliate, they protect - all good things. But they can't reach the deeper layers of skin where collagen is produced and structural changes actually happen. That's where medical-grade skin rejuvenation treatments come in.</p><p>Clinical therapies like laser skin resurfacing, radiofrequency microneedling, and platelet-rich plasma skin therapy work by triggering your body's own repair mechanisms. When we create controlled micro-injuries or deliver targeted energy into the skin, your body responds with a flood of new collagen, accelerated cellular turnover, and tissue remodeling that continues for weeks and months after treatment. The results aren't just cosmetic - they're biological.</p><p>We carry multiple treatment platforms at REFRESH because no single technology addresses every concern. Sun damage responds differently than acne scarring. Fine lines need a different approach than skin laxity. During your consultation, we determine which modality - or combination - gives you the best possible outcome.</p><h2>Advanced Aesthetic Treatments at REFRESH</h2><p>One of the things that sets REFRESH LKN apart from other providers in the Charlotte area is the range of technology we have in-house. Laser energy, radiofrequency, broadband light, and biologic therapies - all under one roof in Cornelius, NC. That means our nurse practitioner can mix, match, and layer treatments based on what your skin actually needs, rather than being limited to whatever single device happens to be available. Here's a closer look at each modality.</p><h3>CoolPeel® CO2 Laser Skin Renewal</h3><p>If you've heard of CO2 laser skin resurfacing but were put off by stories of week-long recoveries and raw, peeling skin - CoolPeel® changes that conversation entirely. This fractional CO2 laser delivers the collagen-stimulating benefits of traditional resurfacing with a fraction of the downtime.</p><p>Here's how it works: the CoolPeel® system delivers controlled micro-columns of laser energy that remove damaged surface skin while stimulating deep collagen remodeling underneath. The precision of this technology means minimal heat spread to surrounding tissue, which is exactly why healing is faster and more comfortable than older-generation CO2 lasers.</p><p>CoolPeel® is one of our most requested treatments, and for good reason. It's excellent for fine lines and wrinkles, sun damage, enlarged pores, uneven skin tone, and that overall dullness that creeps in over time. Most clients describe noticeable improvements after just one session, with results that continue building for months as new collagen matures.</p><p><strong>SkinPen® Microneedling</strong></p><p>If your skin feels like it’s lost its smoothness, its glow, or that “tight” look it used to have, SkinPen® is often where we start. This is a medical-grade microneedling treatment that creates controlled micro-injuries in the skin, triggering your body’s natural healing response. In other words, it encourages your skin to do what it used to do on its own—produce more collagen and elastin.</p><p>Over time, that process helps soften fine lines, improve skin texture, minimize acne scarring, and restore overall radiance. It’s not about changing your face—it’s about helping your skin function better so it looks healthier, firmer, and more even. Many clients also notice improvement in pore size and that “crepey” look that can show up with sun damage or aging.</p><p>SkinPen® is especially popular because it’s safe for all skin types and requires minimal downtime. You can expect some redness for a day or two—similar to a mild sunburn—but underneath the surface, your skin is actively repairing and rebuilding. Results develop gradually, which is exactly what you want when you’re aiming for natural, refreshed-looking skin.</p><p>For many of our clients at REFRESH LKN, microneedling becomes a foundational treatment—something they return to consistently to maintain skin quality over time. And when paired with other therapies like PRP or targeted skincare, the results only get better.</p><h3>RF Microneedling for Skin Texture and Collagen Stimulation</h3><p>RF microneedling takes the already-proven science of microneedling and amplifies it with radiofrequency energy. Using the VirtueRF® platform, we create tiny controlled micro-injuries with fine needles while simultaneously delivering RF energy into the deeper tissue layers. That dual mechanism - surface-level micro-channels plus deep thermal stimulation - triggers a powerful collagen and elastin response that reshapes skin texture from the inside out.</p><p>This treatment is a standout option for texture irregularities, acne scarring, mild skin laxity, fine lines, and enlarged pores. One major advantage? RF microneedling for skin texture is safe for all skin tones, which makes it an excellent choice for clients who may not be ideal candidates for certain laser treatments.</p><p>Most people describe the sensation as a warm prickling - very manageable with the topical numbing we apply beforehand. We typically recommend a series of three to four sessions spaced about four to six weeks apart for the best results.</p><p>If what you're reading resonates and you're ready to talk about your skin, give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online. We'll figure out the right starting point together.</p><h3>Forever Young BBL™ Photorejuvenation</h3><p>Forever Young BBL™ uses BroadBand Light technology to target pigmentation, redness, vascular concerns, and overall skin quality at multiple wavelengths. It's both corrective and preventive - clearing existing sun damage and age spots while actually changing how your skin ages at a molecular level. A well-known Stanford University study showed that BBL™ treatments can alter gene expression associated with aging, essentially encouraging skin cells to behave more like younger cells. That's not marketing language. That's published research.</p><p>This treatment is ideal for sun damage, age spots, rosacea, and general skin quality improvement. Many of our clients across Lake Norman, Davidson, and Huntersville use Forever Young BBL™ as part of an ongoing maintenance program - a few sessions a year to keep their skin looking fresh and even-toned without any significant downtime.</p><h3>PRP &amp; PRF Skin Restoration</h3><p>PRP and PRF treatments are about as natural as skin restoration gets. We draw a small amount of your blood, process it to concentrate the growth factors and platelets, and then apply those concentrated biologics back to your skin - either topically after microneedling or injected directly into targeted areas.</p><p>Platelet-rich plasma (PRP) delivers a rapid burst of growth factors that accelerate healing and stimulate collagen production. PRF - platelet-rich fibrin - is a newer evolution that uses a fibrin matrix to release growth factors more slowly over time, creating prolonged stimulation and enhanced tissue regeneration. PRF gel and PDGF therapies take this even further.</p><p>What makes PRP and PRF skin restoration so appealing is that there's nothing synthetic involved. It's your own biology, concentrated and redirected to where your skin needs it most. We often combine these biologic therapies with microneedling or laser treatments to compound results - the growth factors enhance healing and amplify collagen stimulation treatments in ways that standalone procedures can't match on their own.</p><h2>Combining Therapies for Better Results</h2><p>At REFRESH, we rarely take a single-treatment approach to skin rejuvenation. Real results usually come from layering or sequencing therapies that work on different levels of the skin. For example, pairing CoolPeel® with PRP creates a powerful combination - the laser resurfaces and stimulates while the platelet-rich plasma floods the area with growth factors that accelerate healing and deepen rejuvenation. Or we might combine Forever Young BBL™ with RF microneedling to address tone and texture simultaneously.</p><p>Your treatment roadmap gets built during your consultation. Our nurse practitioner looks at your skin, listens to what's bothering you, and maps out a plan that makes sense - not just for today, but for where you want your skin to be six months or a year from now. No cookie-cutter approaches. Just smart, personalized care from someone who does this every single day.</p><h2>What to Expect During Your Visit</h2><p>If you've never had a clinical skin treatment before, here's the general flow. Your first visit starts with a thorough skin assessment and conversation about your goals. From there, we discuss which therapies make the most sense and build out your plan. On treatment day, we prep your skin with cleansing and topical numbing as needed, then move through the procedure itself - most treatments take between thirty and sixty minutes.</p><p>Afterward, you'll receive clear post-care instructions specific to your treatment. Downtime varies: some therapies let you return to your normal routine the same day, while others involve a few days of redness or mild peeling. Most rejuvenation therapies require a series of sessions for optimal results, and improvements continue building for weeks and even months as your body produces new collagen. That gradual progression is one of the best parts - your skin just keeps getting better.</p><h2>Start Your Skin Renewal in Cornelius</h2><p>Whether you're dealing with years of accumulated sun damage, early signs of aging, texture concerns, or skin that's just lost its glow - we have the clinical tools and expertise to help you get it back. REFRESH Medical Spa &amp; Wellness serves clients throughout Cornelius, Mooresville, Huntersville, Davidson, and the greater Charlotte area, and we'd love to see you at our office.</p><p>Ready to find out which rejuvenation therapy is right for you? <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031 - right in the heart of Lake Norman. Your skin already knows how to repair itself. We just give it the right reason to start.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How much do rejuvenation treatments cost?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the specific treatment, the area being treated, and whether we're recommending a single session or a series. We provide transparent pricing during your consultation so you know exactly what to expect before committing to anything.</p><h3>How long does a typical treatment appointment take?</h3><p>Most rejuvenation treatments take between thirty and sixty minutes, depending on the modality and treatment area. Your first visit will run a bit longer since it includes the consultation and skin assessment portion.</p><h3>Do you offer financing or payment plans?</h3><p>Yes, we understand that investing in your skin is a real commitment. We can walk you through available financing options during your visit so you can choose what works best for your budget.</p><h3>How should I prepare for my treatment?</h3><p>Preparation varies by treatment type, but in general we recommend avoiding sun exposure, retinoids, and certain active ingredients for a few days beforehand. We'll send you specific pre-care instructions once your appointment is scheduled.</p><h3>Can I combine a rejuvenation treatment with BOTOX® or filler on the same visit?</h3><p>In some cases, yes - certain combinations work well on the same day, while others are better staged a week or two apart. Our nurse practitioner will recommend the safest and most effective sequencing based on your specific plan.</p><h3>Is there an ideal age to start rejuvenation treatments?</h3><p>There's no strict age requirement. Clients in their late twenties and thirties often start for prevention, while those in their forties, fifties, and beyond seek correction for existing concerns. A consultation is the best way to figure out what makes sense for you right now.</p>
