<h1>Facials</h1><p>You've got a solid routine at home. The cleanser, the serums, the SPF - you're doing the work. But something still feels off. Maybe it's a stubborn dullness that won't lift, or texture you can feel under your fingertips, or pores that seem to have a mind of their own. Here's the thing: even the best over-the-counter products can only do so much. They're designed to work on the surface, and your skin's needs often run deeper than that. That's exactly where we come in. At REFRESH LKN, our facials aren't pulled from a preset menu. They're clinical-level skin care treatments built around what your skin actually needs today - not what worked for someone else last week. We're a clinical wellness clinic in Cornelius, not a day spa, and that distinction matters more than you might think. Every facial starts with your skin's story, and we listen before we ever touch your face.</p><h2>Why Professional Treatments Matter</h2><p>Your skin has a protective barrier, and it's doing exactly what it's supposed to do - keeping things out. That includes a lot of the active ingredients in the products you buy at the store. Retail formulations are made for general use, which means lower concentrations and gentler delivery systems. They maintain. They don't change much.</p><p>A professional facial works differently. We use medical-grade products with higher percentages of active ingredients that can actually reach the deeper layers of your skin where real change happens. Our extraction techniques are precise and clinical - not the kind of thing you want to attempt with a magnifying mirror at home. And before we do anything, we assess. Dehydration looks different from dryness. Congestion patterns tell us something specific. Sensitivity has triggers, and we want to identify them, not just work around them. Our board-certified nurse practitioner oversees everything we do at REFRESH, which means your facial isn't just relaxing - it's informed by real medical knowledge. That's a different standard of care, and your skin can tell the difference.</p><h2>Customized Facials for Every Skin Concern</h2><p>No two faces walk through our door with the same needs. That's why we never deliver the same facial twice. Here's a closer look at how we approach the most common concerns we see from clients across the Lake Norman area.</p><h3>Deep Cleansing and Pore Refining</h3><p>If you're dealing with blackheads, enlarged pores, or that heavy, congested feeling - especially during the humid months here in the Charlotte area - a deep cleansing facial is where we start. We work through thorough extractions, apply purifying masks that draw out impurities, and finish with pore-minimizing steps that leave your skin feeling lighter and cleaner than your daily wash ever could. This is one of our most-requested treatments for clients with oily or combination skin who feel like they can never quite get ahead of the buildup.</p><h3>Hydrating and Glow Facials</h3><p>Dull, tired, thirsty skin doesn't need more exfoliation - it needs replenishment. Our hydrating facials focus on deep moisture infusion and barrier repair, bringing back that lit-from-within look that stress, travel, and seasonal changes can steal. This is a favorite before weddings, vacations, or any time you want your skin to look its absolute best. Clients looking for a glow facial near Lake Norman find exactly what they need here - radiance that lasts well beyond your appointment.</p><h3>Anti-Aging and Rejuvenating Treatments</h3><p>Fine lines creeping in. A little loss of firmness. Uneven tone from years of sun exposure. Our rejuvenating skin treatments use professional-strength peptides, retinoids, and antioxidants at concentrations you simply can't get over the counter. These facials are designed to stimulate cell turnover, boost collagen activity, and restore clarity. And because REFRESH is a full aesthetic clinic, we can pair your anti-aging facial with complementary treatments like chemical peels, CoolPeel® laser sessions, or injectables when a bigger-picture plan makes sense.</p><p>If you're ready to see what a real professional facial can do for your skin, give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or go ahead and <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online.</p><h2>What to Expect During Your Facial</h2><p>If this is your first time getting a licensed aesthetician facial - or your first time at REFRESH - here's how it goes. We start with a conversation. Not a clipboard. A real conversation about your skin, your goals, what's been bothering you, what products you're currently using, and whether you have any sensitivities or conditions we should know about. This is how we figure out exactly what your skin needs today.</p><p>From there, your treatment follows a clinical flow: a thorough cleanse to remove surface buildup, exfoliation suited to your skin type, extractions if needed (always gentle, always careful), followed by targeted serums and treatment masks chosen specifically for you. We finish with hydration and sun protection so you leave ready for the rest of your day. Most sessions run about 45 minutes to an hour, and the experience is genuinely relaxing - even in a clinical setting. You'll feel the difference between this and a basic spa facial immediately. There's no guesswork. Every step has a purpose, and every product earns its place on your skin.</p><h2>Medical-Grade vs. Spa Facials</h2><p>We have nothing against a relaxing spa day. But there's a real difference between a facial designed to feel nice and one designed to create measurable change in your skin. At REFRESH LKN, we use medical-grade formulations with significantly higher active ingredient percentages than what you'll find at a traditional day spa. Choose from our Skinwave Hydrofacial or Jet Peel Facial. Our aestheticians are licensed professionals working within a clinical framework, with oversight from our nurse practitioner.</p><p>The result? You get the relaxation and the results. Treatments here aren't just about the hour you spend with us - they're about what your skin looks like a week later, a month later. And because we offer a full range of professional skincare services under one roof, your facial can be part of a bigger plan that includes SkinPen® microneedling, VI Peel® treatments, Forever Young BBL™ sessions, or whatever combination serves your skin best. That kind of integration is something only a medical-grade facial setting can offer.</p><h2>Who Benefits Most from Regular Facials</h2><p>Facials aren't a once-a-year indulgence. Think of them more like dental cleanings for your skin - regular maintenance that keeps small issues from becoming big ones. You'll benefit most if you're dealing with persistent acne or congestion that won't clear with home care alone. If you're starting to notice early signs of aging and want to get ahead of them. If you have sensitive or reactive skin and need someone who actually understands what's triggering your flare-ups.</p><p>We also see a lot of busy professionals from Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, and across the greater Charlotte metro who want efficient, high-impact treatments that fit into a real schedule. Whether you come monthly or quarterly, consistent facials create a baseline for your skin that makes everything else - your home routine, your other treatments - work better. Your skin responds to consistency, and we're here to help you build that rhythm.</p><h2>Start Your Skincare Path at REFRESH</h2><p>Whether you've had a hundred facials or you've never had one, we'd love to meet your skin. Every treatment at REFRESH LKN is built around you - your concerns, your goals, your comfort level. No two appointments look the same because no two faces are the same. We're located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, in Cornelius, right in the heart of the Lake Norman community. Getting started is easy. You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online anytime, or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> if you'd rather talk it through first. Either way, your skin will thank you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How often should I get a facial?</h3><p>For most skin types and goals, once a month is a great rhythm - it aligns with your skin's natural cell turnover cycle. If you're addressing a specific concern like acne or hyperpigmentation, we may recommend more frequent sessions initially, then space them out as your skin improves.</p><h3>Can I wear makeup after my facial?</h3><p>We recommend giving your skin at least 6 to 8 hours to breathe after your treatment. If you need coverage for an event the same day, a light mineral makeup is your safest bet. Your aesthetician will walk you through post-treatment care before you leave.</p><h3>How do I know which facial is right for me?</h3><p>You don't have to know - that's our job. During your consultation, your aesthetician will assess your skin and recommend the best approach based on what she sees and what you're experiencing. Just show up and tell us what's been on your mind.</p><h3>Are facials safe during pregnancy?</h3><p>Yes, with modifications. Certain active ingredients like retinoids and high-percentage acids are off the table during pregnancy, but we have plenty of safe, effective alternatives. Just let us know when you book so we can plan accordingly.</p><h3>Can facials help with acne scarring?</h3><p>Facials can absolutely improve skin texture and tone associated with mild scarring. For deeper or pitted acne scars, we'd likely recommend combining facials with treatments like SkinPen® microneedling or chemical peels for more significant improvement.</p><h3>Is there any downtime after a facial?</h3><p>Most facials have zero downtime - you can go right back to your day. Some deeper treatments may leave mild redness for a few hours, similar to a light sunburn, but nothing that would keep you from your normal routine.</p>
