<h1>Chemical Peels</h1><p>You've invested in good serums. You're consistent with your SPF. You cleanse every night and moisturize every morning. And yet - your skin still looks dull. Those dark spots from last summer haven't budged. The texture across your cheeks feels rough no matter what you try. Sound familiar? Sometimes the best skincare routine in the world can only do so much, because the damage isn't sitting on the surface. It's deeper than that.</p><p>That's exactly where a chemical peel comes in. This is a skin resurfacing treatment that works below the outermost layer, addressing what your at-home products simply can't reach. At REFRESH LKN, we don't do cookie-cutter peels pulled off a shelf. Every peel we perform is a medical-grade peel selected by our board-certified nurse practitioner based on your specific skin type, your concerns, and what you're hoping to achieve. This page will walk you through how peels work, what they treat, what recovery looks like, and why so many of our clients in Cornelius and the surrounding Lake Norman area count peels among their favorite treatments.</p><h2>What Is a Chemical Peel?</h2><p>A chemical peel is a clinical skin treatment where a professional-grade solution is applied to the face to accelerate the skin's natural exfoliation process. The solution works by loosening the bonds between old, damaged skin cells and the healthy skin underneath. Over the following days, that damaged outer layer sheds - and what's revealed beneath is smoother, brighter, and more even.</p><p>This is not the same as an exfoliating facial treatment you’d get at a day spa. The formulations we use at REFRESH LKN are clinical-strength, with controlled penetration depths that create real, measurable change in your skin—that’s a big distinction. Chemical peels have been one of the most trusted treatments in medical aesthetics for decades, and for good reason—they address everything from fine lines and wrinkles to acne scarring to stubborn discoloration. And they do it predictably, safely, and effectively when performed by trained providers using professional-grade products.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, we’ve carefully selected industry-leading peels to match a range of skin types and concerns. Our offerings include the VI Peel, BioRePeel, and The Perfect Derma™ Peel—each chosen for its ability to deliver consistent, noticeable results with minimal downtime. Whether you’re looking to brighten dull skin, target pigmentation, smooth texture, or support acne-prone skin, we customize the peel selection and treatment plan to meet you exactly where you are and help you get where you want to go.</p><h2>Skin Concerns Peels Can Correct</h2><h3>Uneven Tone and Hyperpigmentation</h3><p>Living in the Lake Norman area means spending time outdoors - on the water, at the pool, walking your neighborhood in Davidson or Huntersville. All that sun exposure adds up. Over time, it shows as dark patches, sun spots, and uneven skin tone that even the best vitamin C serum won't fully correct. Peels accelerate cell turnover at a rate your skin can't achieve on its own, fading discoloration layer by layer. For concerns like melasma or post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation, a peel is often the most effective first step in a hyperpigmentation treatment plan.</p><h3>Fine Lines and Aging Skin</h3><p>As we age, our skin's natural renewal process slows way down. Peels essentially jumpstart that process, stimulating collagen production while smoothing fine lines and wrinkles. Whether you use a peel as a standalone anti-aging treatment or pair it with injectables or laser treatments we already offer at REFRESH, the results speak for themselves - skin that looks firmer, fresher, and more alive.</p><h3>Acne and Acne Scarring</h3><p>If you're dealing with breakouts that won't quit or scarring left behind from years of acne, targeted peels can make a real difference. Certain formulations unclog pores and reduce oil production to calm active acne, while others work on smoothing depressed scars and evening out post-acne marks. We adjust the peel depth and formulation based on your acne severity - because what works for mild breakouts isn't what we'd choose for deep acne scarring treatment.</p><h3>Dullness and Rough Texture</h3><p>Sometimes your skin just looks... tired. It's not necessarily a specific condition you can name - it's more of a general flatness, a roughness you can feel when you run your fingers across your cheeks. A peel strips away that buildup of dead cells and reveals the brighter, smoother complexion hiding underneath. Many clients notice the difference after just one session.</p><p>If any of this sounds like what you're seeing in the mirror, we'd love to talk through your options. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online to set up a consultation.</p><h2>Superficial vs. Medium vs. Deep Peels</h2><p>Not all peels are created equal, and understanding the difference matters. Peel depth determines how far the solution penetrates, which directly affects intensity, downtime, and results.</p><p>Superficial peels - sometimes called "lunchtime peels" - target just the outermost layer of skin. They're gentle, require little to no downtime, and are perfect for maintenance or mild concerns like light dullness and minor uneven skin tone correction. You could get one over your lunch break and head right back to work in Mooresville or Charlotte without anyone knowing.</p><p>Medium-depth peels go further. They penetrate into the middle layers of skin to address moderate sun damage, deeper pigmentation, and more visible fine lines. Expect several days of peeling and some redness as your skin works through the renewal process. The tradeoff? Noticeably stronger results.</p><p>Deep peels are the most aggressive option and are reserved for significant concerns - deep wrinkles, pronounced scarring, substantial sun damage. These require careful medical oversight and meaningful downtime, but the results can be dramatic.</p><p>Here's what matters most: this isn't a decision you make from a menu. During your consultation at REFRESH LKN in Cornelius, our licensed aesthetician and nurse practitioner evaluate your skin thoroughly and recommend the appropriate depth based on your condition, your skin tone, your lifestyle, and how much downtime you can realistically accommodate. We'll explain exactly which level is right for you and why, so you feel completely confident before we begin.</p><h2>What to Expect During Treatment</h2><p>When you arrive at our Cornelius location, we start with a brief skin assessment. Your provider cleanses the skin and may apply a prep solution to ensure the peel penetrates evenly. Then the peel solution itself goes on. What does it feel like? Depending on the depth, you'll notice tingling, warmth, or a mild stinging sensation. Nothing unbearable - and your provider is monitoring your skin's response the entire time, adjusting as needed.</p><p>Most peels take somewhere between 20 and 45 minutes from start to finish. One thing our clients consistently mention is how different the experience feels compared to a larger clinic. At REFRESH, you're not being shuffled through a packed schedule. This is a boutique wellness and aesthetic clinic where your provider is focused entirely on you. After the peel is neutralized (if applicable), we apply soothing products and finish with SPF to protect your freshly treated skin before you walk out the door.</p><h2>Post-Treatment Skin Renewal</h2><p>Here's what happens next, and we want you to be prepared for it: your skin is going to peel. That's the whole point. It's post-treatment skin renewal working exactly as intended. After a light peel, you might see subtle flaking for two to three days. A medium peel involves more visible peeling over five to seven days, along with some redness. This is normal and temporary.</p><p>Your aftercare matters just as much as the treatment itself. We'll send you home with clear instructions - strict sun protection is non-negotiable, and you'll want to stick with a gentle cleanser and hydrating products while your skin recovers. No picking, no scrubbing, no active exfoliants. We'll recommend specific post-care products during your appointment to support the healing process.</p><p>Most clients notice a brighter, smoother complexion within one to two weeks. For deeper concerns - like stubborn hyperpigmentation or acne scarring - we may recommend a series of peels spaced out over several months to get you where you want to be. Every plan is built around your skin and your goals.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose REFRESH LKN</h2><p>Your skin deserves more than a one-size-fits-all approach, and that's exactly what we refuse to offer. Every chemical peel at REFRESH is overseen by our board-certified nurse practitioner, who works alongside our licensed aesthetician in Cornelius, NC to build a plan specific to you. We assess your skin individually - the peel type, strength, and layering technique are all customized based on what we see and what you tell us.</p><p>We're also Lake Norman's only medspa combining advanced lasers with hormone wellness, weight loss, and injectables - which means your peel can be part of a bigger picture. Peels pair beautifully with CoolPeel® CO2 treatments, Forever Young BBL™, VirtueRF® microneedling, or our signature facials when the time is right. Clients who come to us from Cornelius, Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, and across the greater Charlotte area stay because they feel like they're seen here. Not rushed. Not pushed toward services they don't need. Just cared for by people who actually know their skin.</p><h2>Book Your Peel Consultation</h2><p>Whether you're frustrated by dark spots that won't fade, texture that feels rough no matter what you try, early signs of aging, or you simply want to maintain the healthy skin you've worked hard for - a chemical peel consultation at REFRESH is the perfect starting point. We'll evaluate your skin, talk through your goals, and build a plan that makes sense for your life and your downtime tolerance. No pressure, no upselling. Just honest guidance from providers who care.</p><p><a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> to schedule your consultation at REFRESH LKN - 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC. We can't wait to see you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How often should I get a chemical peel?</h3><p>For light peels, most clients come in every four to six weeks as part of a maintenance routine. Medium-depth peels are typically spaced further apart - every three to six months depending on your skin's needs. If we're working on a specific corrective concern, we'll map out a series schedule during your consultation.</p><h3>Can I wear makeup after a chemical peel?</h3><p>We generally recommend waiting at least 24 to 48 hours before applying makeup after a light peel, and up to a week for medium-depth peels. Your provider will give you specific guidance based on the peel you receive, but the general rule is to let your skin breathe and heal before layering anything on top of it.</p><h3>Are chemical peels safe for darker skin tones?</h3><p>Yes - when the right peel is selected by an experienced provider. The concern with darker skin tones is the risk of post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation, which is why peel selection matters so much. At REFRESH, we carefully evaluate your skin tone and choose formulations that are safe and effective for you specifically.</p><h3>Can I combine a peel with other treatments?</h3><p>Absolutely, and many of our clients do. Chemical peels pair well with Forever Young BBL™, VirtueRF® microneedling, SkinPen® treatments, and our facials. We space treatments appropriately so your skin has time to recover between sessions, and your provider will build a combination plan that makes sense for your goals.</p><h3>What age should I start getting peels?</h3><p>There's no magic age. Teens dealing with acne can benefit from targeted peels, clients in their twenties often use light peels for maintenance and glow, and those in their forties and beyond may choose medium-depth peels for more corrective results. A consultation helps us determine what's appropriate for where you are right now.</p><h3>What's the difference between a peel and a facial?</h3><p>A facial focuses primarily on surface-level cleansing, hydration, and relaxation. A chemical peel creates controlled exfoliation at a deeper level, producing measurable corrective changes in tone, texture, and clarity. Both have their place, but if you're looking for visible improvement in a specific skin concern, a peel is the stronger choice.</p>
