<h1>Lashes, Brows &amp; Waxing</h1><p>You know that twenty minutes every morning - the mascara, the brow pencil, the careful blending so everything looks "natural"? What if you could skip most of that and still walk out the door feeling completely put together? That's exactly the kind of freedom our lash, brow, and waxing services are designed to give you. At REFRESH LKN, we treat these services with the same precision and care we bring to every treatment in our Cornelius wellness and aesthetic clinic. This isn't an afterthought tacked onto a menu. Our dedicated brow and lash specialist focuses entirely on the details that frame your face - lash lifts, tints, extensions, brow shaping, lamination, and professional waxing from your chin to your toes. Whether you live here in Cornelius or you're coming to us from Mooresville, Davidson, or Huntersville, you'll notice the difference when these services are done by someone who truly knows what they're doing.</p><h2>Lash Lift &amp;Tint </h2><h2>If you've ever wished your lashes had a little more curve and color without relying on mascara, a lash lift and tint is probably your perfect match. During a lash lift, we use a gentle solution to reshape your natural lashes from the root, creating a semi-permanent curl that opens up your eyes beautifully. Add a professional tint to that, and suddenly your lashes look darker, fuller, and more defined - no makeup required. The whole effect lasts about six to eight weeks, and the maintenance is basically zero. Wake up, wash your face, and go.</h2><p>Before any lash service, we start with a consultation. Your natural lash health matters to us. We assess the condition of your lashes, talk about your daily routine, and help you choose the right curl type and tint shade for your skin tone and eye shape. We have clients who drive past plenty of options in the Charlotte area to see us here in Cornelius because they trust the care and attention they get at REFRESH LKN. That kind of reputation means everything to us.</p><h2>Brow Shaping, Tinting &amp; Lamination</h2><h3>Eyebrow Shaping &amp; Tinting</h3><p>There's a real art to eyebrow shaping, and it goes way beyond plucking a few stray hairs. Our specialist maps your bone structure, evaluates your natural growth pattern, and designs an arch that complements your unique face shape. It's the kind of detail you just can't replicate with a pair of tweezers and a magnifying mirror at home. Pair that shaping with a professional brow tint, and the result is striking - sparse areas fill in with subtle color, everything looks more defined, and you get that "no-makeup makeup" effect that lasts three to five weeks. Shaping and tinting together is one of the fastest ways to refresh your entire look without changing a thing about the rest of your routine.</p><p>If you're ready to stop fighting your brows and lashes every morning, we'd love to help. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online whenever it's convenient.</p><h2>Professional Waxing Services</h2><h3>Facial Waxing in Cornelius</h3><p>Facial waxing requires a lighter touch and a sharper eye than body waxing, and the clinical setting at REFRESH makes a real difference here. We handle upper lip, chin, sideburns, and full face waxing with careful attention to your skin type and any sensitivities. Because our practitioners understand skincare on a clinical level, we screen for things like retinoid use and other contraindications that a typical salon might overlook. That means fewer reactions, better results, and skin that stays calm after your appointment. Most of our clients pair facial waxing with their brow shaping visit - it's efficient, and you leave with a completely polished look.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose REFRESH</h2><p>You might wonder why it matters where you get a lash lift or a wax. Here's the honest answer: the environment shapes the quality. At REFRESH Medical Spa &amp; Wellness, every service happens under the oversight of a board-certified nurse practitioner. That means the products we use are higher grade, our sanitation standards are stricter, and the people performing your treatment are trained to assess your skin health - not just get through the appointment. If something looks off with your skin, we'll tell you. If a product might cause a reaction given your history, we'll catch it before it becomes a problem.</p><p>There's also the advantage of having your beauty treatments under one roof with services like chemical peels, VI Peel® treatments, facials, and laser services. We can create a plan that addresses everything from your brows to your skin texture to fine lines - all coordinated and all personalized. REFRESH LKN is a woman-founded, relationship-driven practice here in Cornelius where you're a person, not a ticket number. That matters when someone is working inches from your eyes or on sensitive skin. Trust is everything, and we earn it one appointment at a time.</p><h2>Book Your Appointment</h2><p>Whether you're ready for your first lash lift, a brow rescue that's been a long time coming, or a head-to-toe waxing reset, we're here for it. Booking is easy - schedule online anytime at your convenience or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> to set something up. If you're not sure which service is right for you, that's totally fine too. Come in for a quick consultation and we'll figure it out together.</p><p>You'll find us at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031 - right in the heart of the Lake Norman community. <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> and let's get you feeling like yourself again.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How should I prepare for a lash lift or tint?</h3><p>Arrive with clean eyes - no mascara, eye makeup, or eyelash curler use that day. If you wear contact lenses, bring your case so you can remove them during the appointment. Avoiding caffeine beforehand can also help reduce any eye sensitivity.</p><h3>How often should I schedule waxing appointments?</h3><p>For most areas, every four to six weeks is ideal. Sticking to a consistent schedule helps synchronize your hair growth cycle, which means cleaner results each visit and finer regrowth over time. Your specialist can recommend the best timing based on your individual hair type.</p><h3>Is there downtime after brow tinting or lamination?</h3><p>Very little. We ask that you avoid getting your brows wet and steer clear of steam, saunas, and heavy sweating for about 24 hours. After that, you can go right back to your normal routine with no restrictions.</p><h3>What's the difference between hard wax and soft wax?</h3><p>Hard wax hardens on the skin and is removed without strips - it grips hair without pulling at the skin, making it gentler on sensitive areas like the bikini line and face. Soft wax is applied thinly and removed with cloth strips, which works well for larger areas like legs and arms. Our practitioners choose the best option for each body area and your skin type.</p><h3>Can I combine multiple services in one visit?</h3><p>Absolutely - and many clients do. Popular combos include brow shaping with a tint and lash lift, or facial waxing added onto a brow appointment. Just let us know when you book so we can set aside enough time and make sure your visit flows smoothly.</p>
