<h1>BOTOX® Treatments</h1><p>You know that moment - you catch your reflection and notice the frown line between your brows is still there, even when you're not frowning. Or the forehead crease that used to disappear has decided to move in permanently. These are the small changes that start to bother you, not because you're vain, but because they don't match how you actually feel. BOTOX® exists for exactly this reason. It's not a trend or a quick fix - it's the most studied, most trusted wrinkle relaxer in cosmetic medicine, backed by decades of clinical research and millions of treatments worldwide. At REFRESH LKN, every single injection is personally administered by our board-certified nurse practitioner, who is focused on one thing: making you look like yourself, just refreshed. Not frozen. Not overdone. You. Our Cornelius office gives Lake Norman clients access to expert-level care without fighting traffic into Charlotte. This is where we begin.</p><h2>How BOTOX® Wrinkle Relaxers Work</h2><p>BOTOX® is a neuromodulator injection, which is a fancy way of saying it temporarily relaxes specific facial muscles. Here's the basic idea: every time you squint, frown, or raise your eyebrows, the muscles underneath your skin contract and create folds. Over time, those folds become creases that stick around even when your face is at rest. BOTOX® works by blocking the nerve signals that tell those muscles to contract. The muscle relaxes, the skin smooths out, and the wrinkle softens.</p><p>It's worth knowing the difference between dynamic wrinkles and static wrinkles. Dynamic wrinkles are the ones caused by movement - the lines you see when you make an expression. Static wrinkles are the ones that stay visible even when your face is completely relaxed. BOTOX® directly treats dynamic wrinkles, and here's the bonus: by relaxing those muscles early enough, you can actually prevent dynamic wrinkles from becoming permanent static lines. Results aren't instant. You'll start noticing changes within three to five days, with the full effect settling in around day fourteen. It's a gradual shift, not a dramatic overnight change - and that's exactly the point.</p><h2>Common Treatment Areas</h2><h3>Frown Lines &amp; Forehead Lines</h3><p>The vertical lines between your brows - sometimes called the "11s" or glabellar lines - are one of the most popular areas we treat with BOTOX®. These lines can make you look tired, stressed, or even angry when you're feeling perfectly fine. Horizontal forehead lines are another frequent request. They develop from years of raising your eyebrows, and while they're completely natural, smoothing them out creates a noticeably more rested, relaxed appearance. What we love about treating these areas is how subtle the result can be. Your expressions still move. Your face still looks like your face. You just look like you had the best sleep of your life.</p><h3>Crow's Feet &amp; Beyond</h3><p>Crow's feet - those little lines that fan out from the corners of your eyes when you smile - are another signature BOTOX® treatment area. They're charming in photos sometimes, but plenty of our clients feel they add years they'd rather not advertise. Beyond these classic zones, there's a lot more BOTOX® can do that most people don't realize. A small amount placed strategically can create a subtle brow lift, smooth bunny lines on the nose, reduce chin dimpling, or even soften neck bands along the platysma muscle. A BOTOX® lip flip - a few precise units along the upper lip border - gives a gentle pout without any filler at all. The key to all of this is having a skilled, licensed injector who understands facial anatomy and tailors every treatment to your unique structure and goals. We don't do cookie-cutter. We do you.</p><h2>Preventative BOTOX® for Younger Clients</h2><p>You don't have to wait until wrinkles are fully established to start thinking about anti-aging injections. Preventative BOTOX® has become increasingly popular among clients in their late twenties and thirties, and the reasoning is simple: if you relax the muscles before deep creases form, you stop those lines from ever setting in permanently. Think of it like ironing a shirt before the wrinkle becomes a crease - much easier to manage early on.</p><p>That said, we're never going to over-treat you. Our approach at REFRESH is consultative and age-appropriate. If you're 28 and starting to notice faint forehead lines, we might use a conservative number of units to keep things smooth without making you look like you've had anything done. The goal isn't to look "done." It's to maintain the skin you have right now, for longer. Subtle prevention is an act of self-care, not vanity.</p><p>If you're curious about whether preventative BOTOX® makes sense for you, we'd love to talk it through. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online - a quick consultation is all it takes to get started.</p><h2>What to Expect During Your Visit</h2><h3>Consultation &amp; Custom Treatment Plan</h3><p>Every new client at REFRESH starts with a one-on-one consultation right here in our Cornelius office. This isn't a rushed five-minute chat - we take the time to really look at your facial anatomy, listen to what's been bothering you, and understand your aesthetic goals. We also review your medical history to make sure BOTOX® is a safe and appropriate option for you. From there, we build a personalized treatment plan that accounts for your muscle strength, your facial structure, and the results you're hoping for. No cookie-cutter dosing. No standard unit counts that get applied to every face that walks through the door.</p><h3>The Injection Process</h3><p>The actual treatment is quick - most BOTOX® appointments take somewhere between ten and twenty minutes. We use a very fine needle, and most clients describe the sensation as a brief pinch. Nothing that requires numbing cream or anesthesia, though we're happy to use ice if you'd prefer. Many of our clients come in on a lunch break and head right back to work afterward. Before your appointment, we recommend avoiding blood thinners, aspirin, and alcohol for about 24 hours to minimize any chance of bruising. That's about it for prep.</p><h3>Recovery &amp; Results Timeline</h3><p>There's no real downtime with BOTOX®. You might notice some mild redness or tiny pinpoint marks at the injection sites, but these typically fade within an hour or so. We ask that you avoid rubbing or massaging the treated areas for the rest of the day and skip intense workouts for 24 hours - this helps the product stay right where we placed it. You'll start seeing results within three to five days as the muscles begin to relax, and the full effect settles in beautifully by day fourteen. Most clients find their results last three to four months. Consistent maintenance appointments help keep everything looking smooth, and over time, some clients actually find they need fewer units as the muscles learn to stay relaxed.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose REFRESH LKN</h2><p>There's a reason people drive from Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, and across the Lake Norman area to see us for cosmetic injections - and it starts with who's holding the syringe. Our board-certified nurse practitioner personally performs every BOTOX® treatment. Your care is never handed off to someone with less training or experience. That matters, especially when we're talking about your face.</p><p>We also think about BOTOX® as one piece of a bigger picture. As Lake Norman's only medical spa combining advanced laser treatments with hormone wellness, personalized weight loss, and injectables, we see the full you - not just one wrinkle. Sometimes BOTOX® is all you need. Other times, pairing it with a treatment like CoolPeel® or dermal fillers creates a result that BOTOX® alone can't achieve. We'll always be honest about what makes sense and what doesn't.</p><p>And then there's the experience itself. REFRESH is a warm, boutique environment - not a high-volume clinic where you're in and out before anyone learns your name. We take our time. We listen. Our goal is for people to tell you that you look great, rested, glowing - not that you "got BOTOX®." Natural-looking results, every time. That's the standard here.</p><h2>Schedule Your BOTOX® Consultation</h2><p>Whether you've been thinking about wrinkle relaxers for a while or you're just starting to explore what's possible, we make the process comfortable and pressure-free. Your first step is a consultation where we talk through your goals, answer every question you have, and put together a plan that feels right for you. No commitment beyond the conversation.</p><p>You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online anytime, or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031 - right in the heart of the Lake Norman community. We proudly welcome clients from Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, Denver, and throughout the greater Charlotte area. We'd love to meet you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How many units of BOTOX® will I need?</h3><p>Unit counts vary quite a bit depending on the treatment area and the strength of your individual muscles. For example, frown lines might require anywhere from 15 to 30 units, while crow's feet typically need 8 to 15 units per side. We determine the right amount for you during your consultation - it's never a guessing game.</p><h3>Is BOTOX® safe to combine with dermal fillers?</h3><p>Absolutely, and we actually do this quite often in the same appointment. BOTOX® relaxes the muscles that cause wrinkles while fillers restore volume and smooth lines that are already etched in. Your provider will recommend the best sequencing and combination based on what you're looking to address.</p><h3>Can BOTOX® help with excessive sweating or jaw clenching?</h3><p>Yes - BOTOX® is FDA-approved for treating hyperhidrosis (excessive sweating), particularly in the underarm area. It's also commonly used to relax the masseter muscle for clients dealing with jaw clenching or TMJ discomfort. We're happy to discuss these therapeutic uses during your consultation at REFRESH.</p><h3>What happens if I stop getting BOTOX® treatments?</h3><p>Your muscles will gradually return to their normal function, and the wrinkles will come back to wherever they were before you started treatment. The good news is they won't get worse because you had BOTOX® - there's no rebound effect and no dependency. You simply go back to your baseline.</p><h3>How do I choose between BOTOX® and other neuromodulators like Dysport® or DAXXIFY®?</h3><p>All three are botulinum toxin type A products that work in a very similar way, but they have slight differences in onset time, how far they spread, and dosing units. Some clients respond better to one than another. We'll recommend the best option based on your treatment area, your history, and how your body has responded to previous treatments.</p><h3>Are there any medical conditions that would prevent me from getting BOTOX®?</h3><p>BOTOX® is not recommended during pregnancy or while nursing, and certain neuromuscular disorders like myasthenia gravis or ALS may also be disqualifying. Active skin infections at the injection site are another reason to wait. This is exactly why we ask for a full medical history during your consultation - your safety always comes first.</p>
