<h1>Dysport® Treatments</h1><p>You catch a glimpse of yourself in the rearview mirror and wonder - when did those lines between my brows get so deep? You're not stressed. You're not angry. But your face tells a different story. Those frown lines between eyebrows and the creases that run across your forehead can add years and an expression that doesn't match how you actually feel. Dysport® is a wrinkle relaxer treatment specifically designed to soften those lines and give your face permission to look as relaxed as you are. Here at REFRESH LKN, every Dysport® injection is performed by our board-certified injector - a nurse practitioner with advanced training who treats your face as the unique canvas it is, not a diagram from a textbook. This page covers everything you need to know before you book, from how Dysport® works to what your appointment will actually feel like.</p><h2>What Is Dysport®?</h2><p>Dysport® is an FDA-approved neuromodulator injection made from botulinum toxin type A. When injected into specific facial muscles, it temporarily blocks the nerve signals that cause those muscles to contract. The result? Smoother skin where repetitive movement has been creating lines and creases. Dysport® has been used around the world for decades, and its safety profile is well established.</p><p>What sets Dysport® apart from other neuromodulator injections is its protein structure. The molecules are slightly smaller, which allows for a broader, more natural diffusion across the treatment area. Many clients love the soft, even result this creates - especially in larger zones like the forehead. One thing worth knowing: units of Dysport® are not the same as units of other wrinkle relaxers. The dosing conversion is something we handle during your consultation, so you never have to worry about the math.</p><h2>Treatment Areas for Dysport®</h2><h3>Forehead Lines and Frown Lines</h3><p>Forehead lines treatment is one of the most popular reasons clients come to us for Dysport®. Those horizontal creases that form every time you raise your eyebrows - they respond beautifully to a few precise injections. The glabellar lines, also known as the "elevens" between your brows, are actually the primary FDA-approved indication for Dysport®. This is where its natural diffusion pattern really shines, creating smooth results without that heavy, "frozen" look across the upper face.</p><h3>Crow's Feet Reduction</h3><p>The fine lines that fan out from the corners of your eyes when you smile or squint are completely normal - but they can become deeper over time, eventually sticking around even when your face is at rest. Crow's feet reduction with Dysport® softens these lines while keeping your smile authentic. This area demands an experienced hand because the skin around the eyes is thin and the muscles are delicate. Precise placement matters here more than almost anywhere else.</p><h3>Brow Lift and Other Uses</h3><p>A brow lift injection isn't about dramatically reshaping your face. It's about strategically placing Dysport® to relax the muscles that pull your brows downward, allowing the natural lifting muscles to do their thing. The effect is subtle - a slightly more open, refreshed look around the eyes. Some clients also ask about off-label uses like a lip flip, jawline slimming, or neck bands. We're happy to discuss those during your consultation and determine whether Dysport® or another approach makes the most sense for your goals.</p><h2>What to Expect During Your Appointment</h2><p>When you walk into REFRESH, the first thing you'll notice is that it doesn't feel clinical or intimidating. It feels like a place where someone is actually going to listen to you. Your appointment starts with a one-on-one consultation with our nurse practitioner. She'll assess your facial anatomy, ask about your goals, and determine the right number of units of Dysport® for each area. There's no rushing through this part.</p><p>The treatment itself takes roughly 10 to 20 minutes. We use fine-gauge needles, and most clients describe the sensation as a quick pinch - nothing dramatic. Anesthesia isn't typically needed, though ice or topical numbing is available if you'd prefer it. One thing that matters to many of our clients: the same nurse practitioner who consults with you is the one performing your injections. Every single time. There's no hand-off to rotating staff.</p><p>After treatment, you're free to go about your day. We just ask that you skip heavy exercise for the rest of the day, avoid lying flat for about four hours, and resist the urge to rub or massage the treated areas.</p><p>If you're ready to see what Dysport® can do for you, we'd love to hear from you. Call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online whenever it's convenient.</p><h2>Dysport® Results and Longevity</h2><p>Here's something clients love about Dysport®: it tends to kick in fast. Many people notice their muscles starting to relax within two to three days, which is often quicker than other neuromodulator injections. Full results typically settle in by day 10 to 14, and that's when you'll really see the smoothing effect at its best.</p><p>Results generally last three to four months, though your individual experience depends on factors like metabolism, muscle strength, and how many units of Dysport® were used. Here's the encouraging part - with consistent treatments over time, the muscles you're targeting actually learn to stay more relaxed on their own. Many of our long-term clients find they can gradually extend the time between visits.</p><p>A word on expectations: Dysport® is incredible at softening dynamic wrinkles - the ones caused by movement - and preventing them from becoming deeper. If you have lines that are visible even when your face is completely still, Dysport® can improve their appearance over time, but those etched-in creases may benefit from a combination approach we can discuss together.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose REFRESH LKN</h2><p>There's no shortage of places offering cosmetic injections in Cornelius, NC and the surrounding Lake Norman area. So why do clients from Huntersville, Davidson, Mooresville, and even south Charlotte keep finding their way to our door? It starts with who's holding the needle. Our nurse practitioner is board-certified with advanced injectable training, and she personally performs every treatment. No exceptions.</p><p>REFRESH is Lake Norman's only medical spa combining advanced lasers, hormone wellness, personalized weight loss, and injectables under one roof. That means if Dysport® alone isn't the full answer - if dermal fillers, a CoolPeel® laser treatment, or skin resurfacing would give you a more complete result - we can build that plan together without sending you somewhere else. Our approach to Lake Norman clinical injectables is personal. We look at your face, your skin, your life. We dose conservatively, place precisely, and always prioritize a result that looks like you - just refreshed.</p><h2>Is Dysport® Right for You?</h2><p>If you're an adult who's bothered by moderate to severe dynamic wrinkles - lines that show up when you move your face - Dysport® is a proven, minimally invasive option worth considering. It's a botulinum toxin type A product with a long track record, and the treatment itself takes less time than most lunch breaks.</p><p>Dysport® isn't recommended if you're pregnant or nursing, have certain neuromuscular conditions, or have a known allergy to botulinum toxin products. And if you've ever worried about looking "frozen" or expressionless - that concern usually disappears once you see what conservative, thoughtful dosing actually looks like. You'll still look like you. You'll still move like you.</p><p>The best way to find out if Dysport® fits your goals is to sit down with us. Sometimes Dysport® alone is the answer. Sometimes we'll recommend pairing it with dermal fillers or a skin treatment for results that go even further. That's what the consultation is for - no pressure, just a plan that makes sense for your face and your life.</p><h2>Book Your Dysport® Consultation</h2><p>If you've been searching for anti-aging injections near me and you've made it to this point on the page, something tells us you're ready. We'd love to meet you, hear what's been on your mind, and show you what's possible. REFRESH LKN is located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031 - right in the heart of the Lake Norman community and easy to reach from Denver, Sherrills Ford, and anywhere in the north Charlotte area.</p><p><a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. Your refreshed look is closer than you think.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How many units of Dysport® will I need?</h3><p>It varies by area and by person, but common ranges are 40–60 units for glabellar lines, 20–40 for forehead lines, and 20–30 for crow's feet. Our nurse practitioner determines your exact dosing during the consultation after evaluating your muscle activity and goals. Remember, Dysport® units are measured differently than other wrinkle relaxers, so the numbers will sound higher - that's completely normal.</p><h3>Does Dysport® hurt?</h3><p>Most clients describe it as a quick pinch that's over before they have time to think about it. The needles are extremely fine, and the injections take just seconds per site. If you're sensitive, we can apply ice or a topical numbing cream beforehand - just let us know.</p><h3>Can I combine Dysport® with fillers in one visit?</h3><p>Absolutely. Many clients choose to do a full-face session where we address both movement-based lines with Dysport® and volume loss with dermal fillers. Our nurse practitioner will advise on what's safe and appropriate to combine based on the areas being treated.</p><h3>How far in advance should I schedule before a special event?</h3><p>We recommend booking at least two weeks before any big occasion. This gives Dysport® time to fully settle and allows any minor bruising - which is uncommon but possible - to completely resolve. If it's your first time, three weeks gives you even more breathing room.</p><h3>How much does Dysport® cost?</h3><p>Dysport® is priced per unit, and total cost depends on how many units your treatment plan requires. During your consultation, we'll give you a clear estimate based on your specific goals. We want you to know exactly what to expect before we begin.</p><h3>What's the difference between Dysport® and other wrinkle relaxers?</h3><p>The main differences come down to molecular size, diffusion pattern, and onset speed. Dysport® tends to spread more evenly across broader areas and often shows results a bit faster. Unit measurements differ between products, so a direct number comparison isn't apples to apples. The best way to know which wrinkle relaxer is right for you is to discuss it with us during your visit.</p>
<hr>
<h1>JEUVEAU® Treatments</h1><p>You catch your reflection in the rearview mirror and notice those two vertical creases between your brows - the ones that make you look frustrated even when you're perfectly happy. Or maybe it's the horizontal lines across your forehead that seem deeper in every photo. You're well-rested, you feel great, and yet your face tells a different story. That disconnect is real, and it's exactly why so many of our clients at REFRESH LKN ask about JEUVEAU®. This modern wrinkle relaxer was built from the ground up specifically for aesthetics - a prabotulinumtoxinA treatment designed with one purpose in mind: smoothing the lines that bother you most. As newtox injections go, JEUVEAU® has become a favorite here in our Cornelius office because it delivers targeted, natural-looking results without the premium price tag of legacy brands. Every treatment is performed by our board-certified nurse practitioner, so you're in experienced hands from the very first consultation. You have options when it comes to anti-aging injections in Cornelius, NC, and JEUVEAU® is one worth knowing about.</p><h2>What Is JEUVEAU® (Newtox)?</h2><p>JEUVEAU® is an FDA-approved injectable neurotoxin - and when it launched, it was the first new neurotoxin to receive approval in nearly a decade. The aesthetic community quickly nicknamed it "newtox," and for good reason. Unlike other botulinum toxin products that were originally developed for medical conditions and later adapted for cosmetic use, JEUVEAU® was purpose-built for one thing: frown line treatment and cosmetic wrinkle reduction. That single-minded focus is part of what makes it appealing.</p><p>Here's how it works. JEUVEAU® temporarily relaxes the specific facial muscles responsible for dynamic wrinkles - the ones that form when you squint, frown, or raise your eyebrows. It does this by blocking the nerve signals that tell those muscles to contract. The result? Smoother skin where those repetitive movements have been leaving their mark. And just to clear up a common question - this is different from dermal fillers. Fillers add volume. JEUVEAU® relaxes movement. Two completely different tools, both useful in their own way.</p><h2>Treatment Areas for Wrinkle Relaxers</h2><h3>Frown Lines &amp; Forehead Wrinkles</h3><p>Those vertical "eleven lines" between your brows - the glabellar lines - are the primary FDA-approved indication for JEUVEAU®. They're caused by the corrugator muscles that pull your brows together every time you concentrate, squint at your laptop, or react to something surprising. Over time, those lines stick around even when your face is completely at rest. Forehead wrinkle treatment addresses the horizontal creases higher up, the ones created by habitually raising your eyebrows. These two areas tend to be the first places clients want to address because they're front and center during every conversation, every video call, every photo. They shape how people read your expression - and when those lines are softened, you just look more like yourself.</p><h3>Crow's Feet Treatment</h3><p>The fine lines that fan out from the outer corners of your eyes deepen every time you smile, laugh, or squint into the sun. If you spend any time out on Lake Norman, hiking local trails, or just enjoying the Carolina sunshine, crow's feet treatment is probably something that's crossed your mind. JEUVEAU® softens these lines while still letting your smile look completely natural - because the goal is never to erase expression. It's to smooth the creases that linger after the smile fades.</p><h3>Brow Lift Injection</h3><p>This one is all about technique. A brow lift injection uses strategic placement of neurotoxin injections to gently relax the muscles that pull the brow downward, allowing the natural lifting muscles to do their thing. The result is a subtle but noticeable opening of the eye area - you look more awake, more refreshed, without anyone being able to pinpoint exactly what changed. This isn't a one-size-fits-all approach. It requires a practitioner who understands the anatomy of your specific brow shape and muscle dynamics. That's exactly why our nurse practitioner handles every treatment personally at REFRESH - this kind of precision matters.</p><p>If you're curious about which areas would make the biggest difference for you, we'd love to talk it through. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online whenever you're ready.</p><h2>What to Expect During Your Appointment</h2><p>If this is your first time considering neurotoxin injections, we want you to know - there's nothing intimidating about this appointment. Really. When you walk into our Cornelius office, the vibe is warm and relaxed, not clinical or sterile. Your visit starts with a one-on-one conversation with our nurse practitioner. She'll look at your facial movement patterns, talk about what's been bothering you, and ask about the results you're hoping for. Maybe you want something subtle. Maybe you want to go a bit more aggressive with the frown lines. Either way, the plan is built around you - your anatomy, your muscle strength, your goals.</p><p>The actual injection process is quick. Most appointments take 15 to 30 minutes total. The needles are very small, and while you'll feel a brief pinch with each injection, most clients describe it as completely manageable - no anesthesia needed. There's no downtime afterward, either. You can head right back to work, pick up the kids, grab lunch in Davidson, whatever your day looks like. That's why people call this a lunchtime treatment. It fits into your life without asking you to rearrange it.</p><h2>Results, Timing &amp; Maintenance</h2><p>Here's the part everyone wants to know. You'll typically start noticing changes within two to three days as the neurotoxin begins taking effect. Full results settle in around 10 to 14 days - that's when you'll see the complete smoothing of those targeted lines. It's a gradual process, which is actually a good thing. No one wakes up looking dramatically different overnight. You just start noticing that the crease between your brows isn't as deep, or that your forehead looks calmer and more relaxed.</p><p>Results from JEUVEAU® generally last about three to four months for most clients. To maintain that smoother look, we recommend scheduling follow-up treatments on a regular cadence. An interesting thing we see with consistent clients - over time, some people find they can stretch their appointments a bit further apart as those overactive muscles gradually weaken. Results do vary person to person, and we'll always be honest with you about what to expect. Natural-looking smoothing, never a frozen face. That's the REFRESH philosophy.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose JEUVEAU®</h2><p>So why pick JEUVEAU® over another wrinkle relaxer treatment? A few reasons come up again and again. First, pricing. JEUVEAU® is frequently more affordable than legacy neurotoxin brands, which makes a real difference when you're maintaining results every few months. Lower cost doesn't mean lower quality - it means a newer product competing for your trust, and the savings get passed along to you.</p><p>Second, it was designed exclusively for aesthetics. That purpose-built approach resonates with clients who like knowing their botulinum toxin alternative wasn't originally intended for something else entirely. The efficacy and safety profile are comparable to other well-known neurotoxins - same mechanism of action, same FDA approval process, supported by clinical trials. Some clients even tell us they notice results a touch faster with JEUVEAU®, though individual experiences vary.</p><p>We'll be straightforward with you: if you're wondering whether JEUVEAU® is "as good as" another brand you've tried, the honest answer is that it works the same way at the molecular level. At REFRESH, we offer multiple neurotoxin options because different products work slightly differently for different people. We'll help you figure out which one is the best fit for your face and your budget.</p><h2>Cosmetic Injections Near Lake Norman</h2><p>Choosing where to get injectable treatments matters just as much as choosing the product itself. At REFRESH LKN, our board-certified nurse practitioner performs every single injection - your treatment is never handed off to someone with less training or experience. She brings a deep understanding of facial anatomy and an eye for balance that comes from working with hundreds of clients across the Lake Norman area.</p><p>We also think about the bigger picture. Neurotoxin injections are just one piece of what we do here. Because we offer everything from dermal fillers to laser treatments to wellness services under one roof, we can help you build a plan that actually makes sense for your skin, your goals, and your life - not just a quick fix for one concern. Our Cornelius office is easy to reach from Huntersville, Mooresville, Davidson, and communities throughout the greater Lake Norman area, so getting here is simple no matter which direction you're coming from.</p><p>If you're ready to see what JEUVEAU® can do for you - or if you just have questions and want to talk through your options - we're here. <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online, call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>, or stop by our office at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031. We'd love to meet you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions About JEUVEAU®</h2><h3>Is JEUVEAU® safe for first-time patients?</h3><p>Absolutely. JEUVEAU® went through rigorous FDA clinical trials before approval, and its safety profile is well-established. If you've never had a neurotoxin injection before, it's actually a great starting point - our nurse practitioner will walk you through every step and start conservatively so you feel comfortable with the process and the results.</p><h3>Can JEUVEAU® be combined with fillers or other treatments?</h3><p>Yes, and many of our clients do exactly that. JEUVEAU® addresses movement-based wrinkles while dermal fillers restore lost volume in areas like the cheeks or lips. We often map out a treatment plan that incorporates both, along with skin treatments like CoolPeel® or SkinPen® microneedling, depending on what you're looking to achieve.</p><h3>How many units of JEUVEAU® will I need?</h3><p>Unit count varies quite a bit from person to person. It depends on the treatment area, the strength of your facial muscles, and the look you're going for. We determine the right number during your consultation rather than applying a standard formula - what works for one person's forehead may be completely different for yours.</p><h3>Are there side effects I should know about?</h3><p>The most common side effects are minor and temporary - slight redness or swelling at the injection site, occasional bruising, and in rare cases a mild headache. Serious side effects are uncommon but possible, which is exactly why having an experienced, credentialed injector matters so much. We'll review your full health history before any treatment.</p><h3>What should I avoid before and after treatment?</h3><p>In the days leading up to your appointment, try to avoid blood-thinning medications (with your doctor's approval), alcohol, and supplements like fish oil or vitamin E that can increase bruising. Afterward, don't rub or massage the treated areas, skip intense exercise for about 24 hours, and stay upright for at least four hours post-treatment.</p><h3>How does JEUVEAU® pricing compare to other wrinkle relaxers?</h3><p>JEUVEAU® is typically priced lower per unit than brands like BOTOX® or Dysport®, which can add up to meaningful savings over the course of a year of maintenance treatments. We're always happy to discuss pricing during your consultation and help you understand the total investment based on the areas you want treated.</p>
