<h1>DAXXIFY® Treatments</h1><p>You know the cycle. You get your wrinkle relaxer, love how you look for about two months, then start noticing those lines creeping back in right around month three. So you book another appointment, rearrange your schedule, and start all over again. It's effective, sure - but wouldn't it be nice if those results just... stuck around longer?</p><p>That's exactly why we're excited to offer DAXXIFY® at REFRESH LKN. This is the first and only FDA-approved wrinkle treatment powered by a peptide-based formula, and it's changing the way we think about long-lasting wrinkle relaxers. Clinical results show it lasts significantly longer than traditional neuromodulator injections - we're talking months longer, not days. Our board-certified nurse practitioner personally administers every DAXXIFY® treatment, so you're always in expert hands. No handoffs, no surprises. Just precision care from someone who knows facial anatomy inside and out.</p><p>This isn't hype. It's a real shift in what's possible with cosmetic injectables in Cornelius, NC.</p><h2>How DAXXIFY® Works</h2><p>DAXXIFY® - the technical name is DaxibotulinumtoxinA-lanm - is a neuromodulator injection. Like BOTOX® and Dysport®, it works by temporarily relaxing the muscles responsible for creating wrinkles. When those muscles stop contracting as forcefully, the skin above them smooths out. The frown lines soften. The forehead calms down. You still look like you, just more rested.</p><p>So what makes DAXXIFY® different? It comes down to what's holding the formula together. Traditional neurotoxins use human serum albumin - a protein derived from human blood - as a stabilizer. DAXXIFY® replaces that with a proprietary peptide. This makes it the first peptide-based injectable in its class, and researchers believe this unique formulation is what gives DAXXIFY® its extended results. The peptide essentially helps the active ingredient bind more effectively at the treatment site.</p><p>DAXXIFY® received FDA approval specifically for the treatment of glabellar lines - those vertical frown lines between the brows that can make you look tired or frustrated even when you're neither. The science is solid, and the results speak for themselves.</p><h2>Treatment Areas and Candidates</h2><p>The primary FDA-approved use for DAXXIFY® is moderate-to-severe glabellar lines treatment - the "11s" that form between your eyebrows when you concentrate, squint, or frown. These are often the first dynamic wrinkles people notice, and they're some of the most stubborn to smooth out with skincare alone.</p><p>Beyond the 11s, our nurse practitioner may also use DAXXIFY® for forehead line smoothing and other areas based on her clinical expertise and your specific goals. Every face is different, and that matters more than most people realize. Muscle strength, skin thickness, how your expressions move across your face - all of these influence where and how we treat.</p><p>You might be a great fit for DAXXIFY® if you're bothered by wrinkles that show up when you make expressions and are starting to linger even when your face is at rest. At REFRESH, we never assume. We assess your facial anatomy, listen to what's bothering you, and build a plan from there.</p><h2>DAXXIFY® vs BOTOX®</h2><h3>Results That Last 6–9 Months</h3><p>Here's where DAXXIFY® really stands apart. In clinical trials, the median duration of results was approximately six months, with some patients seeing their results hold for up to nine months. Compare that to BOTOX® or Dysport®, which typically wear off in three to four months.</p><p>Think about what that means for your year. Instead of three or four appointments to maintain your results, you might only need two. That's fewer days juggling your calendar around an appointment, fewer co-pays or session fees, and fewer of those frustrating weeks where you can feel the lines starting to return but it's not quite time for your next visit. For busy people across the Lake Norman area - from Davidson to Huntersville to Mooresville - fewer trips to the office is a real win.</p><h3>Same Appointment, Different Technology</h3><p>The actual treatment experience with DAXXIFY® is nearly identical to what you'd expect with any neuromodulator injection. It's a quick in-office visit with fine-needle injections and minimal downtime. The difference isn't in how it's given - it's in what's inside the syringe and how long those results carry you.</p><p>That said, DAXXIFY® isn't automatically the right choice for everyone. If you're brand new to wrinkle relaxers, you might prefer starting with a shorter-acting option so you can see how your face responds before committing to an extended results neurotoxin. And that's perfectly fine. At REFRESH, we carry multiple options and we'll always recommend what makes sense for you - not push a single product on every person who walks through the door.</p><p>If you're curious whether DAXXIFY® fits into your goals, we're happy to talk it through. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online - no pressure, just answers.</p><h2>What to Expect During Treatment</h2><h3>Before Your Session</h3><p>Every DAXXIFY® treatment at REFRESH starts with a one-on-one consultation with our nurse practitioner. She'll evaluate your facial anatomy, talk through what you're hoping to achieve, and review your medical history to make sure DAXXIFY® is safe and appropriate for you. This is the kind of individualized planning we're known for - your face, your goals, your plan.</p><p>In the days before your appointment, we'll ask you to avoid blood-thinning medications and supplements like aspirin, ibuprofen, fish oil, and vitamin E. Skipping alcohol for 24 hours beforehand also helps minimize bruising. Small steps that make a real difference.</p><h3>During and After Treatment</h3><p>The appointment itself is quick - usually 15 to 30 minutes depending on how many areas we're treating. The number of injection sites varies, but most clients describe the sensation as a brief pinch. No anesthesia needed.</p><p>Afterward, we'll ask you to stay upright for a few hours, avoid touching or rubbing the treated areas, and skip intense workouts for the rest of the day. That's about it. Most people head right back to their normal routine. You'll start to notice smoothing within one to two days, with the full effect settling in around day 14. And then you get to enjoy it - for a long time.</p><h2>Anti-Aging Injectables at REFRESH LKN</h2><p>DAXXIFY® is one piece of a much larger picture at REFRESH Medical Spa &amp; Wellness. We offer a full range of anti-aging injections in Lake Norman, including BOTOX®, dermal fillers, PRF treatments, and more. What makes our approach different is that we see the whole person, not just the wrinkle.</p><p>As Lake Norman's only clinic combining advanced lasers with hormone wellness, personalized weight loss, and injectable treatments, we can help you build a strategy that addresses how you look and how you feel. Our nurse practitioner understands facial aesthetics and overall wellness, so your cosmetic injectable in Cornelius, NC can be part of something bigger - whether that means pairing DAXXIFY® with a CoolPeel® laser treatment, exploring bioidentical hormone therapy, or simply starting with one thing and seeing where it takes you.</p><p>We proudly serve clients throughout the Charlotte area, including Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, and the broader Lake Norman community. Wherever you're coming from, you'll find a warm, thoughtful team ready to meet you where you are.</p><h2>Schedule Your DAXXIFY® Consultation</h2><p>Choosing a new injectable can feel like a big decision, and we want you to feel completely comfortable before anything happens. That's why we always start with a conversation. Come in, ask every question on your mind, and let's figure out together whether DAXXIFY® is your next step - or whether something else might be a better fit right now.</p><p>We'd love to meet you. <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. You'll find REFRESH LKN at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031. We'll be here when you're ready.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>Is DAXXIFY® safe for first-time injectable patients?</h3><p>Yes, DAXXIFY® is FDA-approved and safe for people who've never had neuromodulator injections before. That said, some first-timers prefer to start with a shorter-acting option like BOTOX® so they can experience how a wrinkle relaxer feels and looks before committing to longer-lasting results. We'll walk through the options during your consultation so you can make the choice that feels right.</p><h3>How much does DAXXIFY® cost compared to BOTOX®?</h3><p>The per-session cost of DAXXIFY® is generally higher than BOTOX® because the product itself is priced differently. However, since DAXXIFY® typically requires fewer sessions per year, many clients find their total annual spending is comparable - or even lower. We'll give you personalized pricing during your consultation based on the areas you'd like treated.</p><h3>Can DAXXIFY® be combined with fillers or other treatments?</h3><p>Absolutely. Many of our clients pair DAXXIFY® with dermal fillers, laser treatments, or other clinical injectables in the Charlotte area for a more complete result. Our nurse practitioner will help you plan the timing and sequence so each treatment complements the others.</p><h3>Are there side effects specific to DAXXIFY®?</h3><p>The most common side effects include headache, mild bruising or swelling at the injection site, and occasional eyelid heaviness. These are similar to what you'd expect from other FDA-approved neurotoxins and typically resolve on their own within a few days. Serious side effects are rare, and we'll review everything with you before treatment.</p><h3>What if I don't like my results?</h3><p>Because DAXXIFY® is a temporary treatment, the effects will naturally fade over time even without any intervention. The longer duration is a benefit for most people, but if you're at all uncertain, starting with a smaller treatment area can help you feel more confident about the process. We'll never push you toward more than you're comfortable with.</p><h3>Do you offer financing for DAXXIFY® treatments?</h3><p>We want great care to be accessible. Ask our team about current payment options and any promotions when you schedule your consultation. We're always happy to help you find a way to make your treatment plan work within your budget.</p>
<hr>
<h1>SCULPTRA® Collagen Stimulator</h1><p>You've been staring at yourself in the rearview mirror again, tilting your chin, pulling your skin back just slightly - wondering when your face started looking so… tired. Not old, exactly. Just deflated. Like the structure underneath quietly packed its bags and left. That hollowness in your temples, the way your cheeks don't catch light the way they used to, the deepening lines framing your mouth - none of it happened overnight. It happened slowly, over years, as your body's collagen production wound down. And here's the thing most people don't realize: traditional dermal fillers can replace what's missing, but they don't fix the reason it went missing. SCULPTRA® takes an entirely different approach. Instead of adding volume from the outside, it activates your body's own ability to rebuild from within. It's a collagen stimulating treatment that works with your biology, not around it. And at REFRESH LKN, our board-certified nurse practitioner personally administers every single treatment - because something this nuanced deserves that level of care.</p><h2>Why Your Face Loses Volume</h2><p>Starting in your mid-twenties, your body begins producing less collagen - roughly one percent less each year. By the time you hit fifty, nearly half your collagen is gone. That's the protein responsible for keeping your skin firm, lifted, and full. Without it, skin loses its scaffolding. Cheeks flatten. Temples hollow. The jawline softens. And because it happens gradually, most people don't notice until one day they look in the mirror and something just feels off.</p><p>Here's where it gets tricky. Hyaluronic acid fillers like JUVÉDERM® and Restylane® are wonderful tools - we use them at REFRESH all the time. But they're designed to add volume in a specific spot, right now. They don't ask your body to make anything new. Once the filler dissolves, you're back to the same deficit. SCULPTRA® is a biostimulator filler, which means it addresses the root cause of dermal volume loss. It triggers your skin to actually produce collagen again. The result isn't instant fullness. It's your own tissue rebuilding itself over time - which is exactly why the results look so incredibly natural.</p><h2>How Poly-L-Lactic Acid Injections Work</h2><p>SCULPTRA®'s active ingredient is poly-L-lactic acid, or PLLA. It's a biocompatible, biodegradable synthetic material that's been used safely in medicine for decades - including dissolvable sutures. Nothing exotic. Nothing experimental. Just well-understood science applied to aesthetics in a really smart way.</p><p>When poly-L-lactic acid injections are placed into the deep dermis, the PLLA microparticles create a mild, controlled inflammatory response. Think of it as a signal to your body: "Hey, we need more structure here." Your fibroblasts - the cells that manufacture collagen - get to work. Over the following weeks and months, new collagen fibers form around the PLLA particles, which gradually dissolve on their own. What you're left with isn't a foreign substance sitting under your skin. It's your own collagen, your own tissue, restoring volume and firmness from the inside out.</p><p>This is what makes SCULPTRA® a true collagen production booster rather than a traditional filler. The product itself isn't what gives you the result. Your body is. SCULPTRA® just starts the conversation.</p><h2>Gradual Results That Look Natural</h2><h3>The Treatment Timeline</h3><p>Most patients need two to three treatment sessions, spaced about four to six weeks apart. You won't walk out looking dramatically different after your first appointment - and that's entirely by design. Gradual volume restoration is what makes SCULPTRA® so appealing to people who want natural-looking anti-aging results without anyone knowing they've had anything done. No sudden shift. No "what happened to her face?" moment at brunch. Just a slow, steady return to a version of yourself that looks rested, healthy, and full of life.</p><h3>What Results Look Like</h3><p>Over the months following your sessions, you'll notice restored midface volume, softened nasolabial folds, improved definition along the jawline, and an overall reduction in skin laxity. Deep wrinkle correction happens naturally as the new collagen fills in areas that had gone flat or hollow. People often tell us their friends and family comment that they look amazing but can't quite pinpoint why. That's the goal. Looking refreshed rather than "worked on." And here's what really sets SCULPTRA® apart as a long-lasting facial filler alternative: results can last two years or more. For many of our clients in Cornelius and the surrounding Lake Norman area, that kind of longevity changes the math on everything.</p><h2>What SCULPTRA® Treats at REFRESH</h2><p>We use SCULPTRA® to address volume loss across multiple areas of the face. Temples that have gone hollow. Cheeks that have lost their lift. The midface, jawline, chin, nasolabial folds, marionette lines, and pre-jowl area - all common spots where collagen depletion shows up first. It's an effective dermal volume loss treatment whether the cause is age-related or the result of significant weight loss, which can leave the face looking gaunt even when you feel healthier than you have in years.</p><p>For many of our clients coming from Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, and the greater Charlotte area, SCULPTRA® serves as a non-surgical face lift option. It provides real structural improvement without surgery, without general anesthesia, and without weeks of recovery. That said, it's not the right answer for everyone. During your consultation, our nurse practitioner evaluates your facial anatomy, listens to what's bothering you, and makes an honest recommendation. Sometimes SCULPTRA® is perfect on its own. Sometimes it works best combined with other treatments. And sometimes a different approach entirely makes more sense. We'd rather tell you the truth than sell you a treatment.</p><p>If you're curious whether SCULPTRA® is right for what you're seeing in the mirror, we're happy to talk it through. Call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online - no pressure, just a real conversation.</p><h2>Your SCULPTRA® Appointment in Cornelius</h2><h3>Before Treatment</h3><p>Everything starts with a consultation at REFRESH LKN on West Catawba Avenue. Our nurse practitioner will assess your facial structure, ask about your goals, review your medical history, and set expectations that are honest and grounded. This isn't a rushed appointment where someone tries to upsell you. It's a thoughtful evaluation of what will actually give you the results you're after.</p><p>In the days leading up to treatment, we'll ask you to avoid blood thinners, alcohol, and certain supplements like fish oil and vitamin E - all of which can increase bruising. We'll give you a clear pre-treatment checklist so there are no surprises.</p><h3>During and After</h3><p>Each session typically takes thirty to forty-five minutes. The product is mixed with lidocaine for comfort, and we apply topical numbing beforehand. Injection technique matters enormously with SCULPTRA® - precise placement and proper depth are what separate a beautiful, even result from a mediocre one. This is exactly why our practitioner handles every treatment personally.</p><p>Afterward, you'll follow what's known as the 5-5-5 rule: massage the treated areas for five minutes, five times a day, for five days. This helps distribute the product evenly and encourages smooth collagen formation. Temporary swelling, tenderness, and some redness at the injection sites are completely normal and typically resolve within a few days. Most people head right back to their regular routine - picking up kids from school, running to meetings in Cornelius or Huntersville, all of it. Downtime is minimal.</p><h2>SCULPTRA® vs. Other Options</h2><p>Hyaluronic acid fillers like JUVÉDERM® and Restylane® give you instant volume that lasts several months to a year, and they're reversible - which makes them ideal for targeted areas like lips or under-eye hollows. SCULPTRA® works differently. It's a gradual process that addresses broader volume loss and actually improves skin quality over time. Think of it as facial rejuvenation without surgery, focused on rebuilding rather than replacing.</p><p>Treatments like RF microneedling with VirtueRF® or laser resurfacing with CoolPeel® - both available at REFRESH - complement SCULPTRA® beautifully by addressing texture, tone, and fine lines at the skin's surface while SCULPTRA® rebuilds structure underneath. Many of our clients combine approaches for a result that covers all the bases. Skin, tone, texture, definition - all thoughtfully enhanced.</p><p>The right plan depends entirely on you. During your consultation, we'll map out what makes the most sense for your face, your goals, and your timeline.</p><h2>Schedule Your Consultation</h2><p>We built REFRESH LKN to be the kind of place where you can walk in, say "something doesn't look right and I don't know what to do about it," and get an honest, expert answer. No jargon. No pressure. Just a board-certified nurse practitioner who will look at your face, listen to your concerns, and help you understand your options - whether that's SCULPTRA®, something else entirely, or a combination that gets you where you want to be.</p><p>We're located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, in Cornelius - right in the heart of Lake Norman and easy to reach from Denver, Mooresville, Davidson, and throughout the Charlotte metro. If you've been thinking about this, trust that instinct. <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We'd love to meet you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How much does SCULPTRA® cost?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the number of vials needed and how many sessions your treatment plan includes, so it varies from person to person. We'll give you a clear cost breakdown during your consultation so you know exactly what to expect before committing to anything.</p><h3>Am I a good candidate if I've had dermal fillers before?</h3><p>Absolutely - many of our clients have existing hyaluronic acid filler and transition to SCULPTRA® for longer-lasting, broader results. Our nurse practitioner will evaluate what's currently in place and design a plan that works with it, not against it.</p><h3>How many vials of SCULPTRA® will I need?</h3><p>Most patients need anywhere from two to six vials per session, depending on age, degree of volume loss, and which areas are being treated. This is something we determine together during your consultation after assessing your facial structure in person.</p><h3>Does SCULPTRA® work on areas other than the face?</h3><p>SCULPTRA® can be used on the décolletage, buttocks, and hands to stimulate collagen in those areas as well. During your appointment at REFRESH, we'll discuss which treatment areas make sense for your specific goals and what to realistically expect.</p><h3>What if I don't complete all recommended sessions?</h3><p>You'll still see some benefit - collagen stimulation begins with the first treatment. However, partial treatment typically yields partial results, and you may not achieve the full structural improvement that a complete series delivers.</p><h3>Does REFRESH offer financing for SCULPTRA® treatments?</h3><p>We want treatments to be accessible, so we're happy to discuss payment options when you come in for your consultation. Our team can walk you through what's available so cost doesn't have to be the thing that holds you back.</p>
