<h1>Restylane® Dermal Fillers</h1><p>You catch your reflection and something feels off. Not dramatic - just a subtle shift. Maybe your cheeks don't sit quite where they used to, or the lines around your mouth seem deeper than you remember. Your under-eye area looks hollow even after a full night's sleep. You still feel like you, but the mirror isn't keeping up. That disconnect? It's one of the most common things we hear from clients walking through our doors in Cornelius for the first time.</p><p>Restylane® is one of the most trusted families of hyaluronic acid filler injections available, and it's designed to do exactly what you need - restore what time quietly takes away. At REFRESH LKN, our board-certified nurse practitioner personally administers every single injection. Your face is never handed off to someone with less training or less experience. When you sit down with us, you're getting clinical expertise paired with a genuine understanding of what natural-looking filler results actually look like on a real person living a real life.</p><h2>What Is Restylane®?</h2><p>Restylane® isn't a single product - it's an entire FDA-approved collection of dermal fillers, each one formulated with hyaluronic acid. Hyaluronic acid is a substance your body already makes naturally. It lives in your skin, holds onto moisture, and gives your face its underlying structure and bounce. As we age, we produce less of it, and that's when volume loss, lines, and that "deflated" look start to creep in.</p><p>What makes Restylane® so versatile is that each product in the family - Restylane®-L, Restylane® Defyne, Restylane® Kysse, Restylane® Lyft, Restylane® Contour - is engineered with a different gel texture. Thicker gels lift and contour. Softer gels move with your expressions. This is different from neurotoxins like BOTOX®, which relax muscles that cause wrinkles. Fillers actually add volume back and smooth lines from the inside out, making Restylane® one of the most flexible tools for non-surgical facial rejuvenation we have.</p><h2>Treatment Areas &amp; Natural Results</h2><p>This is the part most people really want to know - what can Restylane® actually do for me? The answer depends on where you're noticing changes, and that's exactly what we figure out together. But here's a look at the areas we treat most often, and why the specific product choice matters just as much as the technique.</p><h3>Lips &amp; Smile Lines</h3><p>Lip filler in Cornelius, NC does not have to look overdone. Period. Restylane® Kysse was designed specifically for lips - the gel is soft and flexible, so your lips move naturally when you talk, smile, and laugh. No stiffness, no "duck lip." Just your lips, a little fuller, a little more defined. For the lines that run from your nose to the corners of your mouth - nasolabial folds, or what most people call smile lines - we often reach for Restylane® Defyne. It's designed to integrate smoothly into tissue that moves a lot, so the correction looks natural even when your face is animated. Smile line filler done well should be invisible. People should notice that you look great, not that you "got something done."</p><h3>Cheeks &amp; Midface Volume</h3><p>Your cheeks do more than you might think. They're the scaffolding of your entire face - when cheek volume drops, everything below it follows. You get deeper folds, a heavier jawline, and a tired look that has nothing to do with how much sleep you got. Cheek augmentation near Lake Norman using Restylane® Lyft or Restylane® Contour restores that foundational support. We're not building cheekbones you never had. We're putting back what was there before. Facial volume restoration in the midface is one of the most effective anti-aging filler treatments we offer because the impact cascades - lift the cheeks and the whole face looks refreshed. Years come off without a single incision.</p><h3>Under Eyes &amp; Tear Troughs</h3><p>This might be our most requested treatment across the entire Charlotte area. Those dark, hollow circles under your eyes? Often that's not fatigue or allergies - it's volume loss beneath the skin. Under eye filler carefully placed in the tear trough can soften that hollowness and reduce the shadow that makes you look exhausted. Here's what you should know: this is a delicate area with thin skin and complex anatomy. Having an experienced, board-certified injector matters more here than almost anywhere else on the face. It's one of the reasons our nurse practitioner never delegates injections - especially in high-precision areas like this.</p><p>If you're seeing changes that bother you and want to explore what's possible, we'd love to talk. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online - a conversation is always the best first step.</p><h2>Your Consultation at REFRESH LKN</h2><p>A dermal filler consultation at REFRESH starts with you telling us what you're noticing. You don't need to know product names or treatment terminology. Just point to what's bothering you, tell us how you want to feel, and we take it from there.</p><p>Our nurse practitioner evaluates your entire face - bone structure, skin quality, proportions, how different areas relate to each other. Even if you come in focused on one specific thing, we look at the bigger picture. Why? Because treating one area in isolation can sometimes look off. A balanced approach gives you results that make sense for your face as a whole. That might mean Restylane® in one area, BOTOX® in another, and a skin treatment layered on top. Or it might mean starting with a single syringe and seeing how you feel.</p><p>There's no pressure to treat on the same day as your consultation. We'd rather you feel completely confident in your plan than rush into anything. This is your face. We take that seriously. As Lake Norman's only clinic combining advanced lasers with hormone wellness, personalized weight loss, and injectables, we see your skin and your overall well-being as connected - and that perspective shapes every recommendation we make.</p><h2>What to Expect During &amp; After</h2><h3>The Treatment Experience</h3><p>Most Restylane® treatments take between 15 and 30 minutes, depending on the areas we're addressing. The process is straightforward - after cleansing and marking your treatment zones, we place the filler with precision using fine needles or cannulas. Every Restylane® formulation contains lidocaine, a built-in numbing agent, so comfort is part of the design. We also offer topical numbing cream if you'd like an extra layer of ease. You'll see results right away in the mirror, though your final, settled result takes about one to two weeks as any initial swelling resolves.</p><h3>Recovery &amp; Aftercare</h3><p>Downtime is minimal. Most of our clients in Cornelius head right back to their day - work, errands, school pickup, whatever life looks like. You may notice some mild swelling and tenderness at the injection sites, and bruising is possible, especially around the lips and under-eye area. That's normal and temporary. We ask that you skip strenuous exercise for 24 hours, avoid excessive heat like saunas or prolonged sun exposure, and resist the urge to press or massage the treated areas unless we've specifically told you to. Results typically last anywhere from 6 to 18 months depending on the product used, the treatment area, and your individual metabolism. We'll talk through what to expect for your specific plan so there are no surprises.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose REFRESH LKN</h2><p>Our board-certified nurse practitioner performs every injection, every time. That's not a marketing line - it's a promise. When you're choosing who holds a needle near your eyes or lips, experience and credentials aren't optional. REFRESH is a female-founded wellness and aesthetic clinic built on a simple belief: you should look like yourself, just refreshed. Not overdone. Not frozen. Not someone else entirely. We treat your aesthetic goals, your skin health, and your overall wellness as parts of one picture - because they are.</p><p>Our location at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, in Cornelius makes us an easy destination for clients throughout the Lake Norman area, including Huntersville, Davidson, Mooresville, and the greater Charlotte region. But people don't drive from across the metro because we're convenient. They come because they trust us with their face.</p><h2>Schedule Your Restylane® Consultation</h2><p>Whether you're thinking about your very first syringe of filler or you've been getting Restylane® for years and want a fresh perspective, it all starts with a real conversation about what you want and what's possible. No scripts, no pressure - just honest guidance from someone who does this every day and loves it.</p><p>You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online anytime, or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031 - right in the heart of the Lake Norman community. We'd love to meet you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>Is Restylane® safe for first-time filler patients?</h3><p>Absolutely. Restylane® has been FDA-approved for years and has one of the longest safety track records of any dermal filler family on the market. It's one of the products we recommend most often for clients who've never had filler before because results are natural, predictable, and reversible if needed.</p><h3>How do I know which Restylane® product is right for me?</h3><p>You don't need to figure that out - that's our job. During your consultation, our nurse practitioner assesses your facial anatomy, your goals, and the specific area being treated to determine exactly which Restylane® formulation will give you the best result. Different textures work better in different parts of the face, and we match accordingly.</p><h3>Can Restylane® be dissolved if I'm unhappy?</h3><p>Yes, and this is one of the biggest advantages of hyaluronic acid fillers. An enzyme called hyaluronidase can be injected to dissolve Restylane® quickly if you're not happy with the results or if any correction is needed. It's a safety net that other filler types simply don't offer.</p><h3>How much does Restylane® cost at REFRESH?</h3><p>Pricing varies depending on how many syringes you need and which areas we're treating. We're always happy to discuss options that fit both your goals and your budget during your consultation. We'd rather give you an accurate, personalized quote than post a number that may not apply to your situation.</p><h3>Can I get Restylane® and BOTOX® at the same appointment?</h3><p>Yes, many of our clients benefit from combining filler and neurotoxin in a single visit. We assess whether that makes sense for your specific treatment plan during your consultation, and we'll walk you through exactly what to expect if we recommend both.</p><h3>What's the difference between Restylane® and JUVÉDERM®?</h3><p>Both are hyaluronic acid-based fillers, and both are excellent products. The differences come down to gel technology - how the filler is cross-linked and how it behaves in tissue. Honestly, the skill and experience of the person injecting you matters more than which brand is on the box. We choose the product that performs best for each specific area and concern.</p>
<hr>
<h1>Morpheus8® RF Microneedling</h1><p>You're doing the right things - the serums, the sunscreen, the consistent skincare routine - but somewhere along the way, your skin stopped responding the way it used to. Maybe it's a softness along the jawline you didn't notice until recently, or texture changes that no amount of retinol seems to touch. Maybe it's the way your neck skin looks in photos, or acne scars you've carried since your twenties that still bother you every time you catch your reflection. These aren't things surgery needs to fix. But they're also beyond what a good moisturizer can handle. Morpheus8® RF microneedling sits right in that sweet spot - a fractional radiofrequency treatment that works beneath the skin's surface to rebuild what time, sun exposure, and gravity have quietly undone. At REFRESH LKN in Cornelius, NC, we use Morpheus8® as one of our most powerful tools for subdermal tissue remodeling, and every treatment is performed or directly overseen by our board-certified nurse practitioner. No guesswork. No cookie-cutter plans. Just honest guidance about what will actually work for your skin.</p><h2>How Morpheus8® Works</h2><p>Standard microneedling - like the kind we do with SkinPen® - creates controlled micro-injuries in the skin to trigger your body's natural healing response. It's a great treatment for surface-level concerns. Morpheus8® takes that concept significantly further. The device uses gold-coated microneedles that penetrate the skin and simultaneously deliver radiofrequency energy deep into the tissue, reaching depths of 4mm or more. That RF energy heats the underlying fat and connective tissue layers, creating a wound-healing cascade that goes well beyond what needles alone can accomplish.</p><p>The result is true collagen induction therapy - your body generates fresh collagen and elastin from the inside out, restructuring and tightening tissue at a level that topical products simply cannot reach. Because Morpheus8® is a fractional treatment, only a portion of the skin is affected during each pass. This means your body can heal faster while still receiving dramatic remodeling benefits. It's the difference between refinishing a floor by sanding the whole thing at once versus working in careful, strategic sections. Same beautiful outcome, far less downtime.</p><h3>Face, Neck, and Body Applications</h3><p>On the face, Morpheus8® is one of the best non-surgical facelift alternatives available today. It's especially effective along the jawline where early jowling starts, around the nasolabial folds, and for under-eye crepiness that makes you look more tired than you actually are. Clients who want more jawline definition without filler often love what Morpheus8® can do on its own.</p><p>The neck is notoriously difficult to treat - most devices don't work well there - but Morpheus8® is one of the few treatments that genuinely tightens neck skin. And it doesn't stop at the chin. We also use the Morpheus8® Body tip for larger treatment zones like the abdomen, inner arms, knees, and thighs. If you're dealing with mild laxity or want body contouring in the Lake Norman area without surgery, this is worth a conversation.</p><h2>Skin Concerns Morpheus8® Treats</h2><p>People come to us for Morpheus8® for all kinds of reasons, and that's part of what makes it such a versatile treatment. Wrinkles and fine lines - especially those stubborn ones around the mouth, across the forehead, and near the eyes - respond beautifully to the deep collagen remodeling that RF microneedling skin tightening provides. If skin laxity and sagging are your main concern, Morpheus8® delivers the kind of tightening that actually holds because the changes happen beneath the surface.</p><p>For acne scarring, Morpheus8® is one of the most effective options we offer. The RF energy breaks down old scar tissue and stimulates new, healthy collagen to fill in textured areas - making it a go-to acne scar treatment for clients coming to us from the greater Charlotte area. It also addresses uneven skin tone and texture, enlarged pores, and stretch marks on the body. One thing worth knowing: Morpheus8® is safe and effective across all skin tones, which is a real advantage over certain laser treatments that carry higher risk for darker complexions.</p><p>During your consultation, we'll look at what's going on with your skin and talk honestly about whether Morpheus8®, CoolPeel®, or another treatment is the right fit. Sometimes the answer is a combination. Sometimes it's something completely different. We'd rather tell you the truth than sell you a treatment you don't need.</p><p>Ready to find out what Morpheus8® can do for your skin? Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online - we'll take it from there.</p><h2>What to Expect During Treatment</h2><p>We start by applying a topical numbing cream about 30 to 45 minutes before your treatment begins. This makes a real difference in comfort, and we want you to feel at ease the entire time. Once your skin is numb and cleansed, we use the Morpheus8® handpiece in a controlled stamping pattern across the treatment area. The tiny needles penetrate the skin while simultaneously delivering RF energy to the deeper tissue layers. Most sessions take between 30 and 60 minutes, depending on how many areas we're treating.</p><p>What does it feel like? You'll feel pressure and warmth - some areas are more sensitive than others, and we're honest about that. Most clients describe it as very manageable with the numbing in place. There are no incisions, no general anesthesia, and no operating room. This is a minimally invasive skin rejuvenation procedure performed right here in our Cornelius office. Immediately afterward, your skin will look red and feel warm, similar to a moderate sunburn. Some mild swelling is normal and expected.</p><h3>Recovery and Downtime</h3><p>Most of the redness and swelling fades within two to three days. The tiny micro-lesions created during treatment heal within three to five days, and most clients can wear makeup again after about 48 to 72 hours. Compared to ablative laser treatments, the social downtime is minimal - most people are back to their normal routine within a day or two. For aftercare, we recommend sticking to a gentle cleanser, a hydrating serum, and consistent SPF. Skip the active ingredients like retinol and acids for about a week to let your skin focus on healing.</p><h2>Results and Collagen Remodeling Timeline</h2><p>Here's where patience pays off. You'll notice some initial improvement within one to two weeks as swelling resolves and the skin starts to tighten. But the real transformation unfolds over the following three to six months as new collagen and elastin fibers mature and strengthen. Your skin keeps getting better long after the treatment itself is over - that's the beauty of collagen induction therapy working from the inside out.</p><p>For most concerns, we recommend a series of two to three Morpheus8® treatments spaced four to six weeks apart. If you're addressing deep scarring or more significant laxity, additional sessions may be helpful. Results typically last one to two years or longer, especially when you're consistent with quality skincare and sun protection. Many of our clients at REFRESH combine Morpheus8® with other services - Forever Young BBL™, PRP skin treatments, or injectables - for a more complete rejuvenation plan. We build that plan around you, your goals, and your timeline. That's how we approach medical spa skin care in Cornelius.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose REFRESH LKN</h2><p>Our board-certified nurse practitioner personally performs or directly oversees every Morpheus8® treatment. This isn't handed off to someone with less training or experience. You're getting clinical-level expertise in a warm, boutique setting - not a revolving door of providers at a high-volume chain. REFRESH is Lake Norman's only wellness and aesthetic clinic combining advanced RF and laser technology with services like bioidentical hormone therapy, medical weight loss, and nutrition support. We see the full picture of your skin health, not just the surface.</p><p>Our consultations are thorough and honest. If Morpheus8® isn't the right answer for what you're noticing, we'll tell you. Clients come to our W. Catawba Avenue location in Cornelius from across the region - Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, and the greater Charlotte area - because they trust us to give them a straight answer and a thoughtful plan.</p><p>If you've been thinking about radiofrequency skin tightening and you want to know whether Morpheus8® makes sense for your skin, a consultation is the best place to start. We'll look at what's happening, listen to what's bothering you, and map out a realistic path to the results you're after. You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online whenever it's convenient, or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're here when you're ready.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>Is Morpheus8® painful?</h3><p>With the topical numbing cream we apply beforehand, most clients find the treatment very tolerable - you'll feel warmth and pressure, but sharp pain is uncommon. We check in with you throughout the session and can adjust settings or add more numbing if any area feels too intense. Your comfort matters to us, and we take the time to make sure you feel good about the experience.</p><h3>How many Morpheus8® sessions will I need?</h3><p>Most clients see great results with two to three sessions spaced four to six weeks apart, though some concerns may respond well to just one treatment. At your consultation, we'll assess your skin and create a plan based on what you're hoping to achieve. Everyone's starting point is different, so your plan will be specific to you.</p><h3>Can Morpheus8® be combined with BOTOX® or fillers?</h3><p>Absolutely - many of our clients do combination treatment plans for more complete results. We typically recommend scheduling injectables about two weeks before or two weeks after a Morpheus8® session to allow each treatment to work without interference. We'll map out the timing for you so everything works together smoothly.</p><h3>What age is best to start Morpheus8®?</h3><p>There's no single right age. Clients in their early 30s often use Morpheus8® preventively to maintain skin firmness and boost collagen before visible aging sets in. Clients in their 40s, 50s, 60s, and beyond see wonderful corrective results for laxity, texture, and scarring. It really comes down to what your skin needs right now.</p><h3>How is Morpheus8® different from CoolPeel® CO2?</h3><p>We offer both at REFRESH, and they do different things. Morpheus8® works deeper - it remodels tissue beneath the surface for tightening and structural improvement. CoolPeel® is a CO2 laser that focuses on surface-level resurfacing, improving tone, sun damage, and fine texture. During your consultation, we'll help you decide which one - or whether a combination - fits your goals best.</p><h3>Does REFRESH offer financing for Morpheus8® treatments?</h3><p>Yes, we want to make sure the treatments you need are accessible. We're happy to walk you through available financing options during your consultation so you can make a decision that feels comfortable for both your skin and your budget. Just ask - we'll give you all the details upfront.</p>
<hr>
<h1>SkinPen® Microneedling</h1><p>You've been consistent with your skincare. The serums, the SPF, the retinol routine you researched for weeks before committing. And yet - those acne scars still catch the light wrong. The fine lines around your eyes seem deeper every morning. The texture on your cheeks refuses to smooth out no matter what you layer on. It's not that your products aren't working. It's that some concerns live deeper than any topical can reach.</p><p>That's exactly where SkinPen® microneedling comes in. This FDA-cleared, minimally invasive skin rejuvenation treatment works with your body's own healing response to rebuild your skin from the inside out. No harsh chemicals. No extended downtime. Just real, progressive results that keep getting better over time. At REFRESH LKN, we offer SkinPen® microneedling under the direct oversight of our board-certified nurse practitioner right here in Cornelius, NC - because your skin deserves expert-level care, not guesswork.</p><h2>What Is Collagen Induction Therapy?</h2><p>SkinPen® is a medical-grade microneedling device that creates thousands of controlled micro-channels across the surface of your skin. Each tiny puncture triggers your body's natural wound-healing cascade - a three-phase process that clears out damaged tissue, floods the area with growth factors, and generates fresh collagen and elastin production where you need it most. The clinical term for this process is collagen induction therapy, and it's one of the most well-studied approaches to skin rejuvenation available today.</p><p>Here's what makes SkinPen® different from those at-home derma rollers you've probably seen online: precision, sterility, and adjustable needle depth. A professional device lets us control exactly how deep the needles penetrate - which matters a lot when we're treating delicate skin around your eyes versus denser tissue on your cheeks or jawline. At-home rollers can't do that. They also carry a higher risk of infection and uneven results because they lack the sterile, single-use cartridge design that SkinPen® uses. This device earned FDA clearance for a reason - it's held to a standard that consumer-grade tools simply aren't.</p><h2>Skin Concerns SkinPen® Treats</h2><h3>Acne Scars &amp; Scarring</h3><p>If you've been living with acne scars, you already know they can affect how you feel about your skin long after the breakouts stop. Microneedling for acne scars works by breaking down the rigid, fibrous scar tissue beneath the surface while stimulating new collagen to fill in and smooth out depressed areas. Whether you're dealing with rolling scars that create a wave-like texture, boxcar scars with defined edges, or deeper ice pick scars, SkinPen® can make a measurable difference in how your skin looks and feels. Multiple sessions build on each other, and many of our clients in the Lake Norman area tell us this was the treatment that finally gave them confidence to go without full-coverage foundation.</p><h3>Fine Lines, Wrinkles &amp; Aging Skin</h3><p>Fine lines and wrinkles treatment doesn't have to mean dramatic intervention. SkinPen® restores firmness and smooths crepey texture by encouraging your skin to produce the collagen it naturally slows down on as you age. We see especially good results around the eyes, mouth, and forehead - those areas where expression lines tend to settle in first. And because we offer a full range of anti-aging services at REFRESH, we can pair SkinPen® with treatments like Forever Young BBL™ or injectables when a combined approach makes sense for your goals.</p><h3>Texture, Tone &amp; Stretch Marks</h3><p>Skin texture and tone improvement is one of the most common reasons clients book SkinPen® treatments with us. Enlarged pores, rough patches, sun damage, uneven pigmentation - these all respond well to collagen induction therapy. And SkinPen® isn't limited to your face. Microneedling for stretch marks on the abdomen, thighs, and arms is a proven application that we recommend often, especially for clients who've been through pregnancy or significant weight changes. The versatility of this treatment is one of the things we love most about it.</p><p>If any of this sounds like what you've been dealing with, we'd love to talk through your options. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online - we'll take it from there.</p><h2>The SkinPen® Treatment Experience</h2><h3>Before Your Session</h3><p>Every SkinPen® treatment at REFRESH starts with a one-on-one skin assessment. We want to understand what's bothering you, what you've already tried, and what kind of results you're hoping for. From there, we'll map out a plan that's specific to your skin - not a cookie-cutter approach pulled off a shelf. Before your appointment, we'll ask you to avoid retinoids, chemical exfoliants, and excessive sun exposure for a few days. These pre-treatment instructions help ensure your skin responds as well as possible to the procedure.</p><h3>During the Procedure</h3><p>On treatment day, we start by cleansing your skin thoroughly. Then we apply a topical numbing cream and give it about 20 to 30 minutes to take full effect - because your comfort matters. Once you're numb, the SkinPen® device glides across the treatment area in a controlled, methodical pattern. You might feel a light vibrating sensation and hear a soft buzzing sound, but most clients describe it as very tolerable. A full-face session typically takes 30 to 45 minutes, and we adjust the needle depth based on which areas we're treating and what concerns we're addressing. Forehead gets a different setting than cheeks. Scars get a different approach than fine lines. That precision is the whole point.</p><h3>Recovery &amp; Aftercare</h3><p>One of the biggest advantages of SkinPen® as a minimally invasive skin rejuvenation option is how quickly you bounce back. Expect mild redness similar to a sunburn for about 24 to 48 hours. Some clients notice light peeling a few days later as the skin turns over. Most people return to their normal routine the next day. For aftercare, keep it simple: gentle cleanser, a good SPF, and skip makeup for the first 24 hours. We'll send you home with specific instructions so you don't have to guess.</p><h2>SkinPen® Results &amp; What to Expect</h2><p>You'll likely notice a healthy glow within the first few days after your treatment - that's the initial healing response doing its thing. But the real magic happens over the following weeks as your skin ramps up collagen production beneath the surface. Full collagen remodeling from a single session takes about four to six weeks, which is why we typically recommend a series of three to four treatments spaced four to six weeks apart for the best results.</p><p>When it comes to microneedling before and after expectations, honesty matters more than hype. This isn't an overnight transformation. It's progressive, cumulative improvement that continues building for months after your final session. Many of our clients notice their most dramatic changes two to three months after completing a full series. Skin resurfacing in Cornelius, NC doesn't require aggressive downtime or intense procedures to deliver the kind of change you can actually see in the mirror. Sometimes the gentler path gets you further.</p><h2>Why Choose REFRESH LKN in Cornelius</h2><p>REFRESH isn't a typical medical spa in Cornelius, NC. When you come to us for SkinPen® microneedling, your treatment is performed by our board-certified nurse practitioner - not handed off to a technician. That level of clinical oversight means safer treatments and better outcomes, period. We also think about your skin as a whole picture, not just one appointment at a time. If combining SkinPen® with PRP, a VI Peel®, or Forever Young BBL™ would get you to your goals faster, we'll tell you that up front.</p><p>As the only Lake Norman clinic combining advanced device-based treatments with hormone wellness, weight loss, and nutrition services, we see connections that other practices might miss. Our comfortable, boutique clinical space on W. Catawba Avenue in Cornelius serves clients from across the region - Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, Denver, and the broader Charlotte metro area. SkinPen® treatment in the Lake Norman area doesn't get more personal or more professional than this.</p><h2>Schedule Your Microneedling Consultation</h2><p>Stop guessing what your skin needs. A consultation at REFRESH LKN gives us the chance to evaluate your specific concerns, recommend how many sessions would make sense for you, and talk through whether combining SkinPen® with other services could speed up your results. It's a conversation, not a commitment - and it's the fastest way to get a clear plan for your skin.</p><p>Ready to see what professional microneedling near you can do? <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, in Cornelius - and we'd love to meet you.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How much does SkinPen® microneedling cost?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the treatment area and whether you're adding enhancements like PRP. We're happy to discuss specific pricing during your consultation, and we can also walk you through any package options that might make a series more affordable.</p><h3>How long does a SkinPen® appointment take?</h3><p>Plan for about 60 to 90 minutes total, including numbing time. The actual microneedling portion is typically 30 to 45 minutes for a full face, but we never rush - your appointment takes as long as it needs to.</p><h3>Can SkinPen® be combined with PRP?</h3><p>Absolutely. Adding PRP (platelet-rich plasma) to your SkinPen® session enhances collagen stimulation by delivering your own concentrated growth factors directly into the micro-channels. It's one of our favorite add-ons, and we can talk through whether it's a good fit for your skin during your consultation.</p><h3>Is microneedling safe for darker skin tones?</h3><p>Yes - and this is a really important distinction. SkinPen® is safe for all Fitzpatrick skin types, including darker skin tones that may not be good candidates for certain laser treatments. Because microneedling doesn't use light or heat energy, the risk of hyperpigmentation is significantly lower.</p><h3>How far in advance should I book?</h3><p>We recommend booking at least one to two weeks ahead, especially if you have a specific event or timeline in mind. If you're planning a series, we can schedule all of your sessions at once so you get your preferred appointment times.</p><h3>Does microneedling hurt?</h3><p>Most clients describe the sensation as a mild prickling or vibrating feeling - not painful, just noticeable. The topical numbing cream we apply beforehand does the heavy lifting, and the vast majority of our clients say it's far more comfortable than they expected. Compared to more aggressive resurfacing options, the discomfort level is minimal.</p>
