<h1>Diolaze® Laser Hair Removal</h1><p>You've spent years shaving, waxing, tweezing - and for what? Stubble by tomorrow, ingrown hairs by the weekend, and irritated skin that never quite feels smooth. If you're tired of the endless cycle of temporary hair removal, you're not alone. And you're ready for something better.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, we offer Diolaze® laser hair removal - one of the most advanced diode laser systems available for permanent hair reduction. It's fast, comfortable, and effective across a wide range of skin tones and body areas. Our board-certified nurse practitioner personally oversees every treatment in our Cornelius clinic, which means you're getting medical-grade care in a setting that actually feels good to walk into. Whether you're dealing with unwanted facial hair, razor burn along your bikini line, or just want silky legs without the daily hassle, this page covers everything you need to know before your first session.</p><h2>How Diolaze® Delivers Permanent Hair Reduction</h2><p>Diolaze® works by sending a concentrated beam of laser energy - specifically, an 810nm diode wavelength - directly into the hair follicle. The melanin (pigment) in the hair absorbs that energy, which heats and damages the root. When the follicle is destroyed during its active growth phase, called anagen, it can no longer produce new hair. That's where the "permanent" part comes in.</p><p>What makes Diolaze® stand out from other laser systems is the combination of a large treatment spot size and a built-in sapphire cooling tip. The larger spot size means we can cover more surface area in less time - great news if you're treating your legs, back, or chest. And that cooling tip? It keeps the skin's surface cool and comfortable throughout the treatment, which is why so many of our clients describe this as pain-free laser hair removal. Most don't even need numbing cream.</p><p>One thing we always want to be upfront about: we call this permanent hair reduction, not permanent hair removal. After a full series of treatments, most people see a dramatic and long-lasting reduction in hair growth - we're talking 80% or more. But hormones, aging, and genetics can occasionally trigger new growth, which is why some clients return once or twice a year for a quick touch-up. The difference between that and shaving every other day? Night and day.</p><p>This is a true medical-grade laser, not a spa-grade IPL device you might find at a chain salon. That distinction matters, and here's why.</p><h2>IPL vs. Laser Hair Removal</h2><p>If you've been researching hair removal options around Lake Norman or the greater Charlotte area, you've probably come across both IPL and laser. They sound similar, but the technology - and the results - are quite different.</p><p>IPL stands for Intense Pulsed Light. It uses broad-spectrum light, meaning multiple wavelengths at once. Think of it like a flashlight with a wide beam. Laser, on the other hand, uses a single, focused wavelength. Diolaze® operates at 810nm, which is specifically chosen to target hair follicles with precision while minimizing impact on surrounding skin.</p><p>What does that mean for you? Laser treatments like Diolaze® tend to be more effective, require fewer sessions, and work safely on a broader range of skin tones. IPL can be a fine option for some people, but if you want the most efficient, reliable path to smooth skin - especially if you have a medium to deeper complexion - a true diode laser is the way to go. That's exactly what we use at REFRESH.</p><h2>Laser Hair Removal for All Skin Types</h2><p>For a long time, laser hair removal wasn't safe for everyone. Older technology struggled with darker skin tones, sometimes causing burns or uneven results. If you've been told in the past that you're not a candidate, we understand the hesitation - but the technology has come a long way.</p><p>Diolaze® is designed with adjustable settings that allow us to customize the energy level, pulse duration, and cooling for each individual client. This makes it safe and effective across a broad range of skin types, from very fair to deep complexions. The key is having a trained, experienced provider who knows how to dial in those settings - and at REFRESH Medical Spa &amp; Wellness, our board-certified nurse practitioner does exactly that for every single treatment.</p><p>During your consultation in Cornelius, we'll assess your skin tone, hair color, and the specific area you want to treat. From there, we build a personalized plan that's designed to give you the best possible results for your body. No guessing.</p><h2>Popular Treatment Areas</h2><h3>Bikini and Brazilian</h3><p>This is our most requested area, hands down. Bikini and Brazilian laser hair removal frees you from the cycle of painful waxing and razor bumps in one of the most sensitive areas on your body. Diolaze®'s built-in cooling tip makes a real difference here - most clients tell us it's far more comfortable than they expected. We typically recommend 5–6 sessions for the bikini area, spaced about six weeks apart. And yes, this is a completely routine treatment at a professional clinical setting. Nothing to feel awkward about.</p><h3>Underarm Hair Removal</h3><p>If you're new to laser, underarms are a fantastic place to start. Treatment takes less than 15 minutes, results show up quickly, and the freedom from razor burn and irritation is immediately noticeable. Many of our clients from Huntersville, Davidson, and Mooresville tell us this was the treatment that convinced them to do their legs next.</p><p>If you're ready to learn what Diolaze® can do for you, give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online - we'd love to get you started.</p><h3>Legs, Back, Face, and More</h3><p>Virtually any area with unwanted hair is fair game. Full legs, arms, chest, back, upper lip, chin, sideburns - we treat it all. Diolaze®'s large spot size makes even bigger areas like a full back or full legs surprisingly quick to treat. Whatever's bothering you, we can help.</p><h2>What to Expect During Treatment</h2><h3>Before Your First Session</h3><p>Preparation is simple. Shave the treatment area about 24 hours before your appointment - this allows the laser to target the follicle beneath the surface without wasting energy on surface hair. For several weeks beforehand, avoid waxing, tweezing, or plucking, since those methods remove the root that the laser needs to target. You'll also want to stay out of direct sun exposure and skip self-tanners in the area being treated.</p><p>When you arrive at our Cornelius location, we'll do a quick skin assessment and walk you through what to expect. No numbing cream is usually needed, thanks to Diolaze®'s cooling technology.</p><h3>During Your Diolaze® Session</h3><p>Most clients describe the sensation as a warm snap against the skin, immediately followed by a cooling relief from the sapphire tip. It's very tolerable. Treatment time depends entirely on the area - an upper lip might take five minutes, while full legs could take 30 minutes or a bit more. You'll be in one of our comfortable treatment suites the entire time, with your practitioner guiding the handpiece across the treatment area with care and precision.</p><h3>After Treatment and Between Sessions</h3><p>You might notice some mild redness or warmth right after your session, similar to a light sunburn. This typically fades within a few hours. Over the next one to three weeks, treated hairs will gradually shed - this is a good sign. It means the follicles were effectively targeted.</p><p>Sessions are spaced four to six weeks apart to catch new hairs as they enter their active growth cycle. Most clients in the Lake Norman area complete four to six sessions for their best results, though some areas - particularly hormonal zones like the chin or bikini - may benefit from a couple of additional treatments.</p><h2>Before and After Expectations</h2><p>Results from Diolaze® laser hair removal build over time, so patience pays off. After your first one or two sessions, you'll likely notice thinner regrowth and patches where hair simply doesn't come back. By the time you've completed four to six sessions, most clients see a dramatic reduction - smoother skin, finer texture, and far less time spent thinking about hair removal at all.</p><p>An occasional maintenance session once or twice a year keeps everything looking its best. We encourage you to ask about before-and-after photos during your consultation at REFRESH so you can see real results from real clients.</p><h2>Schedule Your Consultation at REFRESH</h2><p>Every great result starts with a conversation. At REFRESH LKN, your treatment plan begins with a one-on-one consultation where we assess your skin, talk about your goals, and map out a Diolaze® treatment schedule that fits your life. Whether you're coming from Cornelius, Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, or anywhere else in the Charlotte metro, our clinic at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106 is easy to find and even easier to love.</p><p>We'd love to help you ditch the razor for good. <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> to get started. Smooth skin is closer than you think.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How long does a Diolaze® appointment take?</h3><p>It depends on the area being treated. Small areas like the upper lip or underarms can be finished in under 15 minutes, while larger areas like full legs or a full back may take 30 to 45 minutes. We'll give you a clear time estimate during your consultation so you can plan your day.</p><h3>Does laser hair removal work on blonde, red, or gray hair?</h3><p>Diolaze® targets melanin - the pigment inside the hair - so very light blonde, red, white, or gray hairs often don't have enough pigment to absorb the laser energy effectively. During your consultation, we'll evaluate your hair color and let you know what kind of results you can realistically expect.</p><h3>Can I get treated if I have a tan?</h3><p>Active tans and sunburns need to fade before treatment, since the laser can't distinguish between melanin in the skin and melanin in the hair follicle. If you're planning summer sessions, we'll help you time things so you stay safe and still make progress on your treatment plan.</p><h3>How much does Diolaze® laser hair removal cost?</h3><p>Pricing varies based on the size of the treatment area and the number of sessions in your plan. We offer packages that bring down the per-session cost. Call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or reach out through our website to get current pricing for the areas you're interested in.</p><h3>Is there any downtime after a session?</h3><p>There's no real downtime. Most clients go right back to their normal routine after leaving our office. We do recommend avoiding hot showers, saunas, and intense exercise for about 24 hours, and applying sunscreen to any treated areas that are exposed to sunlight.</p><h3>Can I combine Diolaze® with other treatments at REFRESH?</h3><p>Absolutely. Many of our clients pair laser hair removal with facials, chemical peels, or other skin treatments offered at REFRESH LKN. Your provider will advise on the best timing and sequencing so that everything works together without irritating your skin.</p>
<hr>
<h1>Lumecca® IPL Treatment</h1><p>You've tried the creams. You've layered on the serums. You've perfected your foundation routine to cover those stubborn brown spots and that persistent flush across your cheeks. But you're tired of covering things up - you want skin that actually looks clear and even without all the effort. That's exactly why we offer Lumecca® IPL at REFRESH LKN. Lumecca® is the most powerful intense pulsed light device available today, designed to deliver dramatic visible improvement in skin tone and clarity in far fewer sessions than traditional photofacial treatments. Whether it's years of accumulated sun damage, scattered age spots, or redness that never quite goes away, Lumecca® targets it at the source. And every single session at our Cornelius location is personally overseen by our board-certified nurse practitioner - because your skin deserves that level of attention.</p><h2>What Is Lumecca® IPL Photorejuvenation?</h2><p>Lumecca® is an intense pulsed light therapy device manufactured by InMode, one of the most respected names in medical aesthetic technology. It works by delivering controlled pulses of broadband light into the skin, where that energy is absorbed by pigmented cells and visible blood vessels beneath the surface. Here's what sets it apart: Lumecca® operates at a significantly higher peak power than traditional IPL devices. That means more energy delivered per pulse, which translates to more dramatic results - often in just one to two sessions instead of the four to six that older systems typically require.</p><p>It's worth noting that Lumecca® is not a laser. Lasers use a single wavelength of light, while Lumecca® uses a broad spectrum, allowing it to address multiple concerns at the same time. Pigmentation, redness, vascular irregularities - all in the same treatment. That efficiency is a big part of why IPL photorejuvenation has become one of the most requested skin rejuvenation services at REFRESH.</p><h2>Sun Damage, Age Spots &amp; Pigmentation</h2><p>Living around Lake Norman means spending time outdoors. Weekends on the water, afternoons on the golf course, years of soaking up Carolina sunshine - it all adds up. And over time, that cumulative UV exposure shows up as uneven skin tone, scattered sun spots, dark patches, and clusters of freckles that seem to multiply each summer. If you've noticed brown spots on your face, chest, or hands that weren't there a few years ago, you're seeing the visible result of melanin deposits that have settled into the skin.</p><p>Lumecca® targets those deposits directly. The light energy is absorbed by the excess melanin, breaking it apart. Over the next several days, those darkened cells rise to the surface of your skin, appearing temporarily darker before they naturally flake away. What's left behind is clearer, more even-toned skin. It's one of the most effective age spots and pigmentation treatments available - and clients across Cornelius, Davidson, and Mooresville consistently tell us how surprised they are by the results after just one session.</p><h2>Redness, Rosacea &amp; Vascular Concerns</h2><p>Persistent facial redness can feel like something you just have to live with. But you don't. Whether it's rosacea, broken capillaries, or visible spider veins across your cheeks, nose, or chest, Lumecca® addresses these vascular concerns with precision. The light energy is absorbed by hemoglobin - the pigment inside those visible blood vessels - causing them to collapse and be gradually reabsorbed by your body.</p><p>For clients dealing with chronic redness and rosacea treatment needs, this is often a turning point. Most people notice visible improvement after their very first session, with continued clearing over the following week. That constant flushed look? It doesn't have to be permanent.</p><p>If Lumecca® sounds like something you've been looking for, we'd love to talk through your specific concerns. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online - a quick conversation is all it takes to get started.</p><h2>What to Expect During Treatment</h2><h3>Before Your Session</h3><p>Every Lumecca® treatment at REFRESH starts with a one-on-one consultation. We'll assess your skin type, talk through your concerns, and confirm that you're a good candidate. Before your appointment, we'll ask you to avoid direct sun exposure, self-tanners, and certain photosensitizing medications for a set period. Your skin needs to be as close to its natural tone as possible - this is essential for both safety and effectiveness.</p><h3>During the Procedure</h3><p>Once you're settled in, we apply a cooling gel to the treatment area. The Lumecca® handpiece delivers pulses of light across the skin, and most clients describe the sensation as a warm snap - similar to a rubber band, but very brief. Sessions typically take between 15 and 30 minutes depending on the area being treated. No anesthesia is needed, and the vast majority of our clients tolerate it comfortably. Some areas are more sensitive than others, but nothing about the experience is overwhelming.</p><h3>Recovery &amp; Downtime</h3><p>This is one of the things people love most about Lumecca® - the downtime is minimal. Your skin may look slightly flushed or feel warm for a few hours after treatment, almost like a mild sunburn. Dark spots will actually darken before they lighten, which can catch some clients off guard, but it's a great sign. It means the treatment is working exactly as it should. Those darkened pigmented spots typically crust lightly and flake off within seven to ten days, revealing noticeably clearer skin underneath. Sun protection after treatment is non-negotiable - we'll send you home with clear instructions on how to take care of your skin during the healing window.</p><h2>Skin Tone &amp; Texture Results</h2><p>Most clients see significant skin tone and texture improvement after just one to two Lumecca® sessions. For more extensive sun damage or layered pigmentation concerns, a third session may be recommended to achieve the best possible outcome. But the results from even a single treatment are often striking enough that people around you start commenting.</p><p>Beyond clearing spots and reducing redness, Lumecca® stimulates collagen production in the treated skin. Over time, that means improved texture, tighter pores, and a firmer overall appearance. The cumulative effect is skin that looks genuinely refreshed - clearer, smoother, more even. The most common treatment areas are the full face, neck, décolletage, and hands, though we treat other areas too depending on your needs. With consistent SPF use and an occasional maintenance session, your results can last for years. This isn't a quick fix that fades in a month. It's real, lasting improvement.</p><h2>Ideal Candidates for Lumecca® IPL</h2><p>Lumecca® works best on lighter to medium skin tones - generally Fitzpatrick skin types I through IV. This is because the light energy targets contrast between the pigmented concern and surrounding skin, so there needs to be enough differentiation for safe, effective treatment. If you have visible sun damage, age spots, uneven pigmentation, or persistent facial redness and you want noticeable results without surgery or extended downtime, Lumecca® is likely a strong fit.</p><p>It's not recommended for actively tanned skin, and certain photosensitizing medications may require a pause before treatment. Very dark skin tones require a different approach. We always conduct a thorough consultation before your first session to make sure this is the right treatment for you - no guesswork involved.</p><h2>Why Cornelius Clients Choose REFRESH</h2><p>At REFRESH LKN, our board-certified nurse practitioner personally performs every Lumecca® treatment. That's not something you'll find at most medical spas in the Charlotte area. Your session isn't handed off to someone with less training - the person holding the handpiece has the clinical expertise to adjust parameters in real time based on what your skin needs.</p><p>We're also the only wellness and aesthetic clinic in the Lake Norman area that combines advanced light-based technologies like Lumecca® with services like CoolPeel® CO2 laser treatments, VirtueRF® microneedling, and VI Peel® chemical peels. When it makes sense, we can design a treatment plan that layers these services together for results that go well beyond what any single treatment can achieve. Clients come to us from Huntersville, Denver, and across the north Charlotte corridor because they want a thoughtful approach - not a cookie-cutter menu. Our space at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106 in Cornelius is designed to feel comfortable and welcoming, not clinical. And our team is here to educate you, answer every question, and help you feel confident in your decisions. No pressure. Ever.</p><p>If sun damage, brown spots, or stubborn redness have been on your mind, one conversation can help you figure out whether Lumecca® is the right next step. You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online, or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> - we'll take it from there. This might be exactly what you've been looking for.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How much does Lumecca® IPL cost at REFRESH?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the size of the treatment area and whether we're addressing the face alone or adding the neck, chest, or hands. We'll provide transparent pricing during your consultation so there are no surprises - just ask, and we'll walk you through everything.</p><h3>Does Lumecca® IPL hurt?</h3><p>Most clients describe the sensation as a quick warm snap - noticeable but very tolerable. It's significantly less uncomfortable than waxing, and the pulses are so brief that any discomfort passes almost immediately. No numbing cream is typically needed.</p><h3>Can Lumecca® be combined with other treatments?</h3><p>Absolutely. Many of our clients pair Lumecca® with CoolPeel® or VirtueRF® microneedling for a more complete skin rejuvenation plan. We space treatments appropriately so your skin has time to heal between sessions, and we'll map out a timeline that works for your goals.</p><h3>How long do results last?</h3><p>The pigmented spots and vascular lesions that Lumecca® treats don't come back - they're gone. However, new sun damage can develop over time if you're not consistent with sunscreen. Many of our clients schedule an annual maintenance session to keep their skin looking its best year-round.</p><h3>What should I avoid before and after treatment?</h3><p>Before treatment, avoid tanning, retinoid products, and direct sun exposure for at least two weeks. After your session, strict daily sunscreen use is essential - we recommend SPF 30 or higher, reapplied throughout the day. We'll give you a complete pre- and post-care guide at your consultation.</p><h3>What's the difference between Lumecca® and Forever Young BBL™?</h3><p>Both are light-based treatments, but they use different technology platforms and have different strengths. Lumecca® delivers higher peak power for more aggressive correction of existing damage, while Forever Young BBL™ excels at ongoing maintenance and anti-aging at the cellular level. During your consultation, we'll recommend the one that makes the most sense for your skin - or a combination of both if that's the best approach.</p>
<hr>
<h1>Advanced Medical Weight Loss</h1>
<hr>
<h1>Why Choose GLP-1 Based Treatments?</h1><p>You’ve done the work. The meal prepping, the early mornings, the calorie tracking—and maybe it worked for a while. But then it stopped. Or worse, the weight came back.</p><p>If that sounds familiar, we want you to hear this clearly: this is not a willpower problem. Your body is designed with powerful biological systems that resist weight loss. Hunger hormones increase when you cut calories. Metabolism adapts. Your body fights to maintain the weight it knows.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, we take a different approach.</p><p>Instead of forcing your body to comply, we use <strong>GLP-1 based treatments</strong> to work <em>with</em> your biology—helping your body respond the way it was meant to.</p><h2>How GLP-1 Based Treatments Work</h2><p>Your body naturally produces a hormone called GLP-1, which regulates appetite, satiety, and blood sugar. In many people struggling with weight, this system isn’t functioning optimally.</p><p><strong>GLP-1 based treatments</strong> enhance and amplify this natural pathway—supporting your body in a way that feels aligned, not forced.</p><p>What that means for you:</p><ul><li><p>Appetite becomes quieter and more manageable</p></li><li><p>Cravings lose their intensity</p></li><li><p>You feel satisfied with smaller portions</p></li><li><p>Blood sugar regulation improves</p></li><li><p>Your body becomes more responsive to fat loss</p></li></ul><p>These therapies were originally developed for metabolic health, but their impact on weight loss has been significant and well-studied. When used within a medically supervised program, they can be truly transformative.</p><h2>What to Expect from Treatment</h2><h3>Weekly Injections</h3><p>GLP-1 based treatments are administered as <strong>once-weekly subcutaneous injections</strong>. The process is quick, simple, and designed to fit seamlessly into your routine.</p><p>We start at a low dose and gradually increase over time. This allows your body to adjust, minimizes side effects, and helps us find the dose that works best for <em>you</em>.</p><p>This is not a one-size-fits-all approach. Your plan evolves based on how your body responds.</p><h3>Results &amp; Timeline</h3><p>Most clients begin to notice changes within the first few weeks:</p><ul><li><p>Reduced appetite</p></li><li><p>Less “food noise”</p></li><li><p>Natural portion control</p></li></ul><p>Meaningful weight loss typically develops over <strong>3–6 months</strong>, with continued progress over time. Clinical studies show significant average weight loss with GLP-1 based therapies when used consistently and appropriately.</p><p>Your results will depend on your body, your consistency, and your overall health—but with the right support, outcomes are consistently stronger than dieting alone.</p><h2>Medical Supervision Matters</h2><p>There are a lot of places offering weight loss injections right now.</p><p>We do things differently.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, every client is personally guided by a board-certified nurse practitioner. Your care begins with a comprehensive consultation, including health history and lab review. From there, we monitor your progress closely, adjust dosing, and support you every step of the way.</p><p>This is what medically supervised weight loss should feel like—intentional, personalized, and built around you.</p><h2>Beyond the Injection</h2><p>GLP-1 based treatments are powerful—but a shot alone isn’t a plan.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, we treat weight loss as part of a larger metabolic picture.</p><p>Depending on your needs, your plan may also include:</p><ul><li><p>Nutritional guidance</p></li><li><p>Hormone optimization</p></li><li><p>Vitamin and peptide support</p></li><li><p>Lifestyle strategies that actually stick</p></li></ul><p>Because when your body is supported from every angle, results become not just achievable—but sustainable.</p><h2>Who Is a Good Candidate?</h2><p>GLP-1 based treatments may be appropriate if:</p><ul><li><p>Your BMI is 30+, or 27+ with weight-related conditions</p></li><li><p>You’ve struggled to lose weight despite doing “everything right”</p></li><li><p>Hunger, cravings, or metabolic resistance are holding you back</p></li></ul><p>They may not be appropriate for individuals with certain medical conditions, including a history of medullary thyroid carcinoma, pancreatitis, or during pregnancy.</p><p>That’s why everything starts with a consultation—not a questionnaire.</p><h2>What to Expect at Our Lake Norman Weight Loss Clinic</h2><p>Walking into a weight loss clinic for the first time can feel vulnerable. We understand that—and we’ve designed this experience to feel different.</p><p>Your first visit starts with a real conversation. Our nurse practitioner reviews your full health history, previous weight loss efforts, and your goals. When appropriate, we may order lab work and perform a body composition analysis—because the number on the scale only tells part of the story.</p><p>From there, we build your personalized plan.</p><p>GLP-1 based treatments are prescribed as weekly injections, starting low and adjusting over time. Every step is overseen by the same provider who knows your name, your progress, and your goals.</p><h2>Personalized Dosing &amp; Ongoing Support</h2><p>Dose titration is one of the most important parts of successful treatment.</p><p>We start low and increase gradually, checking in regularly to monitor how you feel and how your body is responding. We also track <strong>body composition</strong>, not just weight—because losing fat while maintaining or building muscle tells a very different story than the scale alone.</p><p>And because REFRESH LKN offers comprehensive wellness services, we can layer in additional support when needed—creating a plan that works together, not in isolation.</p><h2>Appetite, Lifestyle &amp; Long-Term Success</h2><p>One of the most noticeable changes clients experience is how different their relationship with food feels.</p><p>The constant mental chatter—the “food noise”—becomes quieter. You’re no longer battling cravings all day. Instead, you’re able to make intentional choices with more ease.</p><p>But we don’t stop there.</p><p>We use this window of change to help you build habits that last—supporting your nutrition, strength, and overall metabolic health so your results hold over time.</p><p>Side Effects &amp; Safety</p><p>The most common side effects of GLP-1 based treatments are mild and temporary—typically including nausea, digestive changes, or decreased appetite early on.</p><p>These effects are most common during dose increases and usually improve as your body adjusts.</p><p>Because your treatment is medically supervised, we actively manage any side effects—adjusting your plan so you stay comfortable while continuing to progress.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><p><strong>Are there side effects?<br />
</strong> Some clients experience mild nausea, constipation, or stomach upset—especially early on. We adjust dosing as needed to keep you comfortable.</p><p><strong>How long will I be on treatment?<br />
</strong> Most clients stay on GLP-1 based treatments for several months to a year or longer, depending on goals. We guide both progress and maintenance.</p><p><strong>Do I need to follow a strict diet?<br />
</strong> No rigid meal plans. We provide guidance that supports your results without making your life harder.</p><p><strong>What happens if I stop?<br />
</strong> Without a transition plan, some weight regain is possible. That’s why we focus on sustainable habits and underlying metabolic health.</p><p><strong>Can this be combined with other services?<br />
</strong> Yes. Many clients benefit from combining GLP-1 based treatments with hormone optimization, vitamin therapy, and nutrition support.</p><h2>Start Your Weight Loss Program</h2><p>Taking this step is significant—and we respect that.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, there’s no pressure, no judgment, and no one-size-fits-all approach. Just a real conversation about where you are, where you want to be, and how we can help you get there.</p><p>Because you’ve waited long enough to feel like yourself again.</p>
<hr>
<h1>VI Peel® Chemical Peel</h1><p>You've tried the serums. You've been consistent with your skincare routine. But those dark spots are still there every morning, and your foundation is doing more heavy lifting than it should. Maybe it's acne scars that never quite smoothed out, or a dullness that settled in so gradually you almost didn't notice - until someone asked if you were tired when you felt perfectly fine. Whatever brought you here, know this: your skin isn't broken, and you're not out of options.</p><p>The VI Peel® is a medical-grade chemical peel designed to address exactly these kinds of frustrations - without the intense downtime that makes older peels feel like a gamble. At REFRESH LKN in Cornelius, our board-certified nurse practitioner personally evaluates every patient and selects the right peel formula for your specific skin. No guesswork. No generic approach. Just a clear plan built around what your skin actually needs right now.</p><h2>What Is a VI Peel® Treatment?</h2><p>The VI Peel® is not the kind of chemical peel you pick up at a drugstore or receive during a basic facial. This is a professional chemical peel formulated with a proprietary blend of clinical-strength ingredients - including TCA, retinoic acid, salicylic acid, phenol, and vitamin C - that work together to penetrate deeper layers of the skin where real change happens. It's the difference between buffing the surface and actually resurfacing.</p><p>One of the reasons we love this peel at REFRESH is that it's safe and effective for all skin types and tones. Many chemical peels carry a higher risk of post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation for darker skin, which limits who can safely benefit. The VI Peel® was specifically developed to minimize that risk, making it one of the most inclusive medical-grade facial peels available.</p><p>There are also several VI Peel® formulations - VI Peel® Original, VI Peel® Precision Plus, VI Peel® Purify, and VI Peel® Advanced - each designed to target different concerns. During your consultation, we'll determine which one matches your skin's needs so that every layer of product is working with purpose.</p><h2>Skin Concerns the VI Peel® Corrects</h2><h3>Hyperpigmentation and Dark Spots</h3><p>If uneven skin tone has become your biggest frustration, you're in good company. Sun damage, melasma, and post-inflammatory hyperpigmentation are among the most common reasons clients from Cornelius, Huntersville, and the broader Charlotte area walk through our door. Chemical exfoliation for dark spots works by accelerating cell turnover and breaking up excess melanin deposits beneath the surface. The VI Peel® Precision Plus formula is specifically built for hyperpigmentation treatment, delivering targeted uneven skin tone correction that lighter peels simply can't match.</p><h3>Acne Scars and Active Breakouts</h3><p>Acne doesn't always end when the breakout clears. The texture, the discoloration, the little reminders left behind - those can linger for months or years. The VI Peel® Purify formula was designed as a professional chemical peel for acne scars and active acne-prone skin. It helps smooth textural irregularities while fading the dark marks breakouts leave behind. If you've been dealing with both active acne and scarring at the same time, this peel can address them in a single treatment.</p><h3>Fine Lines, Wrinkles, and Sun Damage</h3><p>Years of UV exposure add up - even here in North Carolina where sunny days are the norm for a good chunk of the year. The VI Peel® stimulates collagen production and speeds up cell renewal, which makes it an effective chemical peel for sun damage and early signs of aging. Fine lines soften, skin clarity improves, and that overall firmness you thought was gone for good starts to come back. The VI Peel® for fine lines and wrinkles delivers visible change without the extended recovery of more aggressive resurfacing procedures.</p><h2>What to Expect During Treatment</h2><p>Everything starts with a one-on-one consultation. Our nurse practitioner will evaluate your skin type, review your concerns and history, and select the VI Peel® formula that's right for you. This isn't a conveyor belt experience - we take the time to understand what you're seeing in the mirror and what you'd like to change.</p><p>The application itself takes about 30 minutes. The peel solution is applied in layers, and most patients feel a mild tingling or warmth. No anesthesia is needed, and the sensation is very manageable. Once the peel is in place, you'll head home with a take-home aftercare kit - a hallmark of the VI Peel® system that gives you everything you need for the days ahead.</p><p>If you're ready to find out which VI Peel® formula fits your skin, we'd love to talk. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online.</p><h2>VI Peel® Recovery and Aftercare</h2><h3>The Peeling Process</h3><p>Here's where it gets interesting. Peeling typically begins around day three and continues through about day seven. Some patients experience noticeable sheets of peeling skin, while others see lighter, more subtle flaking. Both responses are completely normal. The skin resurfacing is happening underneath regardless of how dramatic the visible peeling looks, so don't panic if your experience doesn't match what you've seen on social media. The one non-negotiable rule: do not pick or pull at peeling skin. Let it release on its own.</p><h3>Post-Peel Care Guidelines</h3><p>For the first several days, use only the products in your take-home aftercare kit. This isn't the time to experiment with new serums or go back to your retinol. Strict sun avoidance is essential, and SPF 30 or higher is mandatory once you're past the initial healing window. Avoid active ingredients like retinol, glycolic acid, and vitamin C until your skin has fully recovered.</p><p>The good news? Most patients return to work and normal activities within a day or two. Peeling can be managed with moisturizer, and social downtime is minimal compared to deeper skin resurfacing treatments like CoolPeel® CO2 laser. VI Peel® recovery and aftercare is straightforward - just follow the instructions and let your skin do its thing.</p><h2>Chemical Peel Results: Before and After</h2><p>After a single VI Peel® treatment, most patients notice a brighter, more even complexion within the first couple of weeks. Dark spots begin to fade, texture smooths out, and fine lines look softer. But the real magic happens over time. Collagen remodeling continues for four to six weeks after your peel, so results keep improving long after the peeling phase ends.</p><p>For the most dramatic chemical peel results before and after transformation, we typically recommend a series of three to four treatments spaced about four to six weeks apart. During your consultation at REFRESH, we can show you before-and-after photos from real patients and help set expectations based on your specific concerns.</p><p>The VI Peel® also pairs beautifully with other medspa skin rejuvenation treatments we offer in Cornelius. Many of our clients from Davidson, Mooresville, and across the Lake Norman area combine their peel series with Forever Young BBL™ treatments or SkinPen® microneedling to build a full skin health plan. Your provider will help you decide what combination makes sense for where your skin is today and where you want it to be.</p><h2>Why Choose REFRESH LKN in Cornelius</h2><p>At REFRESH, our board-certified nurse practitioner personally performs and oversees every VI Peel® treatment. Your peel is never handed off to someone still learning the ropes. This matters because selecting the right formula and monitoring your skin's response requires clinical expertise - not just product knowledge.</p><p>We're Lake Norman's only clinic combining advanced lasers with hormone wellness, personalized weight loss, and injectables, which means we can support your skin health from every angle. If hormonal changes are driving your pigmentation or breakouts, we can address that too - not just treat the surface symptoms.</p><p>Our space at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, is designed to feel warm and comfortable, especially if this is your first time getting a professional chemical peel. Clients come to us from Cornelius, Huntersville, Davidson, Mooresville, and throughout the Charlotte metro area because the experience here feels personal. Because it is.</p><p>Your skin doesn't have to stay stuck in a cycle of frustration. If dark spots, acne scars, dullness, or fine lines have been bothering you, a VI Peel® at REFRESH LKN might be exactly the reset your skin has been waiting for. We'll help you figure out the right formula, build a plan around your goals, and walk you through every step. <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> - we're here whenever you're ready.</p><h2>VI Peel® FAQs</h2><h3>How many VI Peel® sessions will I need?</h3><p>Most patients see noticeable improvement after one treatment, but a series of three to four peels spaced four to six weeks apart delivers the best results for stubborn concerns like melasma or deep acne scarring. After completing a series, many clients schedule a maintenance peel every three to four months to keep their results looking fresh.</p><h3>Does the VI Peel® hurt?</h3><p>Most patients describe a mild tingling or warming sensation during application, but it's very tolerable - nothing that would make you want to stop. If you've been nervous about chemical peels being painful, the VI Peel® is a great first experience because comfort is built into the formulation.</p><h3>Can I wear makeup during the peeling phase?</h3><p>We recommend avoiding makeup for the first two to three days while your skin is most sensitive. Once peeling starts, you can apply mineral-based makeup lightly if needed, but stick to clean brushes and gentle products to avoid irritation or infection.</p><h3>Is the VI Peel® safe during pregnancy or breastfeeding?</h3><p>The VI Peel® is not recommended during pregnancy or breastfeeding due to ingredients like retinoic acid and salicylic acid. If you're planning to become pregnant, currently expecting, or nursing, we'll recommend alternative treatments that are safe for you during this time.</p><h3>How does the VI Peel® compare to microneedling or laser resurfacing?</h3><p>The VI Peel® focuses on chemical exfoliation to address tone and texture, while SkinPen® microneedling stimulates collagen through controlled micro-injuries and CoolPeel® CO2 laser targets deeper resurfacing. During your consultation, we'll help you decide which treatment - or combination - is the best fit based on your skin's condition and your goals.</p><h3>What if my skin doesn't peel very much?</h3><p>This is one of the most common concerns we hear, and it's completely normal. Minimal visible peeling does not mean the treatment didn't work - the chemical exfoliation is happening at a cellular level whether or not you see dramatic sheets of skin. Your results will still show up in the weeks that follow as brighter, smoother skin emerges.</p>
<hr>
<h1>PDO Threads</h1><p>You see it in photos first. Maybe it's the softening along your jawline, or a heaviness in your lower face that wasn't there a few years ago. Your neck looks different in profile. You still feel like you — vibrant, sharp, confident — but the mirror isn't quite keeping up. If you're not ready for surgery (and honestly, you may not need it), but you've outgrown what serums and creams can do, PDO threads might be exactly the middle ground you've been looking for. This is one of the most requested treatments we offer at REFRESH LKN, and for good reason. It's a minimally invasive lift — real, visible, structural improvement — performed right here in our Cornelius office by a board-certified nurse practitioner who personally handles every single procedure. Clients across the Lake Norman and Charlotte area are discovering what a well-placed thread lift can do, and we'd love to show you why.</p><h2>What Is a PDO Thread Lift?</h2><p>PDO stands for polydioxanone — a medical-grade, absorbable suture material that's been used safely in surgery for decades. During a thread lift, these fine sutures are placed strategically beneath the skin to create two distinct effects. First, there's an immediate mechanical lift. The threads physically reposition sagging tissue, giving you visible improvement the same day. Second — and this is where it gets really exciting — those threads trigger your body's natural collagen production along the entire thread pathway. So even after the sutures dissolve over four to six months, your skin continues to rebuild and firm from within.</p><p>There are different types of threads we use depending on your goals. Smooth threads are ideal for collagen stimulation and overall skin tightening — think of them as an internal scaffolding that encourages your skin to renew itself. Barbed or cogged threads do the heavier lifting, physically gripping and repositioning tissue that's lost its hold. This absorbable suture lift gives you real structural change — a non-surgical facelift alternative without general anesthesia, without incisions, and without weeks of hiding out at home. It's the kind of result that makes people ask if you've been on vacation.</p><h2>Common Treatment Areas</h2><p>At REFRESH, the most popular areas we treat with PDO threads are the jowls and lower face, where restoring jawline definition makes a dramatic difference. Mid-face and cheek lifting is another frequent request — when the cheeks flatten or droop, it changes your entire expression, even at rest. A minimally invasive neck lift with threads can address banding and loose skin below the chin, which is one of the hardest areas to treat with products alone. We also perform subtle brow lifts for clients dealing with hooded or heavy brows, and threads work beautifully to soften deep nasolabial folds — those stubborn lines running from nose to mouth.</p><p>Every treatment plan is customized. We can address multiple areas in one session or stage treatments over time depending on your priorities and budget. There's no one-size-fits-all approach to sagging skin treatment — what matters is what bothers you most and what will give you the biggest impact.</p><h2>What to Expect During Your Appointment</h2><h3>Consultation and Planning</h3><p>Every PDO thread lift at REFRESH starts with a real conversation. Our nurse practitioner sits down with you one-on-one — no rushing, no assistants running through a script. She evaluates your facial anatomy, listens to what you're noticing, and gives you an honest assessment of what threads can and can't accomplish. That honesty matters. Sometimes threads alone are the answer. Other times, we might suggest pairing them with dermal fillers to restore lost volume, or RF microneedling with VirtueRF® or Morpheus8® to improve skin texture, or Forever Young BBL™ to even out tone. The point is building a plan around you — not selling you a menu item.</p><h3>The Procedure Itself</h3><p>The entire treatment happens right here in our Cornelius office and typically takes 30 to 60 minutes depending on how many areas we're addressing. We apply local anesthesia to keep you comfortable, and most clients tell us they feel only mild pressure or a gentle tugging sensation. Threads are inserted through tiny entry points using thin cannulas or needles — no incisions, no stitches, no scars. You'll see an immediate lift before you even leave. And honestly? Most people say it was far more comfortable than they expected. That's usually the first thing they mention.</p><p>If you're curious whether PDO threads might work for what you're seeing in the mirror, we're happy to talk it through. Call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online — a consultation is the best place to start.</p><h2>Recovery and Results</h2><h3>Recovery Timeline</h3><p>One of the biggest reasons clients choose a thread lift over surgery is the recovery — or rather, the lack of it. Most people return to their normal routine within two to three days. You can expect some mild swelling, tenderness, and possibly light bruising around the entry points, but nothing that requires pain medication beyond what's in your medicine cabinet. For two to four weeks after treatment, we ask that you avoid sleeping face-down, skip intense workouts, hold off on dental procedures, and be mindful of extreme facial expressions. That's it. No general anesthesia recovery, no drains, no compression garments, no taking weeks off work. PDO thread lift recovery time is genuinely minimal compared to what most people imagine.</p><h3>When Results Appear</h3><p>Here's what we love about this treatment: the results actually get better with time. You'll see an immediate lift on day one — and that improves as any swelling settles over the next week or two. But the real magic happens over the following three to six months as collagen remodels along those thread pathways. Your skin gets firmer, smoother, and more defined gradually. Skin tightening without surgery that actually keeps working long after you've left our office. Final results typically last 12 to 18 months depending on your age, skin quality, and lifestyle factors. Maintenance treatments can extend those results and continue building collagen over time, which is one of the things that makes this anti-aging treatment so appealing to our Cornelius clients.</p><h2>Why Clients Choose REFRESH LKN</h2><p>Thread lifts are technique-dependent procedures. The person placing those threads needs to understand facial anatomy at a deep level — not just where to insert, but how tissue moves, where tension should be created, and how the face ages as a whole. At REFRESH, our board-certified nurse practitioner performs every thread lift personally. This isn't delegated to technicians or handed off to someone you haven't met.</p><p>What also sets us apart is that we see the full picture. As Lake Norman's only medspa combining advanced aesthetic treatments with hormone wellness and personalized weight loss, we understand that aging isn't just about what's happening on the surface. Hormones, nutrition, skin quality, volume loss, and laxity all play a role. That means when you come to us for a thread lift, we're thinking about how it fits into your bigger picture — not just placing threads in isolation. Clients from Mooresville, Davidson, Huntersville, and across the Charlotte area choose REFRESH because it feels different here. It's a warm, boutique environment where you're a person, not a number.</p><h2>Is a PDO Thread Lift Right for You?</h2><p>The best candidates for PDO threads are people with mild to moderate skin laxity who still have reasonably good skin quality. That tends to be clients in their 30s through 60s, though candidacy is really about what your skin looks like today — not a number on your birthday card. If you've been relying on BOTOX® and fillers but feel like you need something more structural, threads can be a perfect complement. They add the lift that injectables alone can't provide.</p><p>We'll also be straightforward with you: if your laxity is severe, a surgical facelift may give you a better outcome, and we'll tell you that honestly during your consultation. No pressure, no upsell. Just a clear picture of what will actually work for your specific face and goals.</p><p>If you've been thinking about a thread lift — or even just wondering what your options are — we'd love to meet you. Schedule a consultation at REFRESH LKN in Cornelius by calling <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or use our online scheduling to <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> at a time that works for you. No commitment, no pressure. Let's talk about what's possible.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How much does a PDO thread lift cost?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the number of threads used and the areas being treated, so it varies from person to person. During your consultation, we'll give you a clear breakdown based on your specific treatment plan — no surprises.</p><h3>Can PDO threads be combined with BOTOX® or fillers?</h3><p>Absolutely, and in many cases that combination produces the most natural-looking results. We typically recommend spacing treatments about two to four weeks apart so each one can settle properly, and we'll map out the ideal timing during your consultation.</p><h3>How many threads will I need?</h3><p>Thread count depends entirely on the areas being treated and the degree of lift you're looking for. It can range anywhere from four threads for a targeted area to twenty or more for a full lower face and neck treatment. Your nurse practitioner will recommend the right number during your assessment.</p><h3>Are there risks or side effects?</h3><p>As with any procedure, there are potential risks including infection, temporary asymmetry, thread migration, or slight dimpling at entry points. These complications are uncommon and are significantly reduced when the procedure is performed by an experienced provider who understands facial anatomy — which is exactly why provider selection matters so much.</p><h3>Will people notice I had something done?</h3><p>Most clients hear comments like "you look so rested" or "your skin looks amazing" rather than "did you get work done?" The lift is gradual and refined, not dramatic or pulled. That natural-looking quality is one of the reasons this treatment is so popular.</p><h3>Does REFRESH offer financing for PDO thread treatments?</h3><p>We want to make sure cost isn't a barrier to feeling your best. Ask our team about available financing options when you schedule your consultation — we're happy to walk you through what's available so you can make a plan that fits your budget.</p>
