<h1>Skinwave Hydrofacial</h1><p>You've been doing the work — the cleansers, the serums, the SPF every morning. And still, your skin looks… tired. Flat. Like everything you're applying just sits on the surface instead of actually doing anything. It's frustrating, and you're not imagining it. Most over-the-counter products simply can't penetrate deeply enough to make the kind of difference you're hoping to see.</p><p>That's exactly why we brought Skinwave® to REFRESH LKN. This isn't your typical spa facial. It's a medical-grade treatment that cleanses, exfoliates, extracts, and infuses active ingredients into your skin — all in a single session. The result? Skin that looks plumper, brighter, and genuinely refreshed. Not next week. Right away.</p><p>Every Skinwave® treatment at REFRESH is performed under the oversight of our board-certified nurse practitioner, which means your skin is in clinical hands, not just cosmetic ones. If you've been searching for a deep pore cleansing facial in Cornelius, NC that actually delivers, this is it.</p><h2>What Is a Skinwave® Hydrofacial?</h2><p>Skinwave® is an aqua facial skin rejuvenation system that uses water and solution-based technology to deeply cleanse, gently exfoliate, extract impurities, and infuse your skin with targeted active serums. Think of it as a facial that works from the inside out rather than just buffing the surface.</p><p>What sets Skinwave® apart from other hydrofacial systems is the technology behind it. During your treatment, we use hydrogen therapy to deliver powerful antioxidant benefits directly to your skin. Then electroporation — a gentle, non-invasive technique — helps push customized serum cocktails deeper into the skin than topical application ever could. That means the hyaluronic acid, peptides, and brightening agents we select for you actually reach the layers where they can make a real difference.</p><p>There are no needles, no downtime, and no discomfort. Most people describe the experience as genuinely relaxing. And because we customize the serum selection for each client, this is a treatment that works across all skin types and tones. Whether your main concern is dullness, congestion, dehydration, or uneven texture, the Skinwave® system adapts to you.</p><h2>Deep Pore Cleansing and Serum Infusion</h2><h3>Cleansing and Exfoliation</h3><p>We start by clearing away what's standing between you and healthy-looking skin. The Skinwave® system uses an aqua-based exfoliation method that gently loosens and lifts dead skin cells, surface debris, and buildup without the roughness of traditional scrubs or microdermabrasion. Water and mild solutions do the heavy lifting here, so the process feels soothing rather than abrasive.</p><p>This first step is essential. By removing that outer layer of dull, spent skin cells, we create a clean canvas that's ready to absorb everything that comes next. It's an exfoliation and hydration facial rolled into one — your skin is already starting to look fresher before we even get to the good stuff.</p><h3>Extraction and Purification</h3><p>Next, we address what's hiding in your pores. The system uses gentle vacuum-assisted extraction to draw out blackheads, excess sebum, and the kind of stubborn congestion that makes pores look larger than they are. It's painless — nothing like the manual extractions you might be dreading.</p><p>During this phase, hydrogen water infusion delivers antioxidant-rich hydrogen molecules directly into the skin. This helps calm any inflammation and neutralize free radicals right at the moment your skin is most receptive. If you've been dealing with oily skin and congested pores, this step alone can feel like a revelation.</p><h3>Serum Infusion and Hydration</h3><p>Here's where the Skinwave® really shines. Using electroporation technology, we drive customized serums deep into your freshly cleansed skin. We're talking hyaluronic acid for plumping hydration, peptides for firmness, brightening agents for uneven tone, and growth factors for repair — whatever your skin needs most.</p><p>The serums we use are medical-grade formulations that you simply won't find on a retail shelf. And because we select them based on your individual concerns — whether that's dullness, fine lines, dehydration, or sun damage — this serum infusion facial is never the same twice. Your skin gets exactly what it's asking for, delivered exactly where it needs to go. That's the difference between a skin hydration therapy and just putting on a fancy moisturizer.</p><p>If you're curious about what a Skinwave® session could do for your skin specifically, we'd love to talk you through it. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online whenever you're ready.</p><h2>Skin Concerns This Treatment Addresses</h2><p>One of the reasons we love the Skinwave® system is its versatility. A dull, lackluster complexion? This is one of the most effective brightening facials for dull skin we offer — clients often say they look like they just came back from a week of sleep and sunshine. Oily or congested skin with enlarged pores and persistent blackheads responds beautifully to the extraction and purification phases.</p><p>If dehydration and early fine lines are your main concerns, the deep serum infusion restores moisture at a level your daily routine simply can't match. Uneven skin texture or tone — from old breakouts, sun exposure, or just the passing of time — smooths out noticeably after even a single treatment. And if you've got a wedding, event, or important meeting on the calendar, Skinwave® makes a perfect pre-event glow treatment with zero risk of redness or peeling.</p><p>At REFRESH, we assess your skin individually at every appointment and adjust the treatment accordingly. This is a non-invasive facial resurfacing experience designed around you — never a one-size-fits-all approach.</p><h2>Why Choose a Medical Spa Facial in Cornelius</h2><p>There's nothing wrong with a relaxing day-spa facial. But if you want results you can actually see and feel — the kind that change how your skin behaves over time — a medical-grade facial treatment is a different experience entirely.</p><p>At REFRESH LKN, our board-certified nurse practitioner oversees every treatment plan. That means the person guiding your skincare decisions understands your skin at a clinical level — the physiology, the aging process, how different conditions respond to different interventions. The Skinwave® system itself, along with the professional-strength serums we use, aren't available at standard day spas. This is equipment and product access that requires medical oversight.</p><p>What we also love is how well a Skinwave® hydrofacial fits into a bigger skin health strategy. It pairs beautifully with CoolPeel® CO2 treatments for deeper resurfacing, Forever Young BBL™ for photorejuvenation, or VirtueRF® microneedling for texture and scarring concerns. We can build a plan that addresses what's happening with your skin right now and where you want to be six months from now.</p><p>And you don't have to drive into uptown Charlotte to get this level of care. We're right here in Cornelius, serving clients from Mooresville, Davidson, Huntersville, Denver, and across the greater Lake Norman area. A medical spa facial in Cornelius means expert-level skin care close to home.</p><h2>What to Expect During Your Appointment</h2><p>Your Skinwave® session takes approximately 30 to 45 minutes from start to finish. No numbing is needed — most clients tell us it's one of the most relaxing treatments they've had at REFRESH. You might feel a gentle suction during extraction and a cool, soothing sensation during serum infusion, but nothing uncomfortable.</p><p>Immediately after, your skin may look slightly flushed, similar to a mild post-workout glow. That typically calms down within an hour. What you will notice right away is how your skin looks — plumper, clearer, more radiant. It's the kind of result that makes people ask what you've been doing differently.</p><p>There's no downtime at all. You can go right back to your normal day, apply sunscreen, and most clients are comfortable wearing makeup within a few hours. For the best cumulative results, we generally recommend a series of four to six sessions spaced two to four weeks apart. But honestly, even a single Skinwave® treatment delivers a noticeable skin texture improvement that you'll see in the mirror that same evening.</p><h2>Start Your Skinwave® Hydrofacial at REFRESH LKN</h2><p>Your skin deserves more than products that sit on the surface. At REFRESH Medical Spa &amp; Wellness, we personalize every Skinwave® treatment to your unique skin — your concerns, your goals, your life. Whether this is your first time exploring a medical-grade facial or you've been searching for something better than what you've tried before, we're here to help you figure out the right next step.</p><p>Booking is easy. You can <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. We're located at 18067 W. Catawba Avenue, Suite 106, Cornelius, NC 28031 — right in the heart of the Lake Norman community. You'll love how your skin feels after this one. Let's get you on the schedule.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How often should I get a Skinwave® Hydrofacial?</h3><p>For ongoing skin health and maintenance, most clients come in once a month. If you're working on a specific concern like persistent congestion or stubborn dullness, we may recommend more frequent sessions initially — every two to three weeks — and then space them out as your skin improves. We'll help you find the right rhythm during your first visit.</p><h3>Can I combine this with BOTOX® or other injectables?</h3><p>Absolutely, but timing matters. We typically recommend scheduling your Skinwave® session before injectables, or waiting about two weeks after your injectable appointment. Our team will walk you through the best sequencing based on what treatments you have planned.</p><h3>Is the Skinwave® Hydrofacial safe during pregnancy?</h3><p>Some of the active serums used during treatment may need to be adjusted or avoided during pregnancy. We always recommend letting us know at the time of booking so we can plan accordingly and ensure everything is safe for you and baby.</p><h3>What skincare products should I use after treatment?</h3><p>Keep it simple for the first 24 to 48 hours — a gentle cleanser, a hydrating moisturizer, and SPF are all you need. Avoid retinoids, exfoliating acids, and anything harsh during that window. We'll send you home with specific aftercare guidance based on the serums used during your session.</p><h3>How does Skinwave® compare to microneedling or chemical peels?</h3><p>Skinwave® is gentler with zero downtime, making it ideal for hydration, brightening, and regular maintenance. Treatments like SkinPen® microneedling or VI Peel® address deeper concerns such as scarring, significant texture issues, or advanced sun damage. They actually complement each other really well — many of our clients rotate between them as part of their ongoing skin care plan.</p><h3>Do you offer package pricing for multiple sessions?</h3><p>We do offer options for clients who want to commit to a series of treatments. Pricing and package availability can change, so the best way to get current information is to call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or reach out through our website. We're always happy to walk you through your options.</p>
<hr>
<h1>Jet Peel Facial</h1><p>You've tried the facials. The ones that smell lovely and feel relaxing and leave your skin looking pretty much the same by the next morning. Maybe you've even invested in serums that promise deep absorption but mostly sit on top of your skin, doing very little. The frustration is real — and it's exactly why we started offering the Jet Peel® at REFRESH LKN. This pressurized oxygen facial treatment delivers active ingredients past the surface of your skin, into the layers where real change happens. No needles. No downtime. No irritation. Just clean, hydrated, visibly brighter skin from a treatment that actually works as hard as you want it to. As a wellness and aesthetic clinic in Cornelius led by a board-certified nurse practitioner, we don't offer treatments that are all show. If it's on our menu, it's because the science backs it up — and our clients keep coming back for it.</p><h2>What Is a Jet Peel® Facial?</h2><p>The Jet Peel® is a medical grade facial that uses a high-velocity jet stream of micro-droplets — a controlled blend of saline, oxygen, and clinical-grade serums — to cleanse, exfoliate, and infuse your skin all at once. That's three steps happening simultaneously, which is part of what makes this treatment so efficient and so effective.</p><p>Unlike traditional facials that rely on manual extraction or surface-level exfoliation, the Jet Peel® works without ever touching your skin with an abrasive surface. There are no crystals, no suction tips, no chemical agents peeling away layers. Instead, the pressurized stream does the work — clearing out debris from deep within your pores while pushing customized serums into the skin at a cellular level. It's non-invasive skin rejuvenation that feels like a cool breeze on your face but performs like something far more advanced.</p><p>This is what separates a medical grade facial from a spa-day treat. The precision of the device, the quality of the serums, and the clinical knowledge guiding every decision — that's what gets results you can actually see.</p><h2>How Pressurized Oxygen Infusion Works</h2><p>Here's what's happening beneath the surface. The Jet Peel® creates a supersonic jet stream that breaks through the outermost barrier of dead skin cells — the same barrier that keeps your at-home serums from doing much. Once that barrier is bypassed, hydrating and corrective ingredients are delivered directly into the deeper dermal layers where your skin actually uses them.</p><p>The oxygen component plays its own role. Oxygen promotes faster cellular turnover, supports collagen production, and gives skin that lit-from-within quality that's hard to fake with makeup. Think of it as power-washing for your pores, but gentle enough for even the most reactive skin. The result is immediate: a skin hydration and brightening treatment that leaves your face looking plump, clear, and luminous — not red, not peeling, not "recovering." Just refreshed.</p><h2>Skin Concerns the Jet Peel® Addresses</h2><h3>Acne, Congestion, and Clogged Pores</h3><p>If you're dealing with breakouts, blackheads, or that persistently oily-yet-dehydrated skin that nothing seems to fix, the Jet Peel® offers a deep pore cleansing facial without the pain of manual extractions. The pressurized stream flushes out congestion from the inside out, clearing pores without squeezing, prodding, or leaving your skin angry and inflamed afterward. For clients struggling with active acne, this is a smart option — it cleans without aggravating. And because the treatment simultaneously infuses targeted serums, you're addressing breakouts and smoothing texture in the same session. That dual benefit — jet peel for acne and fine lines — is one of the reasons this treatment has become so popular at REFRESH.</p><h3>Fine Lines, Dullness, and Uneven Tone</h3><p>Loss of radiance, creeping fine lines, sun damage showing up as dark spots — these are the things that make you look tired even when you're not. As an anti-aging facial treatment, the Jet Peel® stimulates collagen, improves elasticity, and evens out hyperpigmentation over time. It's also an excellent maintenance treatment between more intensive services like CoolPeel® CO2 laser or RF microneedling with SkinPen® that we offer here at REFRESH. One treatment brightens. A series transforms your skin's baseline.</p><h3>Lymphatic Drainage and Puffiness</h3><p>This benefit surprises people. The jet stream naturally stimulates lymphatic flow in the face, which means reduced puffiness, less under-eye swelling, and a more defined, sculpted appearance. If you wake up looking puffy, carry tension and inflammation in your face, or want post-procedure recovery support, the lymphatic facial drainage component of this treatment is a real bonus. It's one of those results you feel as much as you see.</p><p>If anything here sounds like what your skin needs, we'd love to talk through it with you. Give us a call at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online — we're happy to help you figure out the right starting point.</p><h2>What to Expect During Treatment</h2><p>Your session at REFRESH starts with a skin assessment. We look at what's going on with your skin that day — hydration levels, congestion, sensitivity, areas of concern — and select serums customized to what you actually need. This isn't a one-formula-fits-everyone situation. If you're coming in for brightening, that's a different serum mix than someone focused on acne control or anti-aging.</p><p>Once we begin, you'll feel a cool, fine mist moving across your face. There's light pressure, but no pain. Most clients say it's refreshing — some even find it relaxing. The entire treatment takes about 30 to 45 minutes depending on the areas treated and how many concerns we're addressing.</p><p>When it's done, you're done. There's no redness to hide, no peeling phase to wait through. You can put makeup on, head to lunch in downtown Davidson, pick up your kids in Huntersville — whatever your afternoon looks like. Zero downtime. That's a big part of the appeal, especially for clients across the Lake Norman area who want real results without clearing their calendar.</p><h2>Hydrating Results You Can See Right Away</h2><p>After your first Jet Peel® session, your skin will look noticeably more hydrated, more even, and genuinely glowing. This isn't a subtle maybe-I-see-something difference. People notice. Your makeup sits differently. Your skin feels softer to the touch.</p><p>With a series of treatments, the results build. Fine lines soften progressively. Acne scars start to smooth. Tone becomes more uniform. For clients in the Charlotte area and surrounding communities like Mooresville and Denver who've been chasing that "my skin just looks good" baseline, this is how you get there — consistently, safely, and without aggressive interventions every time.</p><p>The Jet Peel® also pairs beautifully with other services we offer at REFRESH LKN. Many of our clients combine it with chemical peels, Forever Young BBL™ treatments, or their injectable appointments as part of an ongoing skin plan. Our board-certified nurse practitioner oversees treatment planning so that everything works together and nothing conflicts. Your skin gets the full picture, not just isolated fixes.</p><h2>Who Is a Good Candidate?</h2><p>Almost everyone. The Jet Peel® works on all skin types and all skin tones, which gives it an advantage over certain laser treatments that carry more restrictions. If you have sensitive skin and can't tolerate chemical peels or microdermabrasion, this is a fantastic alternative. If you're brand new to medical spa facials and want something effective but gentle for your first experience, this is an ideal starting point.</p><p>It's equally great for seasoned clients who already get regular treatments and want something to maintain their results between more intensive sessions. The only real contraindications are active open wounds or certain skin infections — and we'll talk through all of that before we begin.</p><h2>Book Your Jet Peel® Facial in Cornelius</h2><p>We built REFRESH LKN to be the kind of place where medical expertise meets genuine personal care — where you're not just a ticket number, you're someone whose skin and goals we actually know. Our Cornelius location on W. Catawba Avenue is easy to get to whether you're coming from Davidson, Huntersville, Mooresville, or anywhere across the greater Lake Norman region.</p><p>If you're ready to see what the Jet Peel® can do for your skin, <a href="https://refreshmedicalspaandwellness.myaestheticrecord.com/online-booking"><span class="underline">Book Appointment</span></a> online or call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong>. Not sure if this is the right fit? That's okay too. We're happy to chat through your options and point you in the right direction. Your skin deserves more than guesswork.</p><h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2><h3>How often should I get a Jet Peel® facial for best results?</h3><p>For most clients, we recommend a series of treatments spaced every two to four weeks to build on your results. After your initial series, a monthly maintenance session keeps your skin looking its best long-term. We'll recommend a specific schedule based on your skin concerns during your first visit.</p><h3>Can I combine a Jet Peel® with BOTOX® or filler appointments?</h3><p>Yes, though timing matters. We generally recommend doing the Jet Peel® before injectables rather than immediately after, since the pressurized stream could affect freshly placed product. If you'd like to schedule both, let us know when you book and we'll sequence everything properly.</p><h3>Is there any prep I need to do before my session?</h3><p>We ask that you avoid retinol products and heavy exfoliants for about 48 hours before your appointment. It's also best to come in without heavy sun exposure or an active sunburn. Beyond that, no special preparation is needed — just show up with a clean face.</p><h3>How does the Jet Peel® compare to HydraFacial?</h3><p>The biggest differences are in the delivery method and customization. The Jet Peel® uses no suction and no vortex tip — it relies entirely on pressurized micro-droplets, which makes it gentler on sensitive and reactive skin. It also allows for deeper serum infusion and more flexibility in what ingredients we use for your specific concerns.</p><h3>Will the Jet Peel® help with rosacea or reactive skin?</h3><p>It's actually one of the better facial options for rosacea-prone skin because there's no abrasion, no suction, and no harsh chemicals involved. We can select anti-inflammatory and calming serums specifically for reactive skin types. Many of our sensitive-skin clients say this is the first facial they've had that didn't leave them red or irritated.</p><h3>What does a Jet Peel® facial cost at REFRESH LKN?</h3><p>Pricing depends on the level of customization and whether you're booking a single session or a package series. We encourage you to call us at <strong>980-216-8484</strong> or book a consultation for current pricing — we're always happy to walk you through your options and find something that fits your goals and budget.</p>